Albeit the risk of privacy invasion , RFID tags are potential devices which do benefits a lot to humans if executed under strict regulations .
But with RFID tags , their children can remain safe and sound by lowering the case of being injured or lost as the devices can detect straightaway if such situations happen .
The tagging system is also a measure to deter the problems of having Alzheimer patients lost wandering at other places or patients collapsing outside of hospital area .
Hence , with such surveillance technology , the risk of patients getting injured while getting lost outside can be reduced to a minimal percentage .
Nonetheless , the generalization of certain simple surveillance technologies causes their existence to be found everywhere .
Since most couples in this competitive era have their own business or enterprise , home surveillance is then installed in order to guard their residence .
In conclusion , the effects of surveillance technology surrounding us are based on both major and minor premises , which are privacy and right of freedom of individuals , as well as the psychological condition .
In conclusion , the use of surveillance technology would be constructive to many aspects of our daily life as the benefits far outweigh the societal concerns .
For decades , people has been debating whether the use of surveillance technology should be banned , they argued that the used of surveillance technology is invading individual 's privacy .
