Genetic testing allows early detection of diseases which may be useful to mankind .
First , we will discuss on the relationship between employees and their employer 's organisation .
There is tension between employees and employer regarding genetic testing .
If genetic testing indicates susceptibility for diseases of an employee , there is chance that the employer will sack the employee .
This is supported by the fact that most people with disabilities or diseases are discriminated .
Opponents of this position may argue that such results should be revealed to protect employer from an employee vulnerable to illness .
However , the primary aim of employment should be work performance and efficiency , rather than on genetic testing .
Hence , individual should have the final say to protect them from environment that may harm them .
Critics of this position claim that insurer will also be at a disadvantage if such results are not revealed to them .
Genetic testing is a test performed to allow genetic diagnose of inherited diseases .
Not only so , genetic testing ( fingerprinting ) are also used to determine the child paternity .
[ 1 ] Genetic testing does have many pros in today society .
In the society today , many had debated that do we really have the right to have the final say whether to reveal the results of the testing as many will think that it will lead to many ethnic and social issues .
Or is it that it is a must to reveal it due to reality and we , individual do not have the final say to reveal our testing to the public .
In my own opinion , in the high technology society we are living in , we do not have the final say in revealing of our genetic results to the public .
Companies do have the right to know the genetic testing results of an individual who are applying for the job offer by them .
For example , if one contain inherited genetic disease like muscle dystrophy , it will be dangerous for them to work in the construction site .
Accident might occur and it may also result in death .
Although many has debated that this is discrimination as companies may not employ those who has inherited disease , but companies do have the right to choose employer with concern to their profits and the safety of others .
Individual that may inherit genetically disease should choose job that are beyond their reach .
Spouse of a couple do have the right to know the family disease of their partner .
If a couple is planning to have a child , it is best for them to go through genetic counseling if the parents are carrier of genetic disease [ 2 ] .
It will be unfair if the spouse kept the truth from their spouse .
It is a must to say it out and thus individual do not have the final say in revealing of their genetic results to the third parties
Education sector do have the right to know the genetic testing of their student .
Those with genetic diseases like mental retardation and Down syndrome are asked to be enrolled in school like MINDS and bright sparks .
Some may debate that this is a form of discrimination and violate the human rights of these children .
However , according to the American Association for mental retardation AAMR [ 3 ] , revealing of genetic testing results is not a form of discrimination but it is to be fair to those children with these genetic diseases as the child will be enrolled into the school that provide a better environment for them to study in .
Hence individual do not have the final say in revealing of their genetic results to the public .
All in all , in my own opinion , in the high technology society we are living in , we do not have the final say in revealing of our genetic results to the public .
It may not be disadvantage and can even benefits a lot of people based on the point mentioned above .
Thus individual requesting for genetic testing do not have the final say in whether to reveal the results of these testing .
However , due to the improper exploit of it , surveillance technology has become more of detrimental than beneficial .
