As a person age , physical changes in one 's body occurs and their functions degrade with time .
It was observed that more than one third of the elderly falls each year , and the chances of falling increases proportionately with age , and that three quarters of elderly falls were caused by " non-elderly friendly " design flaws of buildings .
Therefore , a prevention measure , in the form of upgrading public facilities is implemented to prevent this from happening .
This can be achieved through introduction of inventions such as steps-free buses , which helped ease the difficulty of elderly climbing up the steps of the bus .
