Eleven years ago , Singapore welcomes its first Newater plant , which is a turning point in Singapore 's technology development history .
Newater represents the technology that purifies the used water to make it clean and drinkable again ( The Write Staff ) .
During the last decade , the number of Newater plants increases to four .
Meanwhile , a new one is under construction .
What is more , in the near future , 30 % of the demand of water will come from Newater .
During Newater 's history , government , resources and the development of other technology show a significant influence on the development of Newater .
First of all , government plays a determining effect on the development of Newater .
Concerning about the situation of water supply in Singapore , the government officials decide to focus on the Newater technology to meet the water demand in Singapore especially for the industry and commercial use ( The Write staff ) .
The successful development of Newater is due to enough funds that government has invested .
With the support of Singapore government , the technology of Newater has blossomed and the fifth Newater plant has been successfully set up in the Chanqi area this year .
Besides the support of Singapore government , a lack of water supply pushes the development of Newater .
What is more , about 40 percent of the population around the world and more than 80 counties are dealing with the problem of lacking of water ( transl ) .
In consideration of Singapore , shortage of water results from several reasons such as geographic position , climate and increasing population .
These reasons contribute to the development of Newater .
With the pressure of water shortage , having its own water supply system becomes more and more necessary .
That is how the resource shortage leads to the development of Newater .
Government and resource are not the only factors that affect the development of Newater ; the development of other technology also plays an important role in accelerating the development of Newater .
In 1970s , Singapore already paid attention to the technology of its own water supply system ; however , the cost was enormous and technology is immature such as the unreliable membrane is not reliable ( The Write Staff ) .
Nowadays , the development of material science makes the technology of microfiltration succeed .
Meanwhile , there are some other breakthroughs in the technology helping the development of Newater .
The development of Newater is a good example to demonstrate it .
Government invests funds to support the research on Newater .
In addition , resource crisis , especially the shortage of water , pushes the development of Newater .
Meanwhile , the development of other technologies makes Newater possible .
All of these factors have a positive effect on development of Newater and make it succeed .
With time passing by , more and more new technology have been discovered or created , these technologies can be classified in two main patterns , one is the technologies which are developed by research , another type is the technologies which are resulted from serendipitous discoveries .
This article will discuss the similarities and differences between these two patterns of technologies .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) Penicillin was found by Alexander Fleming while he " observed that colonies of the bacterium Staphylococcus aureus could be destroyed by the mold Penicillium notatum .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) After Fleming observed that , he paid high attention to Penicillin , he discovered that Penicillin could kill many kinds of bacteria .
This important finding , however , had not been paid a lot attention until the 1940s when " when Howard Florey and Ernst Chain isolated the active ingredient and developed a powdery form of the medicine .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) Penicillin is " the first drugs that were effective against many previously serious diseases " ( Wikipedia , 2009 ) Although many of the bacteria have the resistance of Penicillin now , it is still in widely used .
Futuremore , the telephone was invented by Alexander Graham Bell in 1876 and " by 1884 , long distance connections were made between Boston , Massachusetts and New York City .
" ( Inventor , 2009 ) Bell was very interested in helping deaf people which leaded him to invent the telephone .
Also , " the telephone came as a direct result of his attempts to improve the telegraph .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) The invention of telephone is not a coincidence , but a lone-term research result .
In nowadays , telephone plays a very important role in our life , we can hardly live with them .
From the previous paragraphs of introduction of Penicillin and the telephone , we can easily find some similarities and differences .
First of all , both of these two technologies have benefit people and improved our life a lot , both of them help us in some aspects , Penicillin can help us to deal with some diseases which were hard to cure , the telephone can help us to communicate with others easier and make the world much smaller .
Secondly , both of the technologies become mature after a long time of hard working studying .
Both Penicillin and the telephone have not been used for years after they were invented ; many people put a lot of efforts to make them more mature and more useful .
The only difference between them two is that the Penicillin was found in accident while the telephone was invented by clear aim .
To conclusion , both Penicillin and telephone help people a lot and both of them are the product of hard working and long-term consummation .
The difference between them is whether the inventor has the clear purpose or not , which Bell had and Fleming had not .
Human needs are always unsatisfied .
At the same time health problems also created great needs for advanced medical technologies and facilities .
As years go by , industrialization emerged in many countries to meet various people 's needs , like job opportunities and economic growth .
However , the big success of industrialization has created a problem for our modern peoplehow to save our fast degrading environment ?
Thus , designing technologies in environmental friendly manner is one of the greatest human needs to protect our living environment and to ensure a sustainable economic development .
After the problem has been defined , which is the first step of engineering design ; engineers need to gather pertinent information about the problem .
For example , engineering who focusing on design environmental friendly transportation tools , must have the basic knowledge about the products of different types of fuel combustion and how they affect the environment .
They should also be updated about any latest methods to generate energy in environmental friendly ways , such as solar energy , tidal energy or wind energy , and their respective advantages and drawbacks .
Engineers will move on to next step once they are equipped with necessary knowledge .
The second step of the design process is generating different solutions to the problems .
For example , engineers basically come up with two main ways to make machineries and transportation tools less polluted .
First way is changing the way energy is generated , such as changing petrol engines which produce carbon dioxide and hydrocarbons to fuel cell which only produce water and oxygen .
This solution can be further divided by considering different types of method to generate energy in less polluting ways .
The other solution is dealing with the polluting products generated along the way .
For example , catalyst convertors are installed on cars to convert toxic gas carbon monoxide and hydrocarbons produced from non-fully combustion to non-toxic gas carbon dioxide and water .
Although different ways of solutions have been found out , not all are practical , so engineers also need to analyze and select a suitable solution .
For example , both of the two solutions we discussed before are theoretically correct , but today we only see convertor has been installed .
It is because changing the ways generating energy is very costly and the safety is unpredictable .
For example , fuel cells are very expensive , thus the cost of production will be so high that they will be unmarketable .
Another example , Hydro-powered cars , which actually have been produced but not used widely due to hydrogen is flammable , there are still big concerns of consumers ' safety .
In this step , engineers will also look at other factors like economic , social factor to filter the solutions .
When we look around , we can see the efforts put in by engineers , the power saved light bulb , solar water heater , car catalytic converters and etc .
These products are produced only after long and complicated designing process .
We should really be grateful to engineers who work dedicative to satisfy our needs .
Roger ( 2003 ) explained the difference between technological determinism and social determinism or the social construction of technology .
Otherwise , technology is a product of society and obviously is influenced by norms and values of the social system .
On the other hand , technological determinism is the belief that technology causes changes in society and this implies technology is somehow autonomous .
Roger did not agree with the latter belief .
Let us take a look at one example of a great human work in the late centuries : nuclear .
We are going to view the definition and some factors that make nuclear become a nuclear .
First of all , let us see the definition first .
According to Wikipedia , " A nuclear weapon is an explosive device that derives its destructive force from nuclear reactions , either fission or a combination of fission and fusion .
" Let us recall the Nagasaki and Hiroshima tragedies , both cities were destroyed completely because of this thing .
From that time , nuclear production was getting more popular all the time .
In " 50 Facts About U.S. Nuclear Weapon " , it is stated that the cost of the Manhattan Project ( through August 1945 ) is 20,000,000,000 USD .
Although it costs great amount of money , but those nuclear countries are still improving their nuclear capabilities .
We must be wondering why people want to spend so much money on such things .
Usually when you are creating nuclear power , the main purpose is to make other countries respect and fear you .
This is very useful in military aspect .
My former history teacher one day said that " To create peace , we need big power .
" This means that if I have enough power to knock you , your friends and your family down , then it is very logical that you want to have a peace with me because you know that I am capable of doing awful things to you .
That is why people ( in this case , countries ) want to be strong so that they are trying to develop something .
As technology is getting better and better , the way people fight with each other is also improved from time to time .
A long time ago people fought using woods , rocks , bones , etc. And then they knew about metals , so they used spears , sword , arrows , etc in their wars .
The next phase is the gunpowder stage .
Finally , we arrive at this nuclear stage .
Everything seems so cool right now , so does the war .
As in , we just need to type some commands on our computer and click a button to launch a rocket .
I have noticed that people are actually trying to be more efficient ( from going to the field and using rocks as weapon until using buttons on the computer only ) and this is the second reason why people keep spending money to improve nuclear .
To conclude , I just want to emphasize that technology depends on social factors .
It is just like a knife ; you can use it for good ( peel fruits ) or for bad ( kill someone ) .
This nuclear case is just one of the examples .
The military aspect has contributed a lot to technology improvements .
And there are still a lot of aspects that contribute to technology as well .
Before the 1950s , most of electricity was created by burning fossil fuel , and no one was aware of other energy .
After the second world war , the whole world was busy recovering economics and industry .
So the need of fossil energy became more and more serious .
At this moment , a few countries found that only relying on fossil energy is not enough and there should be another efficient energy to be created .
After a few years in U.S. , the world 's first nuclear power plant was set up .
Although some scientists and officers in a few countries felt sometime in the future fossil energy can be used up , the governments did not give enough attention to creating another efficient energy because there was still enough fossil energy in store for the near use .
Till decades after , people found that fossil energy is nonrenewable and fast depleting is only a less serious problem , the more serious is that the world 's average degree is increasing since the final product of burning fossil fuel is carbon dioxide which is the main source of aggravating the greenhouse effect .
The use of fossil fuel brings up much pollution and even ruins lungs of many kinds of creatures , including human beings .
From and eco-logical stand point , the world should decrease the use of fossil fuel and try to find other ways of creating energy .
Then , to invest nuclear energy becomes quite important and emergency .
And the development of nuclear energy receives vigor .
However , when fossil fuel prices fall can any country resist the temptation ?
During 1970s and 1980s , influenced by excessive industry development , the world 's economic cost reached to a high point but at that time , fossil fuel prices were decreasing .
This mad those nuclear power plant which were under construction less attractive .
Almost as the same reason in 1973 , France and Japan suffered oil crisis .
Their governments could not pay for such high oil debts and these two countries decided to depend on nuclear technology .
In other words , France and Japan were forced to invest nuclear technology .
What is surprising that today 80 % of the electricity in France is supplied by nuclear energy .
In Japan the percentage is also as high as 30 % ( Sharon Beder , 2006 ) .
But not all the countries can afford the cost to build up a nuclear power plant .
Take the U.S as an example .
The U.S. is the country having most nuclear power plants , and is well known by their technology in this area .
However in the U.S. , to build up an ordinary nuclear power plant will cost as much as $ 6 ~ 10 billion .
But it is sure that in the future , nuclear energy will give a strong support to the whole world industry economics .
When all the countries are aware this point , it is only a matter of time to make nuclear energy all over the world .
Except the factor of countries ' industry development , to have nuclear weapons is also a stimulus .
No wonder , the destructive force of nuclear weapon is terrible .
The original goal of developing nuclear technology is to invent weapons .
It is a truth that if a country has nuclear weapons or technology , it can produce a nuclear deterrent , which helps a country gain a higher position in a negotiation .
But this is prohibited by UN laws .
As nuclear technology becomes so important , it is necessary to have an international organization to supervise the process of every country 's development .
Then the WANO ( world association nuclear operator ) was set up .
With the WANO 's beginning to discharge its duties , the world 's nuclear development goes on the right way .
In 2007 , 14 % of the world 's electricity came from nuclear power and , it can be seen after a few years the nuclear energy will benefit the whole world .
As many big cities in the world are facing the water crisis , as acid rains becomes increasingly frequent , as the number of lung cancer patients keeps going up , environment protection has become one of the most vital need of human .
To satisfy human 's need and make contribution to protecting environment , engineers are to design and invent products in an environmental friendly way .
Through engineering design process , we can see how engineer satisfy that need .
According to Khandani.S ( 2005 ) , there are five steps in solving designing problems .
To design and produce something more environment friendly , engineers should pay more attention on environment-related information when searching for pertinent information .
For example , suppose an engineer is looking for a material for meal boxes of taken-away food .
Apart from information about cost , weight , water resistant ability , etc , he needs to pay extra attention on some environmental information like whether the material can be biodegraded or recycled .
Taking this environment-related information into consideration helps make more environment friendly decision .
The other step is to analyze and select a solution .
Usually , engineers will come up with more than one plan along the way they design a product .
They need to analyze and evaluate them and give a final plan .
In the Engineering Design Process , Khandani.S ( 2005 ) shows us how an engineer evaluates different plans .
Firstly , they need to analyse criteria or factors to evaluate design plans .
They need to perform several types of analysis on each design .
These types of analysis are the factors on evaluating plans .
Next they value each factor by its importance , and give a mark representing how important it is .
After that , they evaluate each factor against the corresponding criterion .
Based on how well that plan fit the criterion , they give a mark .
Last , calculate points and compare .
Let the mark of each factor multiplies the number representing the importance of this factor and add up all the total mark .
By comparing the total mark of different plans , they decide the final plan .
If he can increase the importance of the factors related to environment protection , he may use substitute of phosphorus , or cleanse the waste water before discharge it .
Then the process and product would be more environmental friendly .
If engineers can think more about environment when designing , the product will become very environment-friendly .
Government Regulations and Public Opinions in the Development of Electric Bicycle in China
One typical image remembered by the world about China is about its astounding amount of bicycles on the roads : swarms of people riding bicycles filling the roads which are not really narrow .
While since the year of 2000 , another phenomenon occurs on the roads of cities in China : electric bicycles .
A cording to data on reliable Chinese websites , in 2004 alone , 6750000 electric bicycles were produced by more than 1000 factories all over China and these numbers were expected to increase by times by the end of 2010 .
( { http : //www.ind.com.cn/htm/2009-07/28/content_786827.htm.accessed September 4,2009 } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.ind.com.cn/htm/2009-07/28/content_786827.htm.accessed % 20September % 204,2009 ] ) With the maturing of the technologies on electric motors and long-life battery , multiple types of electric vehicle could have been created .
Previous existing government regulations and public opinions on road safety act important roles in shaping electric bicycle in China into what it is today .
The previously existing government regulations have a tremendous effect on the development of electric bicycles when it comes to the size and speed of electric bicycles .
Before the e-bike ( electric bicycle ) which is light ( lighter than 20kg ) and slower ( maximum speed is less than 20km/h ) we see now , there are also a number of other kinds of electric vehicle in developing .
They are more like electric motorbike which is much more powerful and , of course , heavier .
But because of the government regulations on city transportation under which all means of transportation on road are grouped to either motor or non-motor and nothing in between , the prototype of the heavy electric bicycles was nipped in the bud as it can be counted to either of the two criteria because of its variety of performance .
The later electric bicycle was then designed to be more like a normal bicycle and was only allowed to ride on non-motor roads , light but moving automatically .
People can even ride it just like riding a bike when it runs out of power .
Apart from government regulations , public opinions also have prominent effect on the development of e-bike .
Data on road traffic accidents were counted .
In Hangzhou , the capital city of Zhejiang province , the cases of accidents caused by e-bike has been increasing for three years .
( http : //www.hangzhou.gov.cn/main/xxbs/T152837.shtml accessed September 4 , 2009 ) Though the number was relatively small compared with those caused by cars and motorbikes , people were becoming more and more concerned with the safety issues with e-bike and a series of public hearings were then carried out to discuss how to make e-bike a safe vehicle on the roads .
Finally , the speed limit was set at 20km/h which is quite at the lower end of what the technology allows to do .
Then all the e-bike industries begun to improve other performance of e-bike like battery life and noise rather than speed and loading ability .
In order to meet the requirement of government regulations and public opinions , the development of e-bike has gone through several changes ; therefore it was shaped to the e-bike we see now .
Hopefully , the next typical image left by China to the world will be e-bike .
In 1936 , the first public video telephone had been developed .
At that time , people had to simultaneously go to special post office video telephone booths to use this service .
Until 1980s , with the development of chip , transmission technology , digital communication , video codec technology and integrated circuit technology , videophone became truly usable .
Then many predicted that videophone would be very popular someday and it would be loved by the public .
However , in recent decades , there was almost no market for the videophone and videophone has not emerged in our lives .
One of the reasons why videophone could not become popular is that there were technical problems .
But apart from the technical factor , the development of videophone mainly limited by some social and economic factors .
Videophone was very expensive in early times .
Even in today when the technology is so advanced , the price is still quite high .
One videophone roughly ranges in price of S $ 200 to S $ 1000 .
In addition , the videophone costs much more than the normal phone especially when user takes a long distance call .
Second reason is due to the privacy issues .
When they are talking , they want to be relaxed and feel free .
Videophone users also commonly look at the video screen and not at the video camera , causing the eyes to take on an unnatural awkward glance , as the camera is usually just positioned away from the screen ( " Videophone , " 2009 ) .
For a long time , although there were some companies producing videophones , different kinds of videophone from different companies could not communicate with each other because they did not share a standard .
texting and instant messaging , which are commonly available on all video-enabled cell phones and web chat programs ) ( " Videophone , " 2009 ) .
Nowadays , with the fast development of the internet , more and more people accept to video chat through some internet chatting software .
The necessity of using videophone is becoming lower and lower .
It sounds like a tragedy that this great innovative device has not been used or even seen by most people since it was invented in 19th century .
What experience we should gain is that social and economic issues can indeed shape the development of a new product .
Hence , considering social and economic aspects before the implement of an innovation is important .
Normally skunk works generate innovations more quickly than the conventional R&D organizations , for workers in skunk works work " on a crash basis to create an innovation " ( Rogers , 2003 , p.144 ) .
On the other hand , conventional generated technology probably takes a longer time ; for example , another revolutionary invention , light bulb , was first generated in the 1800s .
Workers in the skunk works have stronger motives than those in the conventional organization .
The result is that researchers in the skunk works generate innovation faster .
Besides the differences of time and cost , nevertheless , when coming to the commercialization stage , products transferred from technology in skunk works are sometimes not so mature as those transferred from conventional R&D organization due to the time limitation .
On the contrary , Conventional R&D organizations have more time to make their innovation more customer-friendly and more mature in technology .
However , it has higher requirements for the personnel and capital , which are difficult for some companies that are in shortage of capital .
Prior to the Industrial Revolution in the 19th century , the needs of people are just basic-food , clothing , air and last but not least , shelter .
Well , in order to have a better transportation , design processes are needed to fulfill the need .
Transportation which is cheap and safe , environmentally friendly and uses alternative source of energy has the utmost importance in the need of transportation .
One of the imminent problems faced by the modern transportation is to depend less on fossil fuels .
At the rate of usage of fossil fuels -at three billion barrels per year-now , it will not take long before the fuels deplete .
According to a presentation made by Osman Chughtai and David Shannon , fossil fuels will mostly run out in 17 years minimum or a maximum of 50 to 70 years .
Nevertheless , other transportation problems like producing too much pollutant such as nitrogen oxides .
Pollutants produced have been proved to have an enormous effect on the Earth ozone layer , corroding the ozone layers and exposing humans to the deadly ultraviolet ray .
To add to the problems stated above , the world currently needs a better transport , in terms of safety and functionalities as well as its cost .
First of all , engineering processes provides the foundation for researches to get a new state-of-the-art design .
Recently there was this groundbreaking news stating that engineers found a technology called H2CAR process , a process for producing fuels from plants or what they call the process-biomass .
Besides researches , development processes enable engineers to produce designs that will be tested on real ground .
In this case , transportations like cars must be able to withstand extreme weathers and must be aerodynamically shaped for maneuverability .
In a nutshell , design processes are the main essence for a better future transportation , in terms of fuel type , environmentally friendly , functionalities as well as its cost .
This need must be taken seriously in order to secure a brighter future- a future people do not need to travel on bicycle or on foot .
" Chinese mobile phone users total 703 million " ( HYPERLINK " http : //thegovmonitor.com/world_news/asia/chinese-mobile-phone-users-total-703-million-3376.html " http : //thegovmonitor.com/world_news/asia/chinese-mobile-phone-users-total-703-million-3376.html ) this is reported at 4th September 2009 .
But seven out of ten of the mobile phones users holding are not Chinese brands .
How can Chinese enterprises compete against foreign mobile phones ?
History witnesses that mobile phone markets are always broadened by new features of the phone .
Motorola 8900 which was available in market in the year 1995 was firstly featured with a cover so that miss-press of button was avoided .
At the same year the first self-chosen ring tongue was heard from Ericsson GH398 .
The first folding phone was Motorola 328C born January 1999.Nokia 7110 is the first mobile phone with a wap browser which was released in October 1999 .
Hagenuk CH9771 was the first mobile phone put its antenna inside the phone .
As mobile phone is built up by so many parts , there are various ways of innovation .
Appearance means much because people treat mobile phones not only as communication tools but also as kind beloved toys .
I phone conquer the whole world but failed to enter Japan 's market because of two reasons : First , Japanese like to own a unique style of phone but iphone has only one style which would cause embarrassment when Japanese meet the other iphone user .
But iphone doesnot have them .
As for the appearance there are four major designs : straight , flip , slide and rotation .
Such as a straight phone with 3-row,4-collum keyboard .
To protect the fragile touch screen , the keyboard can act as the cover and leave only a little part of the screen out side when not used .
There are plenty of functions now but the new the better .
A phone can act as a telescope in Birdnest during Beijing 2008 Olympic Games by using the camera and its zoom function .
It can also design a diet for its owner for here to lose weight .
Innovative mobile design is important also because designers can harvest both copy right and market .
A new design is protected by its copy right so that for the producer meet slight competition entering the market .
To conclude , China mobile industry need to work on innovation of phones ' appearance and function .
Problems significantly hampering engineering design processes for innovations Along with the development of the living standard , people 's demands for goods increase .
At the same time , people pay more attention on the quality of the goods .
In order to meet the demand of modern society , we need higher efficiency and more advanced technology .
Thus , the innovations of engineering processes are more and more important .
But in real life there are many problems hamper engineering design processes for innovations .
And the two of most significantly are the state of information communication not smooth and the corruption .
In the practical production , only the workers directly use the production equipments .
The senior management and the boss , who have the right to change and introduce new equipments and technologies seldom care about the real condition of production .
And because of the state of information communication is not smoothly , workers can not transmit the problems that they found in production to the people who have the power to make decisions .
In this case , after a long time the workers do not have enthusiasm to think about how to solve the problems .
At the same time it loses the opportunity to save costs and increase production efficiency .
And the corruption often causes more serious problems than other problems .
It is a so serious problem that exist almost every area .
For the leaders in the companies and factories , if they were corrupt , they will only care about their own benefits and ignore many others .
There are many cases that the leaders corrupt lead the whole companies or factories to go bankrupt .
And there are also some cases even more fearful .
Some of set up a company just want to cheat , all the actions that the companies make are all want to cheating for money from consumers or other companies .
For the staffs , if they were corrupt , they would not focus on their jobs any more .
Furthermore , they will envy others who have a higher position or make more money or make greater contributions .
In such case , they may do a lot of bad things , maybe to frame others , in order to make more benefits for themselves .
For workers , they will only care about how to please their leaders to get more benefits and not care about the production .
What the worse influence is the corrupt people will affect the general mood of a company or a factory .
To conclude , there are many problems existing hampering engineering design processes for innovations .
In this era of globalization , engineering design has been emphasized by the governments of the countries all over the world , such as United State , Russia and France .
This is because the development of engineering design could bring many advantages to country 's economy and also in social aspect .
Actually , the scientists may perceive a future problem and launch some researches to overcome it .
If we observe our surrounding , we could see many inventions of technological creativity such as computer , automobile and other electrical appliances .
Nevertheless , there are some problems which significantly hamper engineering design processes for innovations in my home country , Malaysia and cause the impacts on certain stages of the process of engineering design .
As we all know , if we want to improve our engineering design , we need to launch many researches .
Subsequently , a lump sum of money need to be used to launch all these researches , but our government is not able to invest so much money on all these researches .
So , the financial problem arises and constrains the engineering design processes for innovations .
For your information , Malaysia is a country which is still developing and not as wealthy as other western developed countries such as United State , France and Germany .
Hence , we lack of money to improve our facilities of research such as well-equipped laboratories and other highly technological instruments .
In fact , this will causes the engineering design process to pause in the half way because of the lack of the highly technological instruments .
For instance , if we want to design a race car , we need some highly technology instruments to do researches on the car engine and other parts of car .
Although we have already found the important information about the research , we can not continue to an analysis of design solution because of the lack of highly technology instruments to investigate .
Many of the researches of engineering design which were carried out in the modern countries had been done successfully .
In fact , the lack of professionals in engineering field results the failure of many researches .
For instance , some of the automobile researches have been failed due to the lack of the professionals .
The stage of analysis of design solution has been constrained because of the limited knowledge and lack of professionals .
Hence , some forums of the engineering design should be held between our country and other modern countries such as United State , United Kingdom and Germany .
In a nutshell , financial problem and lack of professionals in my home country should be solved as soon as possible , so as to improve our engineering design processes innovations .
Hence , private sector , the government and also citizens should work hand in hand in order to get more investment for engineering design researches and produce more professionals in the field of engineering design in the future .
Indonesia , a country hosting more than two hundred and thirty million citizens , is South East Asia 's largest country and economy to date .
Yet Indonesia still trails behind its neighboring countries such as Malaysia , Thailand , and even The Little Red Dot : Singapore , in terms of advancement in design based technology .
It is commonly believed that the slow rate of technological growth in Indonesia is caused by two major problems , which may hamper the innovative engineering design process .
Firstly , Indonesia lacks culture of innovation .
According to the statistics published by UNICEF in 2007 , only fifty percent of Indonesian citizens are urbanized , which means the other half live in rural areas with little exposure to modern world and technology .
People living in traditional villages live very simple life .
They stick to their ancestors ' traditions , and sometimes prefer traditional way of doing things to labor saving modern devices ; for example : some farmers prefer buffalo driven ploughs to tractors .
Moreover , the farmers still rely on the government supplies and subsidies , which encounters a lot of logistics problems , instead of innovating their own way of solving problems .
Besides , most universities in Indonesia are more teaching based , less research intensive than those in Japan or The States ; that makes Indonesian university students less creative and innovative in problem solving .
The second problem that may hamper the engineering design process in Indonesia is due to its both excessive and cheap natural resources , space , and workforces .
As mentioned before , Indonesia hosts more than two hundred and thirty million citizens , and its unemployment rate is considered high at 9.1 % ( Reuters , 2008 ) .
Thus , Indonesia needs to create jobs for its people ; one way is by developing its agricultural businesses , which has been a hot topic lately during the presidential campaign .
Prabowo Subianto , son of Sumitro Djojohadikusumo , former minister of economics for both Indonesia and Malaysia , during his vice presidential campaign opposed a solution to current Indonesian problems ; he promised to create jobs by developing bio diesel producing palm plantation in Indonesia , which may absorb about 6 million workforces .
It 's apparent that innovative and labor saving devices will not work in Indonesia ; the new invention seemed to be more expensive compared to the traditional way .
After the invention is patented , there is nobody who is willing to buy it , because in Indonesia 's case it 's not cost efficient .
Another effect is demotivation of young engineers from designing new product , because the rewards the society gives them is not equal to their long time hardworking .
To tackle them , Indonesian government has to work hard in developing innovative culture in the society , and decreasing the people 's dependability on the government .
According to Khandani 's statement " What distinguishes engineers from painters , poets , or sculptors is that engineers apply their creative energies to producing products or systems that meet human needs " , all engineering designs aim to meet human demand to become successful products .
Now , when the society becomes widely and continuingly developed , people are looking for new designs to satisfy their comfortable lives .
Those new designs may be the demands of entertainment , education or even something beyond our imagination .
However , in my opinion , one of the main concerns in our society is finding a new energy supply to alter the old ones , which become exhausted due to the overexploitation of human .
In order to solve this urgent demand , engineering plays an important role in finding the other alternatives such as nuclear energy , solar energy and geothermal energy .
Evidently , energy becomes vital and indispensable in our life , relating to most of everything we are working .
Because of the influence of energy , the natural resources have invisibly caused wars and conflicts between many countries over years and years .
The recent war between United States and Iraq in 2000 might be considered to be a typical example .
Although U.S. has been saying that this war was for the anti-terrorism , or more importantly for keeping the peacefulness of the world , it is clear that one of the reasons why American troopers stay in Iraq is the benefits of petroleum .
This is a typical example of showing how important energy is since it exerts a grave impact on our daily life .
Due to the non-renewability of the natural " fossil " resources , the more demands the society needs , the more exhausted they become .
According to the online newspaper Financial Times ( 2006 ) and USA today news ( 2004 ) , the oil reserves in Trinidad and Tobago will run out in the next 20 years and the world oil reserves will become exhausted just in 40 years .
The process of finding a new alternative energy source , which is not only renewable but also environmental-friendly , has been conducted for a long time and regarded as an ultimate goal for engineering .
The nuclear power is extracted from the usable energy from heavy atomic nuclei ( for example Uranium 235 ) via chain of nuclear reactions .
The first nuclear plant was built in Russia in 1984 whose initial electricity production is about 5000KW .
However , the design of nuclear reaction has to meet many rigorous requirements to avoid the nuclear releases as well as to isolate the radiation from the life .
All of these conditions have to be followed strictly otherwise it may cause immeasurable consequences .
For instance , one of the most tragic accidents involving radiation release was the Chernobyl disaster , which happened in 1986 .
This disastrous accident results from the weakness in design and up to now , the neighboring areas still suffer from the radiation .
Another solution is the perpetual resources as known as solar , geothermal energy and etc...The solar energy is drawn from sunlight 's energy by many solar panels which are designed to fit the house proof .
This energy will be converted into electric or thermal energy to serve our life .
Geothermal power takes the thermal calorie in the entrails in the earth and translates into other energies which contribute an important role to operate turbines and machines .
Geothermal energy is considered as the most potential alternative for the nonrenewable energy resource in the future .
Also , those resources may not be applied and used everywhere on earth due to the geographic differences .
In conclusion , I content that energy problem should be classified on the first priority in human must-solves not only because of many huge benefits it provides for people but also because of the critical shortage of energy resources .
In this context , engineering design process meets these urgent needs by finding many feasible solutions such as nuclear energy , solar energy and geothermal energy sources .
Although this process has just gotten initial achievements , it promises a fully potential energy source in the future which may permanently serve human kind .
Thus , many countries spend more money and time on developing new resources which can be used as a substitution to petroleum .
This can be seen through the increasing in research and development of the solar cars or other products .
The using of the solar energy related goods has been highly encouraged by the environmentalists .
So I would like to discuss about the reasons of innovation of these technology in the following factors , named economic factor , government factors and environmental factor .
First of all , as what I have mentioned before , the petrol price was fluctuating in recent years , this makes many factories start to worry about the cost and the profit they can earn .
Most of them feel unsecured because the cost of petrol may lead the low profit or even red deficit .
So we can see many firms and companies start to invest in solar energy areas .
It is because of the cost of the batteries .
Presently , there is limitation of the amount of energy the batteries can store as we can only " use solar cells to generate up to 240 watts of electrical power in full sunshine " ( wikepedia ) .
As long as we can find a way to increase the amount of the energy the batteries can store , the cost will not be much a problem anymore .
So I think , although they have to spend much more on researches now , they can definitely save more in the long run .
For example , their enemy may cut down the inflow of the petrol provided to their land .
This will in turn cause many harmful results include acidic rain or global warming .
And as solar energy comes from the sun , it can be regarded as reproducible and we do not need to worry about if it will be used up one day .
In conclusion , I think we should decrease the using of petrol related product and slowly switch towards using the products which need new resources .
Only if we show our interests and demands on these products , those researchers can have motivation and more funds to do their projects .
Their achievements are influencing the developments of every industry .
People 's need is so various that one prime need must be given priority to avoid distractions .
In today 's world , this need should be people 's demand of fresh water .
As is known , water is a resource that human can not live without .
Its uses range from climate regulating , industry application to food processing and daily drinking .
Back to a hundred years ago , water was never a concern .
While , today it is different .
It 's now commonly recognized that fresh water will be the scarcest resource in the follow century .
Some people even assume that the next world war will be fought for the limited fresh water on the earth .
In order to ensure human 's survival and the peace of world , engineers should respect the human 's need for water most when designing products .
One aspect engineer should work on to meet people 's need of water is to reduce the pollution in engineering process .
To be exact , there is never a lack of water on the earth , but pollution damaged most of the available water sources , such as rivers and lacks .
This can stop pollution to water more thoroughly than government 's fine on water pollution .
In addition , engineers can design device that can save water .
Therefore , if device can avoid wasting water in daily life of each person , it will surely save considerably large amount of water .
Small device like taps , water coolers , washing machines , can all be the targets of engineers .
Engineers should attach importance to water-efficiency together with other efficiencies regarding designing device , so that enough water can be conserved to meet people 's need .
To sum up , engineering should give priority to people 's need for water first , as water is necessary for human 's survival .
In order to highlight this need , engineers should emphasis on environmental friendliness and water saving in designing .
For the next 10 years or more , Singapore would have a high percentage of population consisting of the elderly .
There are a few factors leading to ageing population , where some of them are low birth rates and increase in the cost of standard living .
With the increase number of elderly , there would be a need in safety areas , thus products or services should be designed to meet this need .
This product is a smart suit that is equipped with array of microsensors which are able to detect falls suffered by the wearers and to send alerts to their caregivers .
Besides these functions , the engineers have also included an " impact-reduction " system to reduce the damage does to the wearer when he or she falls .
For the product , we have seen that the engineers have make use of the engineering design processes to meet the need .
Firstly , they have defined the problem , which is the ageing population and they have seen the need to invent a product which could gives extra safety protection to the elderly .
Secondly , they have brainstormed on the preliminary criteria for a better design for the product ( Khandani , S. ( 2005 ) ) .
For instance , in the case of a fire , the temperature sensor will be alerted and sends warning alerts to their caregivers or call for Civil Defense Force immediately .
Furthermore , when considering the design of the product , there is a need to make special considerations that are suitable for the elderly use .
Those factors that might need to take into consideration when designing the product are inflexible movements and slow response time .
Engineering would have to use the engineering design processes to list out multiple solutions the designing of product ( Khandani , S. ( 2005 ) ) .
In order to make sure the product works well , engineers have to test it before they launched the product .
In conclusion , we have seen that the problems of ageing population could get more serious for the next few years , thus there is a need to design a product that could help to reduce the risks and impacts faced by the ageing population .
By the example of these two products , we could see that both of them have make use of the engineering design processes to meet the need .
And thus , it proved that it is really important to follow through the engineering design processes when inventing a new product .
Humans ' activities on Earth have always been depleting Earth 's valuable yet limited amount of natural resources and at the same time damaging Earth 's environment .
This will cause Earth 's natural resources to be depleted and modifying Earth 's environment so much that it is no longer suitable for human life .
Therefore humans have to give priorities to conserving Earth 's natural resources and protecting its environment .
This can be achieved by completely abolishing already available engineering processes , modifying and improving these old processes , or correctly identifying the reasons for the rise of that need .
Firstly , engineering processes that are available now and are widely used can be abolished while new ones can be introduced to perform the function of its predecessor and at the same time fulfilling the need .
For instance , humans have always been depending of one of Earth 's natural resources , fossil fuels as an important source of energy .
However , due to human 's overuse of it , fossil fuels are expected to be completely depleted in the year 2050 .
Therefore engineering processes of technologies that extract energy from fossil fuels must be abolished and new ones must be introduced to ensure a constant supply of energy for humans .
For example , western powers like countries in Europe and the United States is planning to construct large scales solar energy farms in areas in Africa like the Sahara desert to replace generating energy from fossil fuels .
Therefore we can see how abolishing old engineering processes and embracing new ones can satisfy that need .
Secondly , instead of removing available engineering processes , they can also be modified so that its original function is still available but at the same time satisfying the need to reserve natural resources and protecting the environment .
For example , transportation systems like cars require fuels like fossil fuels which is processed from a depleting natural resource , fossil fuels .
Furthermore , greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide are produced from these cars which will contribute to the notorious greenhouse effect .
For instance , the introduction of electricity cars by General Motors , uses electricity to power the car 's engine instead of fossil fuels .
This satisfy the need as electricity can be generated from renewable sources of energies like solar and wind energy .
Furthermore , greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide will not be emitted also .
Thirdly , the need can be fulfilled by correctly identifying and analyzing the reason for the rise of that need , so that the correct decisions can be made in engineering processes to fulfill the need .
For example , CFC gases in the past is a by-product of many of our industries .
These gases causes the destruction of the Earth 's ozone layer in the atmosphere which causes more harmful ultraviolet , UV rays to penetrate the atmosphere , causing health problems like skin cancer to humans due to these UV rays .
Therefore a worldwide policy was implemented to ban the emission of CFC gases into the atmosphere by industries .
Thus , we can see how making the correct decisions to prevent pollution to the environment can fulfill the need .
In conclusion , to ensure a sufficient supply of natural resources and a healthy environment for us and our future generations to live in , engineering processes can meet our need by removing and introducing or modifying available engineering processes and making the correct decisions in engineering processes can fulfill that need .
Out of all the human needs in the world , to have clean water should be given priority compared with others .
In addition , due to the global warming , the sea level rises .
Therefore , some precious sources of drinking water , like underground water is polluted and not drinkable any more , which makes the situation even worse .
In some regions in the world , such as the Middle East and Africa , the shortage of clean drinking water is very serious , which even causes wars sometimes .
Water we daily use can be divided into two categories , which are respectively for drinking and not for drinking .
For example , water we use to flush toilet , to irrigate farmland and to wash cars is not necessary to reach the same hygienic level as the drinking water .
Hence , we may use recycled water to do these jobs so that we can save more clean drinking water for people to drink .
However , this method may not suitable for those developing and undeveloped countries because it costs a lot of money , and the technology required is also very high .
The other way to get drinking water is the desalination of sea water .
Another limitation of this method is that it can only be applied in seaside countries , like Singapore , which means that it is not the first choice to many inland countries .
Therefore , since the two methods mentioned above are both costly and difficult to apply , they can be restricted by the economic and market and thus , they may be not able to solve the shortage of water in a short period .
It is this kind of hope that motivates humans to develop , to improve , to pursue our dream , and finally to have such a beautiful world today .
Hope is the most significant contribution which engineers have ever made to the world .
Environment-friendly car is a current humans ' need which should be given priority .
The current car 's technology , the fuel injection has satisfied that need , but dissatisfies environment 's need .
Humans need a car which not only able to transport them easily but also friendly to the environment .
It is engineers ' job to apply their creative energies in designing a solution which meets humans ' need .
First of all , the current car 's technology , the fuel injection has satisfied humans ' need to travel .
For example , the time taken to travel from one place to another with a distance of a few hundred kilometres has reduced from 2-3 days to 2-3 hours ; as a result , humans are able to travel instantly .
This is indeed makes human 's mean of transportation rises to another level .
Second , in contrast with the benefit which the fuel injection has contributed to humans ' life , it has polluted the environment .
This is due to the fuel processing in the car .
For example , the fuel injection is exhausting Carbon Dioxide ( CO2 ) as a result of incomplete burning of fuels .
Third , humans not only need to travel but also need a pollution free environment to live in .
In the view of this issue , engineers are needed to design a solution .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , products or systems are designed to meet human needs by engineers .
For years , engineers have experimented to design a solution to this issue .
This eco-car has no fuel tank therefore produce no emissions at all .
Lastly , Japan 's engineers had followed engineering design processes , Khandani ( 2005 ) , to design their first eco-car .
They defined that the fuel injection system 's problem lies on the fuel it uses .
They gathered information in order to arrive successfully at the right fuel 's source ; subsequently , they decided to use electricity as the fuel .
The road to success is not smooth ; likewise , Japan 's engineers had gone through a lot of challenges and tests before they arrived at their final prototype of Japan 's first eco-car .
Humans need to care about the environment 's condition , in order to preserve it for the new generation .
To conclude , by using engineering design processes , engineers can design product that meets humans ' need .
For instance in Singapore and Japan , healthcare is emphasized on the elderly due to their aging populations but both execute their policies in a different way .
With a replacement rate of 1.5 children to 2 adults and estimation that by 2030 , 18.4 % of the population will be make up of the elderly , it is no wonder why Singapore government is promoting reproduction in young couples .
As the population ages , the main users of hospital services will be the old aged .
According to a survey in 2004 , Singapore is named one of the unfriendliest countries towards the wheel chair bounded .
Hence , there is a need for us to better the healthcare services of our older citizens .
In Japan , nearly one quarter of the population is made up of the old aged .
The fast paced society force citizens to place work as priority over family resulting in a declining population .
Since the number of old aged is increasing , it is important to cater to their needs in terms of healthcare .
The first concern is the living condition of the old aged .
Home care facilities such as hospice ; day care centre and nursing home are built to look after the elderly especially when their family members are unable to do so .
For example , in Singapore , one room apartment with specially installed emergency buttons and lifts are catered to the elderly .
Shopping malls and other common places should be equipped with more ramps and handicapped friendly escalator .
They should be offered free medical checkups and treatment if necessary .
In conclusion , healthcare services should not be neglected especially in countries , which face aging population .
Consequently , after years of research and design in aim to alleviate this problem , the NEWater technology was invented .
This is an example in which a particular human need has been satisfied by an engineering design system .
Global warming , as a result , is becoming more and more an issue of raising concern as little has been done to eliminate or tremendously reduce pollution .
Time is running out and to protect the sustainability of life on Earth , necessary actions have to be taken immediately if not , as soon as possible and the help of engineering design processes should not be left out .
Subsequently , engineering design processes have made possible the invention of catalytic converters which convert the harmful gases emitted by vehicles into non- harmful gases .
On the flip side , although the problem of the emission of harmful gases has been handled , vehicles today are releasing carbon dioxide , which is a greenhouse gas , instead .
After years of research , then comes the idea of inventing an environmentally-friendly car ; also known as an ecocar .
Throughout the years , there has always been a debate on whether technology shapes society , a technologically determinist perspective , or does society shape technology , a socially determinist view .
One such technology that is closely related to this debate is the invention of the automobiles .
Due to the influence of these factors , the gasoline powered cars have won over the electric cars for years .
Firstly , societal factors like the expansion of cities favor the gasoline cars over electric cars .
For example , the gasoline powered cars can travel an average of about 300km on a full tank of petrol as compared to a maximum distance of 150km for a full charge on an electric battery .
Everyone now wants to own a car for the convenience and for individualism 's sake .
Take Dubai for instance , they now have an average ratio of 571 cars to every 1000 people .
Therefore , this affects the automobiles as people purchase more gasoline powered cars .
The reason is that car manufacturers , in order to retain their market share of gasoline powered cars , will invest time and money to promote gasoline powered vehicles over the unproven market of electric cars .
A social stigma that electric cars are only meant to be golf carts or less is hence created , and this leads to people purchasing the gasoline powered cars .
Next , technological factors current available technology and limitation of resources have also helped shaped the automobiles .
Hybrid cars involves either part gasoline part electric or part gasoline part compressed natural gas ( CNG ) .
The gasoline powered car has finally seen a worthy competitor .
However , technological restrains like limited resources has been a set back for hybrid users .
This constrain makes consumers think twice before purchasing a hybrid vehicle .
Imagine if there no technological restrains and that we could create a self replenishing battery .
Technology and society co-exist and affects one another .
Even till now , we are shaping many other technological inventions .
Who knows , hybrid cars might actually manage to successfully dethrone the gasoline powered cars in the near future .
Electronics such as lights and cars have become essential to the human beings over the past years .
These electronics though wonderful , but they consume a huge amount of energy .
One current human need that should be given priority for engineering design is to have cost saving electronics .
The milestone in having a motion sensor light to automatically turn on and off the lights with the presence of a human being was how to accurately identify the presence of a human being in the area monitored by the sensor .
To overcome the milestone , the motion sensors use infrared energy to detect human beings .
These natural gases are widely available on earth as compared to petrol fuel which is getting limited as the oil reserves depletes .
In order for a car to be powered using CNG , there are certain modifications that needs to be done .
For example , new fuel storage was introduced , and took the name of Integrated Storage system .
In Singapore , public transports such as taxis , buses have converted to CNG .
In addition , according to Channel NewsAsia , there is an increasing number of private cars owners converting their conventional petrol fuel powered cars to CNG cars .
To sum up , with the depletion of natural resources and high electricity and fuel cost , engineering designing should be given priority to cost saving electronics .
Usually , engineers face difficulty in designing a product or coming out with ideas that are of demand by the public .
As an engineer , he needs to define the problem , gather pertinent information , generate and analyse multiple solutions and finally , test and implement whether the solution works .
However , the two most disturbing problems that may hamper engineering design processes for innovations are the inability to generate multiple solutions to convince their superior to implement their products or ideas and the failure of constantly creating a product that are of demand .
Firstly , in the aspect of generating multiple solutions , engineers often face the problems off lacking of funds and unable to convince their superior that their idea is feasible .
Their idea or product is a total new concept which people may find it hard to accept because of traditional idea or product that may have etched in their mind .
For example , in the Singapore National Service , the professional nature of the military officers , using its portion of dominant influence , typically make most of the important decisions about innovation .
In addition , the low ranking cadets usually fail to convince the high ranking officers that their innovative products or ideas may improve the military .
This unmanned combat air vehicle may be potent enough to replace the ubiquitous manned fighter in the near future .
However , due to the higher officer not having enough trust over the air vehicle being piloted by human , this unmanned combat vehicle project did not succeed in carrying out .
As an engineer , if their ideas or products face constant rejection by their superior , they will stop coming up with new ideas or products as they see no purpose for coming up with new ideas or products and constantly opposing their superiors .
Thus , the superiority in company will significantly hamper engineer morale and their design .
Secondly , the other problem that restricts engineer design is the lack of confident to implement ideas or products that are of demand .
Although in the initial stage the surveying of their products response may be good , when it comes to implementing their ideas or products , the response may be of the reverse .
Engineers spend efforts in developing the products , but the final products that they design may not be of popular demand .
This type of phone faced rejection because the phone was expensive and users found it infringing their privacy .
As a result , the sales of these phones were low , affecting the morale of the engineer who design this phone .
As an engineer , facing multiple failures may cause them to be disheartened and put them on high alert as they will be more careful when they want to design a product .
They will tend to feel disappointed because they need to solicit a lot of funds , putting in their utmost efforts when developing the products , and only to find out that their products face rejection by the public .
The " best " design solution is always hard to develop because it is one that most completely fulfils the client 's requirements .
Therefore , engineers may just stop at gathering pertinent information , and not go into generating multiple solutions as they are worry that their products may not be of demand as expected , which again hamper their design processes for innovations .
In conclusion , it is usually the lack of ability to convince the superiors and the constant rejection by the public that significantly hamper engineering design for innovations .
Traditional mindset should be changed and let engineers have a chance to develop their ideas .
Furthermore , engineers should do their research and marketing of their products effectively , such that product that they develop will be of marketing value .
Meanwhile many new kind of innovative inventions come out almost in every day changing the way people living .
There exists a remarkable fact which is that a technical innovation is viewed different between different groups of people .
A wonderful invention to a group of people may be dislike to the other ones .
In general , the justification of the utility of a specific technology or invention depends on the specific perspectives from different group of people .
Space technology is a good example to explain the reason how different views come out .
Space technology is a kind of high innovative , high compositive and also high cost technology .
Its aim is to find out the unknown scientific questions and for military use .
The beginning of space technology derives from America and Russia .
Then it quickly spreads out to all over the world .
Nowadays European countries , China , Japan and India are all have a high development in space technology .
Toward this new technique , there are two opposite opinion exist in these days .
Government and scientists think it is worth to spend money and people working on this , and it will benefit the whole country .
However , many people look it in another way that it is a waste of resource which can be used to improve people 's living condition .
If we look a little deeper into the causes that lead to the opposite solution , we will find that the focus that specific group of people pays attention to is , obviously , quite different from each other .
In the government and scientists ' point of view , space technology is essential that it is the fundamental things we need to do to protect our country and fulfill future needs .
They pay lots attention to keep technique developing moving and more concentrate on the huge issue , like military demand , and the future .
That is also the reason why every country tries their best to improve the space technique .
Former president of America Regan even state the announcement of star war program , although it was given up at the end .
They focus more on current living condition and environment .
They simply pay their attention to the surrounding that needs to improve to make a better living condition .
Associated with the high cost space technology development , they will think government focus on this is a kind of waste .
In their opinion , government should spend these money and resource to these places where we can benefit from in today 's life .
So , it is not surprising that not all people satisfied when Chinese Government proudly announce the success of launching Shenzhou-5 spacesuit into the universe .
In conclusion , judgments towards a technical innovation or development always tend to different directions when these are made by different group of people .
All in all , the difference does really derive from the different thinking perspectives .
Because people tend to think about things associating with their own experience and life , different justification come out .
Hundreds of years ago , people used to go out riding horses ; illuminate the house by candles ; start fire using firewood 's .
And we now go out by buses ; light the house by electric lights ; start fire using lighters... Nowadays , people are living in a very convenient world .
But few my notice that we are facing a serious problem behind all these inventions we are using .
And the short of petroleum is the most important issue that we must take care .
Why is the petroleum so important ?
Without these extracted products from petroleum , cars can not run , planes can not fly , and ships can not launch out .
What 's more , petroleum is a liquid mixture of hydrocarbons which is present in suitable rock strata and is not reproducible for now .
One way is to conserve and save the petroleum .
Engineers have brought out some solutions for saving the petroleum .
One of the engineer 's solutions is to mix the alcohol and petrol together to provide the energy .
This solution is now in the test and implement period .
In Wuhan , one of the biggest cities in China , all the taxies are operating using this mixture fuel .
When the vehicle starts , it consumes the electric power .
That 's why we can smell strong petrol when the car starts .
To do this concept of power system is to let the fuel fully used in order to save the fuel .
Hydrogen fuel cell , solar power and nuclear power are the three hottest topics that interested engineers most .
The research of fuel cell on vehicles was started in early 1960s and it gets well developed until now .
Most of car makers have come out with their own hydrogen fuel cell powered vehicles .
But hydrogen fuel cell vehicles are still in the test and implement phase .
But for finalized product , the cost should be reduced and the efficiency of the cell should be increased .
The key point to increase the efficiency of solar power is how to concentrate the sunshine .
If this point can be solved , the potential of solar power is prodigious .
For nuclear power , actually it is using the power generated by the nuclear fusion .
Nuclear fusion is the same way as the sun to generate its power .
The research of nuclear fusion has been processed for decades , but the progress is not so obvious .
In brief , the energy problem is one of the most serious problems to us now .
So we need to be step by step , follow the right rules , to get the best solution of this urgent problem .
However the above only holds through for those who are not stricken with poverty .
Surely the needs of these people , most of whom are based in developing countries , are endless .
This is because basic infrastructure is the basis for any country to develop essential facilities like transport , housing and education , to help the poor .
The word 'need ' refers a man 's desire for a certain product or system .
This need is usually identified by the society and may vary from society from society .
Thus needs which are considered a necessity to some might actually be a luxury to others .
The nomads would prefer to conserve the forests and wildlife so as to be able to carry on their nomadic lifestyle .
So it 's vital for engineers to collect as much information as possible so as to not repeat the mistakes and go down the same slippery slope of their predecessors .
The most logical step after you have come up with a few solutions is to pick the best one .
This is actually the decisionmaking process , after studying the various solutions .
For instance , if a school is being built , based in the land available , few designs would have already thought off .
Certain schools might be able to hold more students while not proving to be as stable as another that hold fewer students but is very much stronger .
Ironically , this step is one that is followed by most however , they do not bother to pick out flaws and in the end the consumer uses a flawed product .
Possible flaws should be picked out so that the product can be improved on later .
In conclusion , I would like to recommend the engineering design process because it 's very complete in its steps to provide a solution to those in need .
The establishment of basic infrastructure in developing countries through engineering design will give the poor an avenue to success fully escape from the vicious cycle of poverty .
The world today is undergoing global warming which is caused by the burning of fossil fuels and deforestation .
The first step in the design process is the problem definition .
Tapping of kinetic energy in wind is a good solution as wind is abundant due to the frequent changes in the atmospheric pressure .
It announces to the engineers that Earth is in grave danger , thus giving them more motivation to think of a solution .
For example , by defining the problem as the fast decreasing quantity of fossil fuels , it gives engineers an insight to create a product which can be used to tap kinetic energy in wind .
Referring to the earlier models of windmills like those built in Sistan , Iran , from the seventh century , which were used to grind rice grains , engineers used the same concept to create wind turbine which converts kinetic energy in wind to electrical energy .
The credibility of the problem needs to be addressed after the problem has been defined .
The last step in the design process is the testing and implementing of solutions .
The testing and implementing solutions is closely related to the analysis of the design solution .
Lastly , the testing and implementing of solutions consists of marketability , ergonomics and safety which serve as a check on whether the product is deemed suitable to solve the problem .
Nowadays , engineering design products are cores for everything .
Engineering systems play important roles in all the fields ; for example entertainment , healthcare as well as education .
Although it is essential for all the fields , engineering products and systems in healthcare and medical fields should be given the highest priority since health is the most important thing for all human beings .
Designing of medical products which can make all human beings ; young and old as well as disabilities easier and safer is obviously important .
On the other hand , people spend much more time normally for entertainment than healthcare .
As a result there are mass products for entertainment because of high demand .
There are many healthcare products which are available in research organization but not widely available in current market .
For example , " Fall Detection System " which can detect the fall of person especially elder people and can send instant message via sms to relatives so that the person can get immediate help in critical situations .
As mentioned in " Global action on aging " website that the number of senior citizens are rising and the action for this should be taken , it is obvious that increasing number of elder people and taking care of them has been necessary to be considered .
It is also mentioned that since the number of elderly people increases , the burden of caring is also increasing for young people .
Hence , engineering should consider the situation of increasing number of elders and come out with the solution which can take care of situation in order to help elder people safe as well as make youth work without worry .
Although there are R&Ds for healthcare products for monitoring and taking care of elder people , these devices are not widely used in the market .
So , in order to get this situation , engineers should think about the ways that can make the design process meet the need of the market situation .
One of the examples of medical system is " Posture Monitoring System " which can monitor body posture all the time and keep warning the user to maintain best posture .
Recently in 2009 , Nanyang Poly Technic won merit prize in Tan Kah Kee young inventors ' award competition in Singapore by its posture monitoring system and there are also research papers and prototypes of posture monitoring system by R&D from other countries but are not widely available in current market .
One example of engineering products for disabilities which is mentioned in The Straits Times by Grace Chua is a chair that turns sound into vibrations which is invented by NUS PhD student Suranga Nanayakkara , which could help deaf people experience music and even aid them in speech therapy .
In order to make engineering design product meet the needs , first of all , clear and unambiguous definition of this problem should be defined .
Problems should be widely and well defined by engineers , elder people as well as adults so that more innovative products and ideas come out .
Once alternative solutions coming out , engineers need to analyze and decide bested suited solution to implement .Government and organization are also responsible to support R&D process in order to gather information needed , generate multiple solutions , analyze solutions and test as well as implement solutions which are the necessary steps for the design process .
In conclusion , engineers should try to get preferable situation in the market for the products , for example , " Fall Detection System " which can take care of elder people and " Posture monitoring system " which can help people of all ages to maintain best posture with the help of government and organizations as well as consumers .
And the goal can also be achieved by developing most suitable design engineering process for the system and products for healthcare .
A human need is a necessity that human required in order to survive .
According to the World Food Program 's 2008 report , 25000 people are dying every day due to famine and related issue .
A large portion of the deaths comes from the Third World Countries like Africa and India .
By using the Engineering Design Process introduced by Seyyed Khandani , a professor at Diablo Valley College , we can reduce the famine .
Some factors that play a part in of famine include political , technological and environmental issues .
The World Food Program ( WFP ) has been providing food and aids to areas affected by famine since it established .
The definition of the problem is straight forward in the beginning , the people are starving , so they provide food .
However , for Malawi , the WFP and the World Bank analyzed the solution and found out that it is better to donate cash to them ; as they did some researches and found out that the country has food resources , but the poor can not afford it .
In 1990s , the WFP introduced the donation of cash and vouchers policies ; one of the pioneer countries that received this aids is Malawi .
Thus , providing cash did not only help to solve the famine , it also improved the financial situation for the farmers .
Furthermore , the WFP saved time and cost from the collection of food and delivering it to the affected areas .
In 1970s , the WFP has been providing food to India to temporarily solve the famine .
During this period , they have been analyzing the situation to generate other solutions to permanently solve the famine .
According to the design process , the second step is to gather related information , then generate various solutions .
The first off solution is to provide genetically modified seeds and fertilizers to the farmers , so that they will obtain higher yield .
Before this solution was implemented , they did a further study , and realized that the solution will not work ; as the farmers are using traditional farming methods which are not yield efficient .
These aids have improved the famine situation as the famine dropped by about 20 % in a WFP 's 1990s report ; On the other hand , these solutions are not applicable to all the lands in India as various areas have different types of lands .
For the dry lands , the WFP has do further researches on water irrigation methods .
One of the solutions is to construct a drainage system from the Indira Ghandi canal to irrigate the dry lands in the region .
Some events like drought , flood and earthquakes are causes to famine .
Nevertheless , events like deforestation and overgrazing has affected the fertile lands and caused the yield to go down .
While governments spend millions and billions of dollars on entertainments and military expenditure yearly , these large amount of money can be put to good use in helping their own people .
India has increased the military spending by 50 % in 2008 , bringing the amount to 40 billion dollars ; despite that 35 % of the people are still affected by famine .
That large amount of money can be invested in the agriculture sector , like having the technology to plant seeds that will grow on dry land , which will greatly solve the famine .
In conclusion , the WFP can do more researches and analysis , like creating genetic modified seeds that can survive in dry or wet land , or an indoor farming center that will shelter the crops from natural disasters , which will resolve the famine issue .
In addition , the governments can try to allocate more budgets to the agriculture and research center than invested tons of money on entertainment sector , which is redundant when people in their own country are suffering without having a basic need .
The last step of the design process is to test and implement the solution .
By moving a small step forward , will reduce the famine .
Thus , we should do more to help the people that are suffering from famine .
Communication is an important part of human development , it allows ideas and information to be disseminated effectively .
Two main driving factors that shaped the innovations of radio will be economic and military demands , leading to the usage of radio beyond pure communication .
The first radio set was able to transmit only simple signals , still it was valuable enough to be used by the maritime .
An example will be the sending of message to the nearest ship requesting for assistance by the Titanic before it sank , it illustrated the usefulness of radio as a tool for communication in situations where line communication is not possible .
Sending of Morse code via radio set was further popularised by the telegraphy which transformed the use of radio into a service much like the postal .
Telegraphy flourish as it was relatively reliable and much faster than postal , encouraging more resources to be channelled into the development and research of radio technology .
As the average cost of production declined steadily , radio set was mass produced leading to the birth of radio broadcasting .
Warnings and announcements regarding weather or disaster evacuation can be made via broadcasting will greatly help in minimising the casualty rate in a disaster as the mass can receive vital and timely information and instruction even when the cable lines are damaged .
The other factors that influence the development of radio will be military demands .
Besides improving on communication , military demands had also led to the invention of radar which uses radio wave in detecting distance objects and getting information such as their location and movement .
From its communication values to other discovered usages , economic factor and military demands have played a positive role in its overall development .
Invention and development of radio has better the society in numerous ways .
Overpopulation is one of the current human needs that should be given priority .
Size or Density of the population affects the overpopulation .
In the world where the human populations are growing , we should focus on solving the problem of insufficient land to maintain the life on earth .
The houses today are stronger , and some of them can withstand natural disaster .
For example in Japan , a country where earthquake happen often , their engineer is trying to solve the problem of building a building that can withstands earthquake .
By using the Khandani Principle , the engineers gather pertinent information about the earthquake and manage to implement a solution after several test had been conducted , called Seismic retrofitting method , where Seismic retrofitting is the changing of existing building to a structure that is more resistant to ground motion , soil failure due to earthquakes or seismic activity .
Engineers try to solve overpopulation by combine many houses into one building , thus building multi-unit housing or also known as attached dwellings has been invented .
Apartment , barracks , tenement and terrace house is good example of multi-unit housing .
Engineer applied Khandani principle that time , they define the problem and has gather enough information to make sure the building will not collapse .
For example , in Singapore , where the land is very small , engineers build a lot of condominiums and apartments to solve the problem of insufficient houses and manage to save some of the land for other purposes .
In the future , the population will increase much more , and by building more multi-unit housing can not solve the problem effectively .
In my opinion , engineer should focus on upgrading the building .
They should implement the solution of building multiple level basements for multi-unit housing and building since we do n't really use a lot of the underground space .
Building multiple level basements may cause some other potential problems and engineer should try to solve these .
Engineers have to analyze every possible problem that may occur like water seepage , internal condensation , underground virus and bad acoustics when building more underground level .
That is why building more underground level , we need to use Khandani principle 2005,that is require engineer to gather a lot of pertinent information from any sources available before implement it .
In addition , engineers can also improve the stability of the building so that more levels can be built above the building .
The stability of the building depends on the wideness of the base level , the material of the structure and the method of building the structure .
Engineer can increase the wide of the base of the structure to support extra level of building build on it .
Engineer can improve the structures by using more strong material like diamonds , gold , and etc and finding more suitable method for building a structure .
Engineers need to test the solution before they started to use it .
Hidden problem can be found out testing it under real condition .
( Khandani , 2005 )
If we compare the house 10000 BC to the modern house today , engineering design process is apparent .
If in the world we do n't have engineering design process , engineers may generate solution that is ineffective or it may cause harm to other life form .
The issue of the depletion of earth 's natural resources have been raised repeatedly throughout recent times .
Singapore , due to its small land size area also face the problem of the lack of natural resources .
In order for Singapore to be self-reliance on water , there is a need for Singapore to create portable water resources for its people .
Singapore had tried a number of ways in its bid to shift towards self- reliance of water .
However , these methods are still short of providing for the growing need of water of its people .
The product of it is called New water .
New water is treated waste water that had undergone stringent purification processes using advance dual membrane and ultraviolet technology .
The product can be bottled for consumption or be mixed with reservoir water and then going through the usual water treatment to produce drinkable water .
This is indeed a product of system which is engineered to meet the human need for natural resources .
Singapore has been buying water from Malaysia , its neighbouring country in order to supplement its own water supply .
Secondly , they gather pertinent information on the technologies and usage of water that is purified from waste water .
They eventually build its first plant after the technology of dual membrane purification has matured and the production cost has come down .
Thirdly , prior to the implementation of the New water technology , there are also multiple solutions to the problem of lack of water resources in Singapore .
Solutions include desalination of sea water and damping up more rivers to increase the water catchment area .
The desalination of seawater will require large amount of fossil fuel to run which is another natural resource that Singapore do not have .
Furthermore , the desalination plants will also leave a larger carbon footprint .
Despite these , a desalination plant is still build because of the growing demand .
The damping up of rivers to form water catchment areas is in fact being implemented .
Marina barrage the newest kid on the block was formed by damping the marina channel to form a large water catchment area capable of meeting 10 % of Singapore 's need .
However , as Singapore has limited land , we can not go on forever creating water catchment area from our land .
Therefore , New water is decided as a solution needed to meet the need for water of the Nation .
Finally , in May 2000 , the first New water plant is completed .
Currently there are 4 New water plant in Singapore with a fifth on its way .
Bottled New water were also given out during National events , promoting the use of the New water in our daily life .
In conclusion , New water has been a engineering design which was designed to meet the human need of the lack of water resources particularly in Singapore .
Throughout the history of human , there are a lot of successful products which have great effect on human life , just like television , cell phone and so on .
It is not only their high level technology that makes them so successful , but also that they meet the need of the people .
Electric car , which is first invented by General Motors Company ( GM ) , is such an interesting case .
The invention of electric cars is both successful and failure .
We can analysis it in both social and technological aspects .
Electric car is the product of social reasons .
As we know , ordinary car 's fuel is gas which is used since the first car has been produced .
While there exists a problem that the burning of gas gives off poisonous gas and large amount of carbon dioxide which cause serious air pollution .
Furthermore , as it is mineral resource , the storage of gas is becoming less and less which directly leads to the rise of the price .
Another direct reason social reason is that in the early 1990s , the California and Arizona state governments had raised a policy which said at least 10 percent of the cars produced in the automobile companies should be environmental friendly , in another word is nonpolluting .
This promoted the research of electric cars .
In the mean time , GM also wanted to use this opportunity to restore their position in automobile world .
This is the social reasons that do favor to electric car .
With the development of the technology , people have more comfortable and beautiful clothes to wear , more enjoyable entertainment to participate , more delicious food to eat and more convenient transportation tools to use .
Nowadays , as our Earth Mother becomes hotter , human beings ' living condition is greatly threatened by the global warming , the issue which is discussed fiercely among scientists .
As an engineer , we must also take this responsibility to protect our Earth Mother .
It is commonly known that global warming is caused by frequently industrial activities these years ; in detail , it is due to the emission of green house gas ( GHG ) .
In recent years , due to much more frequent industrial activities , the curve of emission of CO2 consequently jumps to a very high point , so does the curve of temperature .
Nowadays , the rising temperature has been paid much more attention because of some sudden , striking surprise , for instance , the melting ice in Antarctica , the rising sea level .
As mentioned above , the rising temperature is due to much more emission of green house gas , so the key to global warming will focus of this issue .
Firstly , we can make use of natural energy instead of fuel , as we all know , burning fuel will emit a lot of green house gas , including CO2 .
However , if we use natural energy , we can not only reduce the emission of green house gas , but also save our resource .
Water energy is also a kind of natural energy which can be exploited by human beings , such as China .
Kyoto Protocol signed in Japan is the best example .
In this protocol , the member countries have to reduce certain amount of green house gas according to the amount of green house gas they produced and the most acceptable way is just reduce industrial activities .
Thirdly , increase planting area is also an efficient way to reach our goal , as plants could absorb CO2 .
In conclusion , the threaten of global warming has come , we engineers need to face it bravely and design products against the climate change .
We have only one Earth Mother , we will never lose her .
As the progress of our society , human beings get stuck in a dilemma of energy .
On one hand , the energy resources we use now which are mainly fossil fuels will be exhausted soon if we continue to consume as current rate while the use of fossil fuels trigger out a series of environmental problems .
On the other hand , the development of society calls for larger and larger amount of energy , which makes us in desperate need of energy .
In order to develop our society without exhausting all the fossil fuels or sacrificing our environment , we have to find new energy resources to take place of traditional fossil fuels .
In this case , solar energy stands out becoming our first choice .
Engineering design play a significant role in the use of solar energy , especially in the system of solar heating .
In fact , humans began to utilize solar energy to heat water as early as 3000 years before .
The question how to make a efficient and effective solar heating system is addressed by engineers .
In order to find the solution , engineers spend large amount of time to collect the relative information , from which they can generate inspiration while draw lessons from the previous work .
Though this preliminary stage appears simple , actually it not only takes a lot of time and calls for patient , but also is the crucial fundamental of the solution .
Then engineers come to the core step that is the generation of solutions .
First , engineers decide to make a solar collector which can effectively collect solar from surroundings .
Because of efficient heat conductibility of metal , engineers use a huge piece of metal which is painted black to collect the solar energy .
After that , engineers build the circulation equipment to make water flow below the metal so that the metal can transmit the heat to water and then people can use the heated water .
According to this solar heating system , engineers also come up with certain products widely used in our daily life , such as the solar water heater .
What engineers do next is to test the system and make possible improvements .
It is not stable enough so that people may not be able to use solar energy to heat water whenever they need .
To improve the solar heating system , engineers add accessorial energy equipment to it such as electrical heater .
To make the efficient and effective solar heating system , engineers carefully define the problem and collect important information about this issue , then they generate all the possible solutions , finally they test the solutions and make changes to improve the solution .
Besides solar heating system , engineering design is also used in other fields in terms of energy issue .
In the current world people depend more and more on technology to improve their life , which stimulus the development of science and technology in reverse .
In my opinion , we should pay most attention on the development of clean energy such as solar energy .
The reason why we should focus on the research of solar energy is that the atmospheric pollution caused by the consumption of fossil fuels is severe , there is enough amount of solar energy to be used on earth , and the diffusion and adoption of solar energy product is satisfying .
In fact , the research of solar energy can be traced back to the year of 1900 .
Although at that time they only focused on solar power plant .
Later , because of the decrease of petroleum and natural gas , the scientists paid attention to solar energy again .
Until today , the process of solar energy research is still quite difficult .
However , because of the severe pollution problem , we have to focus on the development of solar energy .
Nowadays , there are already various kinds of solar energy product in the market .
For example , people use solar energy converter to heat up water , which will save amazing amount of energy acquired from other ways .
Besides , the usage of solar panel should become more and more important in the future .
It is said that if we can cover a place of 40,000 square miles with solar panel , the demand for electricity of the whole world will be satisfied .
Also , solar energy is inexhaustible and we can use it without worrying about polluting the atmosphere , which really solved the problem brought by the consumption of fossil fuels .
In some place of the world , people are accepting solar energy product such as solar energy converter as they think that it is fashionable and pollution-free .
But in cities such as GuangDong and ShangDong provinces in China , people are not so willing to install solar energy converter though the government forced some buildings to install the converters to save energy and reduce carbon emission .
Some residents in America covered their roof with solar energy panel and hopes those panels will provide 50 percent to 80 percent of power consumption in their house .
Moreover , since the price of solar energy panel is decreasing recently , more and more consumers will think about the usage of solar energy panel .
In the 1980s and 1990s , the research of solar energy fell into the low tide because that the price of petroleum fell down and the solar energy product was too expensive and there was no important breakthrough about the development of solar energy product .
However , since the environmental pollution has become one of the most important topics in the world nowadays , we also should pay more attention to clean energy such as solar energy .
The usage of solar energy product will not only save large amount of energy and solve the problem of energy crisis but also give us a clean world with little pollution .
With the developmemt of the society , our demand for the various commodity keeps increasing .
However , without enough energy to manufacture the products , how can our desire be satisfied !
Therefore , the current human need to find endless energy source is becoming more and more urgent so that it should be given priority .
To satisfy the current human need , we ha better use Roger 's Engineering design process to work out a supreme solution .
As we know , most of the energy we are consuming is fossil energy such as coal and oil which is limited .
If we just depend our future on fossil energy source , how can we live on after hundreds of years !
Just a few years ago , America declared a war against Iraq with the justification that there were bio-chemistry weapons in Iraq .
This war alarms us that if we do not solve the energy problems , more wars may be declared in the future .
However , there are many other kinds of energy source on the earth such as nuclear power , water power and solar power .
Now the problem is how to use these power to substitutde the fossil energy , which means how to convert these power into the energy that can be used by us such as electrical power .
To solve this problem , building electrical powerhouse may be the best choice .
The reason is that the electrical power is clean , easily transported and easily stored .
Although making use of nuclear power , water power and solar power seems feasible , there are some reasons that make solar power be the most appropriate .
Nevertheless , it can generate so huge power that it is very unsafe .
The strong radiation of the explosion even influenced all the North Hemisphere .
What a tragedy it is !
Depending our future on nuclear power , we can not guarantee there will be no such kind of explosion any longer .
Undeniably , the technology of solar power convertion today is still not perfect .
Many improvements should be made to increase the convertion rate and lower the cost of the equipment so it can be pervaded .
Compared to other energy , solar power has three big advantages .
Actually , the sunlight is electramagnetic wave .
Nowadays , we already have built some solar powerhouses but we never hear anything unfortunate happens .
Therefore , for the three advantages above , we can find it really meaningful to develop the solar power tachnology .
Furthermore , during the development of solar power technology , we should pay more attention to solving the difficulty of the pervasion .
Lowering the cost of the application is also very important , otherwise nobody is willing to adopt this technology .
In conclusion , to maintain the sustainable development of our society , we should give priority to the current human need to develope more energy from various source of human society .
Among the diverse energy source , solar power has the brightest prospect for its non-pollution , safety and infinitude .
From a luxurious entertaining appliance in the early stage of development , television becomes an indispensable and ubiquitous thing within every family nowadays .
