Natural resources around the world has been depleting at an alarming rate which has led to numerous debates and interventions by environmentalists , in a bid to reduce the amount of resources extracted and employed by mankind .
One such example is the purification of water to make it portable .
According to statistical figures from a United Nations Organisation ( UN ) publication , the global population consumes approximately 3000 kilometric of water daily .
As a result , there is an increasing need for newer , greener and more cost-effective purification methods so as to provide massive amounts of clean and affordable drinking water for all parts of the world especially in less-developed countries .
For example in Singapore , the government identifies that she has to be more self-reliant and self-dependent on her water supplies so as to mitigate any difficulties faced in times of contingency and emergency .
As such , large emphasis and investments have been vested into this initiative since then .
Hence , this example has shown that through the proper implementation of engineering design framework and application of modern technology , the current human need of securing clean and cheap drinking water can be achieved with a high degree of success .
As a result , both human and technology has an important role to play in the quest of satisfying human needs .
According to Rogers , E. M , writer of " Diffusion of innovations " , in general , there are six stages of innovation-development process .
Some of them are determined by the technology perspective or social factors , whereas some includes government involvement .
One important technology that Rogers mentioned is the innovation of refrigerator in 1930 for electric and gas refrigerators .
When people do a comparison on both types , latter has a better advantage on the first and they were expecting for the gas refrigerator .
But it did not captured in the consumer market .
The main reason for this is because of the investment , consideration and decision made by the corporations involved in this project .
They believed that they would make more profits from electric refrigerator and thus market it to the public .
As a result , it turns out that technology in electric refrigerator is available to the consumer in stead of the consumer choice .
Another example on social problem lead to government involvement and scientist is the safety issue with automobile in the United States .
In 1960 , the annual fatality due to vehicle reached 50,000 that drew the government attention of the safety issue on the transport system .
Survey conducted between the specialized researchers and public 's view of the traffic safety problem .
It was found out that the research team did n't agree with the public view and claimed that it was individual-blame perspective .
As a conclusion from conductive researchers , professors , government officials and insurance company executives , the research on safety measure became due to system-blame perspective and thus redesigned auto vehicles and restructured highways .
As a consequence for above both cases , the technology did not become the way the consumers expect and the solution for solving social problem was redirected .
Most of them will be varied along the process due to several factors and thus lead to different type of innovation .
From my point of view , no matter on the sequence of innovation-development process , as long as there is a new invention , it is invented to benefit all the mankind .
Technology has improved so rapidly in the past century that men have threaded into outer space , harvest enormous amounts of energy from minute quantities of nuclear material , and yet there still exists the problem of food shortage .
Like what Seyyed Khandani said , " You start with existing solutions to the problem and then tear them apart-find out what is wrong with those solutions and focus on how to improve their weaknesses " ( 11 ) .
By constantly improving on the process of gene modification , it can be improved to the extent of meeting the strict requirements for human consumption .
Engineering design processes also involve branching into different areas of study and combining existing technology to create new ones .
Seyyed Khandani mentioned about a process called synthesis , which is to integrate ideas , equipment and processes to create new solutions ( 11 ) .
In spite of the increase of research and development in recent years , there is still a significant amount of discoveries and innovation are still been made by people outside of laboratories .
These kind of unconventional environments are commonly referred to as skunkwords environment .
However , we would define it more broadly to include all researches done without the aid of external aid .
As mentioned by E.M. Rogers in his article The Birth of the Laptop Computer at Toshiba , Tetsuya Mizoguchi ,who came up with the idea of developing a mobile computer , had to went " underground " after his proposal was rejected by his superiors .
As his idea was unconventional , his company did not want to allocate resources into this unknown territory .
In order continue his research , he secretly used money from his company and transferred engineers from other projects to carry out his research .
After 2 years of research , they created their first prototype that progress to change how the use of computers around the world .
Indeed , the huge impact brought about by Mizoguchi is shown by IDC 's forecast which says laptops would represent 66 percent of corporate purchases , with 71 percent of consumers opting for a notebook instead of a tower by 2011 .
Also , care were taken to ensure all the of the water treatment procedures are widely acceptable .
Although it has resulted in a sounding success , the technology has not been widely implemented due to patents of the technology being filed by the parent companies .
For example , the engineers of General Motor 's ( GM ) R&D unit in Detroit were able to create astatically pleasing and highly efficient automobile that runs entirely on battery power ( Rogers 2003 ) .
Similarly , bio fuel studies made by independently by many researchers found that it could be used to replace fossil fuels .
One of the techniques involves developing fast-growing trees that can grow to size in just 10 years to generate the bio fuel .
In conclusion , in spite of the various inherent differences of conventionally generated technologies and innovations from skunkworks , such as revolutionary or conservative , both share various similarities such as providing possible but not definite solutions to our problems .
It is by complementing each way of research 's advantages that we may is able to discover ways to solve future problems .
The Innovation-Development Process , as defined by E.M. Rogers , essentially 'consist of all the decision , activities and their impacts that occur from recognition of a need or a problem through research , development and commercialization of an innovation ' ( Rogers 2003 , The generation of innovation ) .
This process is further broken down into 2 perspective , technologically or socially determinist .
