Generally speaking , intended research to pursue development is similar with serendipitous discovery in terms of the aim and contribution to the human society .
First of all , the aim of technology which was developed with research is to explore some useful things and attempt to reach the unknown scientific area in order to solve the problems in real world .
For example , people spend a great amount of money to reach Mars to explore the mysterious outer space even though the probability to help make improvement for the Earth is low .
Similarly , the serendipitous is the effect by which one accidentally discovers something fortunate , especially while looking for something entirely different .
Hence , the result of serendipitous also helps explore the unknown things and places .
In addition , both of technology that was discovered by research and serendipitous discovery contribute to the human society .
Specifically , the majority of technological innovations are developed by scientific research which based on knowledge , research and application in practice .
In order to make achievement , it requires a lot of work to do thus it would take a long time .
On the contrast , serendipitous discovery seems very fortunate because people receive unexpected things which are always beneficial for human society .
For example , Sir Alexander Fleming discovered the first antibioticpenicillin when he was doing research on the biological materials occasionally .
Similarly , DDT was also discovered by accident in the 1930s , when a Swiss chemist , Paul Muller , was trying to find a way to protect wool clothes against moths .
In conclusion , people always try their best to make inventions to solve problems encounter in real world .
Keep doing research on different scientific area is one main aspect to discover what humankind desire .
Both fulfill useful function in human society .
Truly speaking , people may prefer to serendipitous discovery for its convenient , fortunate as well as the same award , whereas it is more difficult to achieve .
Comparison and contrast of two technologies innovated in these two different ways gives us many interesting features of innovations to ponder about .
A classical example for a technology invented serendipitously is the discovery of Warfarin , the most effective rat poison in world .
In due time , it was found that the cattle herd were dying rapidly .
When the cattle blood was analyzed in the lab a hemorrhaging agent called Coumarin was isolated .
Further experiments and tests helped the bioscientists to discover the beneficial effects of this agent for surgeries and other purposes .
In this case , the issue gained high priority in the Congress , thanks to the help of Ralph Nader 's " Unsafe at Any speeds " .
Every detail of the bill passed was carefully constructed keeping in mind the status quo .
However in the case of the serendipitous innovations there is no exact driving force .
Set of experiments accidentally yield results which prove to be significant .
Who could have thought that an apple would be enough for a man to develop the concept of mechanics and gravitation ?
But today without them our survival seems questionable .
Engineers have been designing products or systems to improve the everyday life .
Constantly , the process has developed new technology that helped to solve problems to human like making travel to countries faster and comfortable by planes .
That problem is to make drinkable fresh water to everyone in the third world countries .
Engineering process involves defining the problem , gathering pertinent information , generating multiple solutions , analyzing and selecting solution and test and implements the solution as quoted from Khandani .
Water covers 71 % of the earth surface and water from ocean take up 97 % from total percentage of surface water .
( Wikipedia ) Even though water seemed to be everywhere , only a very small percentage of water is drinkable to the global population .
There are also many places in the third world countries where drinkable water is not available due to lack of rain fall and pollution in the water sources .
Third world countries ' government knows that there is a need to solve water shortage problem .
However , developing new and clean water technology needs large amount of money .
This money can be put to better use like getting medications for their people .
Another possible reason for the problem to be existed could be pollution from industries .
Inland water sources are being polluted by factories which dump chemical waste products into the water sources which make the water source not fit for usage .
Since inland water sources are being polluted and not fit for drinking , Ocean which covers a large area on earth is another possible option .
In order to make the extracted water to be fit for drinking water standard set by World Health organization ( WHO ) , engineers will include a process that add nutrients into it .
However , this solution can only help to solve the problem in the long run if only the water catchment areas are free from pollutions .
The result might not be an immediate effect as it takes time for natural rain fall to fill up the reservoirs .
Lastly , Engineers can do some testing on desalinating seawater into drinkable water after they have drafted out a cheap and affordable desalination process for the third world countries to purchase .
The results from the testing will be sent to WHO for approval to desalination plant to be build for producing drinkable water in the area .
If the technology is newer than the previous old desalination process , the engineers might able to get it patent so the price for this new technology will be affordable to everyone .
This process is able to apply in producing clean water from seawater which helps solve water shortage problems in certain countries .
The process able to identify the problem , understand why it is still not solved , produce solutions to it and getting it work in an engineering way .
Automobile vehicles played an important role in this modern world as human rely heavily on it as a main type of transport for travelling .
Firstly , the raise of the automobile industry started as early as the nineteen centuries and the First World War acts as a catalyst to speed up the research and development processes of automobile vehicles .
This is so as during the war , there is a raise in demand for automobile vehicles to transport soldiers and supplies to front line .
It is also used for combat purposes .
Funding and incentives were given to companies to improve automobile technology as whichever countries with the more advance technologies have a higher chance of winning the war .
Secondly , the developments of automobiles vehicles are encouraged and limited by government policies and regulations .
Most places are accessible by roads , this in term boast the sales of automobiles and with the increase in sales .
With the raising sales of cars , consumers will have more demands ; manufacturers will spend more money in research and development so as to give their customers more choices .
Besides constructing roads , governments give tax rebates to companies that are heavily involves in research and development projects .
Speed limits and safety regulation set by governments are also factors to be considered when designing and developing new technologies .
Automobiles manufacturers take advantage of these situations and limitations to evolve their products technologies to another level .
Finally , all the research and developments of technology depend on economic factor .
This is so as no investor would be willing to fund a project that does not make money .
Hence , when engineers make improvements to enhance the technologies aspect of automobile vehicles , they have to consider the interest of the company .
The technical aspects of car depend heavily on production cost .
Hence technology is actually a product of society and is influenced by the norms and values of the social system .
The biggest priorities of companies were to ensure that projects that they are involved have great profit potential .
Toshiba is the first brand to have laptop known by many people .
But did you ever know that the invention of laptop is not support by the top executives of Toshiba at that time .
Indeed , there are always some innovations were created in a skunk works environment .
However , many other innovations are created in a conventionally generated environment .
The first example is the engineer of Toshiba who wanted to create a laptop ( pp.144- 146 Rogers , ( 2003 ) ) .
Although he discovered the eagerly need of smaller and portable computer in Japan .
However , at that time , Toshiba 's marketing situation was not good and the company did not want to risk for a new concept of product .
Fortunately , our hero Mizoguchi did not give up .
Otherwise , our laptop may not be as good as now .
Moreover , he diverted funds and found engineers himself to fulfill his idea of creating laptop .
The good thing is that after all his hard work , he finally proven to Toshiba that his invention very useful and sells very good .
After that , he became one of the chief of Toshiba .
On the other hand , for a conventionally generated technology , like the development of electric cars in California and Arizona , it is regulated by government ( Rogers , ( 2003 ) pp .
Company had to do research on how to manufacture it and make it be loved by consumers .
Although the whole process of making the car is very tough , the engineers were supported by company , government , and society all the way .
After briefly know the cases of both situations , differences of them come first .
The first difference is that engineers worked in a skunk words environment did not have much support from public or organizations , while conventionally generated technology received a lot of help from society and company .
The second difference between these two cases is that the idea of innovate laptop was come out with the inventor himself while the electric car issue is a requirement by government .
This different may not be necessary , but it is quite obvious that people in skunk words environment are more likely for their own ideas .
First and the most important one is that those innovations all promoted development of the society .
Secondly , no matter how much help they had received , they all do their best to present their best works .
No matter what difficulty they have faced , they did their best to deal with it and finally solve it .
In conclusion , the first differences between a skunk works environment and a conventionally generated environment are the differences between financial , technology , equipment , resource and people 's attitude towards them .
The second difference the source of the idea .
The similarities are those innovations all promoted the development of society and they do their best for the creation of their product and dream .
In Singapore , innovations in engineering design had been in the cold when compared to leading countries like Germany or Japan .
From my opinion , I can identify two problems that lead to this situation : Our education structure as well as the shallow engineering heritage that we have .
Firstly , the education structure in Singapore is too structured and does not promote the creativity of students .
Majority of our Singaporean kids will go through primary school and graduate with a PSLE certificate ; follow up with a Secondary school education in either the express , normal academic or normal technical stream .
This streaming system ; however , was largely based on the students ' abilities to cope with the standard subjects on language , math , science and humanities instead of the interest of the students in terms of arts , science or other humanities like literature .
In their eyes , creative students who want to make it into the art streams were just rotten apples who could n't do well in their standard subjects .
As a result , creativity which is the key to innovation is n't developed since young for many Singaporeans .
Aside from having tons of labor intensive industries during the 1970s , our focus of engineering was more towards money making opportunities rather than research and development .
Germany is famous for their innovative and precise engineering in their automotive industries since the 1920s .
Japan on the other hand , is famous for their creative and remarkable ideas for anything that they manufacture .
Singapore ; however , is famous for our clean and green country , which was basically the work of blue-collared workers cleaning up the streets during the wee-hours .
Singapore 's emphasis on commercial gains rather than innovations was largely influenced by the fact that we were a trading hub since British 's rule .
Chinese Merchants , Indian Spice traders and Malay Rubber traders involved in the trading market were the backbone of our country 's growth .
Our innovations came in the way that they do business instead .
In conclusion , if we are able to solve the education structure problem , it will still take a few more generations of Singaporeans before we can start to see results for our engineering innovations .
We will then be able to catch up to countries like Germany or Japan and be labeled as a country with innovative engineering .
