People are always tending to do things that will benefit .
However , some obstacles still hamper the process of technological innovation of China , as the technological development is in its infancy .
In my opinion , there are mainly two big problems for us to overcome in the next few years , which are the decentralization and shortage of sources and the lagging of technology transfer .
Source refers to human capital and financial support .
Actually , decentralization of human capital and delayed financial support hamper the stage of research and development to a quite large extent .
Compared to other developing countries , China does not have a standard innovation centre where a lot of talented scientists and engineers can discuss and develop a creative project .
Take Silicon Valley as an example , a lot of new technological products are developed and promising companies are founded there every year , which is a result of the cooperation of many talents .
How to call up them and work out some big projects is a tough task for our government .
However , if the financial support is divided into small parts , these departments will not get enough money to do a large scale research .
What 's more , some research projects must wait several months for financial support , during which time scientists may lose heart and give up .
As a result , research and development , which are the first steps of innovation , becomes more and more difficult .
China should try hard to solve the problem of source .
Some new technologies may be born as well as die in laboratories as a result of lagging of technology transfer .
Maybe it takes about a few years to generate a new generation .
What 's more , as China does not have a system to link these new techniques with manufacturing departments , I think most manufacturing factories can not make full use of these innovations .
Therefore , we 'd better to build a sound system to do the technology transfer .
Firstly , we 'd better develop some technical centre to bring talents together and do research .
If we can overcome these problem , I believe the design process of innovation in China will develop farther more .
However , in my home country , many problems exist as huge barriers for engineers to apply their innovative ideas into practice .
Chinese students are very diligent , but sometimes they focus too much on theory knowledge and the exams , while overlook the importance of cultivating their own innovative ability .
So when they become engineers , what they can do is only follow others ' steps and can not put forward new ideas .
Besides the cognition problem , some universities do not pay much attention on students ' hands-on abilities .
Experiment classes , which aim to help students develop their applying and innovative ability , are often deleted from the schedule or are conducted without experimental materials .
For technologies , experiencing personally is the best way to learn .
What 's more , we know it is hard for a person to come up with new ideas continuously but this process becomes much easier when several people exchange their thoughts about this issue .
There is no project , no lab report , no design assignments , how can students learn to work with others ?
Hence , some engineers can not communicate , do not know how to allocate workload ; do not know how to deal with difficulties and conflicts .
Another hamper is the unsatisfying society conditions for engineers to carry out their knowledge and thoughts .
When I compare my hometown university engineering graduates with their peers in NUS , I find those from NUS have more opportunities to have internships in institutes , to do experiments in team , to communicate with researchers and professors .
Apart from this , China does not attach as much attention on technology innovations as many other countries .
Besides the above two problems , lack of communication in engineering society also discourage the innovative ideas to come out .
There are not many conferences on engineering topics which can let engineers and scientists to exchange ideas and learn from each other .
After all the above , we can see the improper model and the unsatisfying social conditions really act as obstacles to innovative engineering designs .
As China is carrying out education reform in a large scale and putting more emphasis on technology innovations , we can predict China 's technology has a good perspective .
In the old days , taking photos was a complicated process which was almost performed solely by professional technicians .
A photographer had to not only adjust all the settings manually , but also print the films with chemicals called film developer in a darkroom .
However , the recent two decades witnessed astonishing innovation in photographythe development of digital cameras ( DC ) which has made taking photos accessible to non-specialists .
Consumers ' desire for more convenient usage and better photo quality shapes the development of DC technology .
Consumers ' desire for convenient usage mainly consists of two partsthe simplicity of camera functions and the accessibility of photo sharing .
Both of these requests stimulate the DC technology development in respective ways .
Relevant innovations include the face detection technology by Sony Company , which was developed in response to the increasing popularity of portrait taking ( Cheung , K. M. , 2007 ) .
Other technologies like the anti-blink function and the Smile Shutter function which automatically capture the best facial expressions are also developed in the need for simpler photo taking ( Sony Unveils World 's First Wi-Fi Digital Camera with Web Browser , 2009 ) .
Users can upload photos to the Internet and share the photos with more people .
A case in point is the development of Wi-Fi cameras .
With a web browser installed , this camera can get access to any hotspot , allowing users to upload their photos immediately after shooting ( Sony Unveils World 's First Wi-Fi Digital Camera with Web Browser , 2009 ) .
Another development that improves the convenience of taking photos is the portability .
Thus , they can be put in pockets and easily carried .
The improvement in portability also results from people 's increasing demand for easy casual shootings .
Consumers ' pursuit of better photo quality also drives the innovation of advanced DC technology .
To improve resolution , a company needs to conduct a considerable amount of research , including generation of new ideas , technology breakthroughs and repetitive experiments .
The process is hard , but companies are still willing to sacrifice their time and labor for the development , since the better the resolution , the more customers will be attracted , and the more profit the companies will make .
Such remarkable improvement shows the strong impact of consumers ' requirement on pushing forward the DC technology .
The innovation and development of DC technology are shaped by the need of the market .
On the other hand , the technological developments have greatly changed our lives at the same time , making our lives more convenient and colourful .
After telephone was invented in the late 1800s , people were thinking about ways to improve such communication technology to extend the range of social network .
The original idea of mobile phone came from combining telecommunication with radio technology which was considerably improved during the World War 2 period CITATION Spe90 \ l 2052 ( Special History Issue , 1990 ) .
Until the 1980s , due to the cellular idea , the portability and the quality of communication of mobile phone were improved and mobile telephony started to play a part in mass market CITATION Tom07 \ l 2052 ( Farley , 2007 ) .
And with the advance in internet technology , the third generation mobiles phones are digitized nowadays CITATION Wei05 \ l 2052 ( Wei , 2005 ) .
This essay will examine three major factors in the development of mobile telecommunication in different stages .
First of all , the post-war economic recovery demanded a better way of communication in order to expand the network of free trade between different countries .
In 1946 soviet engineers Shapiro and Zaharchenko CITATION Spe90 \ l 2052 ( Special History Issue , 1990 ) launched the first radio telephone which was equipped inside a car and could connect to local telephone network within the range of 20 kilometers .
Besides , as water transportation was developed rapidly during that period , radiotelephony service was introduced to harbor and coastal vessels CITATION Spe90 \ l 2052 ( Special History Issue , 1990 ) .
In the past , radio telephony was the only way to connect to telephone service when people were mobile .
Hence , the demands to achieve economic growth pushed mobile technology forward in the early days .
Donald H. Ring came up with the idea of cellular network in 1947 CITATION Tom07 \ l 2052 ( Farley , 2007 ) .
With the advance in computing technology in 1980s , a cellular network on mobile phones called Groupe Special Mobile was developed and this made mobile communication start to boom CITATION Tom07 \ l 2052 ( Farley , 2007 ) .
Similarly , the development of necessary technologies such as semi-conductors , transistors and microelectronic chips also contributed to the development of mobile telecommunications .
Therefore , progress in other fields can promote the innovations of mobile technology .
After the born of GSM , mobile phones started to more attract private users .
Unlike the business usage , private users demand a user-friendly environment to communicate with friends and family as well as some additional entertainment features .
Such demands by the public encouraged mobile developers to create new functions for cell phones such as delivering ring tones , SMS and voice mail CITATION Wei05 \ l 2052 ( Wei , 2005 ) .
Besides , mobile phones became digitized at the beginning of this century , which brought a revolution of mobile telecommunication .
Mobile phone today is no longer a phone that was mobile ; it can be a MP3 player , a game player and even a personal computer .
Within the context of a society , mobile telecommunicate was shaped by economic factors , other inventions and consumers ' demands .
The technology of nanorobotics ( nanobots ) is a modern invention that deals with the making of robots at an atomic level .
Nanobots would be helpful in making materials that is efficient in storing energy and converting energy sources .
They can be used to create a system that is affordable , fast , and compacted .
According to an article , $ 20 million was granted to Stanford - one of 46 Energy Frontier Research Centres - to help the engineers to find energy down at the nano-scale .
In Conclusion , the technology of nanobots is a modern innovation that allows human to process task that is beyond our bear-eye can see .
With the continuous development , nanobots would improve the lives of millions in the near future .
The main problem , however , is time constraint and this problem can be seen to significantly hamper engineering design processes for innovations in companies such as Creative Technology .
This time constraint is caused by competition from other companies which sell similar products and they may also be in the middle of designing similar new products as Creative Technology .
Mr Sim Wong Hoo , chairman and CEO of Creative Technology , commented that having awarded the ZEN Patent to Creative Technology , it had helped to protect its invention and recognized its innovation in portable media players .
He then further commented that in order to be awarded the ZEN Patent , it had taken a major investment of time and effort by a group of its research and development engineers .
( Creative Technology , 2005 ) It can be seen that because of time constraint , the research and development engineers from Creative Technology had to sacrifice most of their time just to focus on the engineering design processes for their new product , ZEN , so that it can be completed as soon as possible .
Furthermore , because of time constraints , certain processes in the engineering design processes may be compromised so that the ZEN can be completed earlier to beat the rest of the competitors .
Another problem is that the designing process must be able to keep up with the rapid developments in technology , otherwise by the time it is completed , it may already been rendered as obsolete .
Such case can be seen in St. James Press ( 2004 ) that Creative Technology began manufacturing its own CD-ROM drives when it could not keep up with the rapid developments in drive technology , however , it was forced to abandon the effort , dumping its inventory and taking a loss of more than $ 30 million in 1995 .
From here , we can see that the Engineering design processes must be constantly be updated , otherwise more problems may occur and this has caused many engineering design process to be abandoned halfway and hence , it is a problem that may significantly hamper engineering design process for innovations .
In conclusion , the two problems discussed earlier are just the few of the many problems that may significantly hamper engineering design processes for innovations .
However , still , there are many people who stood up to the difficulty and successfully completed the engineering design processes for innovations and I hope more people can learn from their experiences .
Since the 1970 's , communication technology has made great advances , offering capabilities that were unthinkable a decade earlier .
The last decade of the 20th century saw a flood of new communication technologies entering the market , office and home according to the Central Statistical office .
This was the result of a better of a better understanding of people 's needs and what technology they really want to use .
One such technology was the mobile phone .
In the past , communication was slow and unreliable as it was done over a distance by physical transportation such as the use of pigeons , boats and messengers .
In the most unfortunate cases , the information would not even reach the desired destination .
As a result , people wanted a form of communication which was fast and reliable .
This all changed dramatically with the introduction of the telephone .
Firstly , it took away the necessity of a transport medium which made it more reliable .
Secondly , the telephone used electricity which was literally accessible to every household and this provided messages to be passed around more quickly .
The society wanted to be able to communicate anywhere and anytime and to anyone they wished .
The introduction of the mobile phone allowed people in the society to have the ability to pass messages to one another quickly and accurately whenever they wished .
This meant that office workers were able to speed up communication and circulate information faster to allow new ideas to be conceived quickly .
Having to do this would result a great benefit to an individual 's company and finally , it would have a positive impact on the economy .
Furthermore , even the military benefited from this wireless telephony .
Through the use of wireless communication , soldiers were able to communicate with each other swiftly and with 100 % accuracy when information was passed around .
Due to the convenience of having a mobile phone , the number of mobile phone users increased drastically over the years .
By 2002 , Japan had 55 million mobile phone users ( out of 122 million ) , China had over 200 million mobile phone users ( out of 1.3 billion ) and about 90 % of Finland 's population had a mobile phone according to BBC in 2003 .
The mobile underwent further developments to enhance its features to suit its consumers .
As a result , by 2003 , the mobile phone was presented more than just a tool for calling someone .
It will also take on roles and an anchor point , a digital navigator and a lifestyle accessory that will help individuals control and enrich their lives ( Nokia , 2002 ) .
Looking back at the evolution of communication , the mobile phone is one that was shaped by social factors .
Recently , there was an outbreak of a pandemic flu which started in Mexico and was spreading rampantly around the world and instilled fear in people .
Experts had estimated that more than 2 billion worldwide will contact the flu ( Scheirer Micheal and Harrell Eben .
As such , the health ministers of various countries were very concerned .
Thus leading to the development of the vaccine for H1N1 Besides the governments , the H1N1 patient and the general public is also very concerned with the development of the vaccine of H1N1 .
The virus is very contagious thus leading to a rampant spread in the society .
Thus there is a large demand for the vaccine by the various government bodies .
This could be seen in the following , whereby the governments of France , Belgium and Finland intended to purchase 50 million , 12.6 million and 5.3 million doses , respectively ( Cormac Sheridan , 2009 ) .
Another reason the government bodies is concerned about the development of the new vaccine is the fear for mutation .
As experts have predicted that many more is going to contact the diseases , there is a higher the chance that the diseases will mutate into a stronger virus .
The health ministers around the world are influencing the development of the vaccine so as to cure the diseases before it spreads too widely or mutates .
The public and the H1N1 patients are the other group that shaped the development of the vaccine for H1N1 .
Although figures of the WHO have shown that out of the 160,000 cases only 1.200 have died , this could not contain the fear in people .
This is due t0 the previous outbreak of another flu virus which took many lives .
Due to the fear there is a high demand for the vaccine , as such the pharmaceutical companies are trying to seize this rare business opportunity .
Besides , the large demand , any new development would also bring about a rise in the respective pharmaceutical companies share price .
For example , in April 30 2009 when Lipoxen ( pharmaceutical companies ) announced positive preclinical results for the delivery of an enhanced influenza vaccine , adding that the technology should also work against the new swine flu strain , Lipoxen 's share price when up from Â£ 6.62 ( $ 10.11 ) to Â£ 21.75 ( $ 33.23 ) ( Brady Huggett , 2009 ) .
Both the health ministries of the world and the patient as well as the public have shaped the development of the H1N1 vaccine in various ways .
For the government , they needed the vaccine to help control the spread of H1N1 and also hope to cure the disease before it mutates into a more deadly virus .
As for the patients and the public their concerned is that they need the vaccine to stay away form the disease .
Many people have already got used to use cell phone to take pictures and transfer to their friends , so that they think that the camera phones are born like this .
However , camera phone changed a lot after coming out at 2000 ( Daisuke , 2003 ) , compared with the first camera phone , camera phones nowadays are quite different .
During the nine-year development of camera phone technology , we can see that the great market demand , customer requirement , and government regulations of different countries have once affected this technology a lot .
The first factor which accelerated the development of the camera phone is the great market demand .
Before the camera phone came out , the digital camera and videophone have existed for many years .
Actually , a camera phone is a combination of the digital camera and the videophone which can take pictures and save the picture in digital form freely at anywhere and anytime as a digital camera and transfer the pictures or videos to others as a videophone .
At that time , digital camera and videophone have already become a part of everyday life , people might really want a tool which can let people take pictures freely and transfer them wirelessly .
This kind of need of the combination of two technologies eventually bring out the camera phone .
Thus , at 2000 , Sharp launch the world first camera phone J-SH04 which has a 110,000-pixel CMOS image sensor for taking digital photos .
This innovation make sharp achieve a great success .
We can easily see that the great sales ensured the development of this technology .
More and more companies began to realize this great market demand and start researching in camera phones .
After integrating the image sensor into the mobile phone , the quality of the pictures taken by the camera phones which only have hundreds of thousands of pixel sensor can not satisfy the need of the consumers .
The pictures taken by the camera phone are very blurred at that time .
Those pictures can not be developed because of its low quality .
What might people need is actually a substitute of the digital camera .
This need greatly boost the camera phone technology development .
Most camera phone companies tried to produce the camera phone with better sensor .
Eventually in the year 2003 , Sharp launched the world first 1 megapixel camera phone ( Long , 2005 ) , which can provide much better quality pictures .
Since then , camera phone became a really useful tool instead of the novel technology .
Different companies also applied the same strategy and released their 1 megapixel camera phone at the same year which made the sales surge 200 % compared with last year .
From this , we can draw the conclusion that the customer requirement greatly shaped the camera phones technology .
Although the worries of sneak shot have existed since the camera phone came out , it has aroused wide concern during last few years as the increase number of such kind of incidents .
For example , on December 30 , 2006 , a short film of the execution of former Iraqi dictator Saddam Hussein leaked out on the internet which led to some serious detrimental effect .
The film was obvious taken by a camera phone .
Different countries also promulgated different regulations to limit the use of the camera phone .
Different companies also try to find new methods to prevent the sneak shot .
We can see that the market demand makes the camera phone come out , costumer requirement led to the improvement of the functions of a camera phone and government regulations also affected the usage of the camera phone .
All these factors make camera phone more and more adapt to our society and eventually bring a novel technology into our daily life .
Hawk-eye is a computer system used in cricket , tennis and other sports to visually track the path of the ball and display a record of its actual path as graphic image .
In tennis and cricket , Hawk-eye system has become an important reference for judgment and even the decision maker when dispute come on the scene .
When the Hawk-eye system was invented , it got prizes including Science and Technology Innovation Award presented by The Royal Television Society .
However , even for now , the popularization has not become widespread .
Hawk-eye 's development is limited due to its high cost , some errors it made and some opposing ideas from the public .
The first limit for the development of Hawk-eye is its high cost .
The above-mentioned equipments need to operate very fast , which needs the facilities to be of high quality .
Theses above reasons as well as the monopoly market of Hawk-eye together lead to the high cost to use Hawk-eye system .
In the 2009 snooker China open , the sponsor spent 400 thousands Yuan per week , which means almost 60 thousands US dollars per week .
( 2009,http : //sports.sina.com.cn/o/2009-04-08/03264312295.shtml ) Not many contest holders can afford to spend so much money on such referencing aids .
We can say that the high cost is a limit for the Hawk-eye to develop further .
The second limit is the shortcoming of Hawk-eye itself .
Although the Hawk-eye company declared that Hawk-eye is precise and accurate , Hawk-eye made a mistake accidentally .
In 2009 Indian Wells Tennis Masters , Hawk-eye system made a mistake in the quarter-final .
When Andrew Murray knocked the ball out of the bound , Hawk-eye did not recognize it and finally Murray beat Ivan Ljubicic and got in the semifinal .
We use Hawk-eye to prevent errors in judgment ; however , if it does not offer us the accuracy , we may not choose to use it .
The errors caused by Hawk-eye itself are sure to prevent the potential users from using it and thus , makes the development of Hawk-eye limited .
In addition , not all the Sportsmen value Hawk-eye system very much .
Even in tennis , one of the sports that Hawk-eye is the most widely used , some of the world 's most popular players still can not accept Hawk-eye system .
Roger Federer and Lindsay Davenport think that Hawk-eye system forgets the true meaning of tennis and makes tennis disinteresting .
As is widely known , those world-famous players have a great influence on the development of the sport .
If those players do not accept Hawk-eye system , it may be very difficult for Hawk-eye system to develop and spread out further .
In conclusion , the reasons why Hawk-eye system does not spread out and develop further are the high cost , the weakness of Hawk-eye system itself and the social opposing ideas from some influential world-famous players .
Since Iphone 's first introduction on June 29 , 2007 , it has become the best- selling smart phone in the world1 .
After a series of hardware and software development , we can now enjoy the latest 3GS Iphone with a lot of improvements , including Internet , 3G , music , video and photos .
In the Iphone 's development process , we can not deny that the user 's demand for new functions and user 's financial problem in economic crisis have a great influence in changing the Iphone .
First of all , users ' demand for the Iphone that has more features and utilities to combine everything in a phone forces Apple to continue developing Iphone .
Comparing to the 1st generation of Iphone , the latest one ( 3GS ) is very different .
At first , Iphone just only support EDGE network , 802.11b wireless standard , and 4GB internal storage .
Now the Iphone 3GS has supported 3G network , video call , 802.11n wireless standard , and up to 32GB internal storage .
To satisfy users ' demand for new applications , themes , software and utilities , on March 6 , 2008 , Apple finally released the Iphone SDK ( Apple , 2008 ) , the platform in which programmer can build and develop software from simple to very complicated .
The second factor that affects the Iphone is the user 's budget during economic crisis .
During the crisis , the sale of smart phone in general decreases because people do not want to spend money on unnecessary thing .
Worldwide sales of hi-tech " smartphones " grew at their slowest pace yet in the fourth quarter of 2008 as the financial crisis hit demand , a research firm said Thursday2 .
There is no way for Apple to encourage people buying their products except making them more valuable .
In 2009 summer , Apple introduces the new version of Iphone , the 3GS , with the same price as the older version .
The new one has higher speed core and bigger RAM , which lets Iphone runs faster and can even display High definition movie .
Apple also reduces the price of 3G version to make it reasonable and affordable to more users .
The result is " California-based Apple was the third-biggest player with iPhone sales of 11.42 million units , more than triple the 3.3 million sold when it launched the device in 2007 " .
After all , user 's financial problem in economic crisis and user 's demand for advanced technology have contributed to the development of Iphone through several years .
Iphone now can serve many purposes of users like entertainment , video conference .
Although Iphone is the best smart phone in the market at the moment , but it will have to be developed more and be offered at a lower price to satisfy the customers .
Both the military and civil demand for precise navigation promote the development of Global Positioning System
Nowadays , almost everybody knows GPS ( Global Positioning System ) which has made a significant difference in our daily life in ways ranging from guiding family hiking to airline navigation .
However , a lot of people may do not know that it is such a seemingly very new advanced technology that actually already have existed for more than forty years .
( Lowry , 2006 ) It is the military and civil demand for precise navigation stimulates the GPS technology advancing to what we know it as today .
After the WW , the US military realized the weakness of navigating by the stars and the radio signals and started to seek for a more precise positioning system to guide their fighters and warships globally .
( Lowry , 2006 ) In late nineteen fifties , the scientists in USA realized the possibility of accurate positioning by satellites and finally in 1960 , a satellite navigation system called Transit is tested in USA navy to meet their intense requirement for precise navigation to avoid unnecessary shipwreck .
Since then , in order to grasp the precise position information of its army all over the world , United States Department of Defense allotted millions of dollars in the GPS R&D which eventually resulted in a complete Global Positioning System with the operation of two dozen of polar orbiting satellites .
( Yogendra , 2002 )
Besides the military demand , the public appeal for a safe civil navigation also promotes the development of GPS .
In 1983 , a US civilian airliner KAL 007 was shot down by the Soviet Union air force by mistake when it lost its way and flied into the airspace of the Soviet Union without authorization , thus making the US civilians intensely blame the government for the ignorance of the safety of civil navigation .
In order to calm the mass and avoid such disasters in future , the then president Ronald Regan promised to apply GPS to civilian users as well as military once it was completed .
( Lawry , 2006 ) And due to the immense pressure of the public , the US government turned off the SA ( Selective Available ) in May 2000 , which maked GPS develop from a critically military supplied technology to a real dual-use system for both civilian and military use .
( Gibbon Media& Research LLC , 2007 )
The idea of GPS is firstly put forward in the nineteen forties .
Afterwards , both the military and public demand for precise navigation promote the further development of GPS and make it like what we see today -a precise dual-use global positioning system for both civilian and military .
Technology is the practical application of knowledge especially in a specific area .
This essay will compare and contrast the discovery of penicillin and the development of embryonic stem cells these two technologies , in terms of impetus to the invention , researchers involved in the innovation development and the effects on society .
The impetus to these technologies both comes from the needs of society .
For the development of embryonic stem cells , the main reason why it can develop rapidly during such a short period is that the society needs a new way to transplantation .
Similarly , because the society needed a new medicine to cure some diseases like pneumonia , penicillin was discovered .
The discovery of penicillin is by accident and after a long time it was being used as medicine .
Impetus to these technologies is society needs and differences can be seen from it .
However , there are slightly differences between these two technologies in terms of researchers involved .
For the technology that was developed via research , like the stem cells mentioned before , it has a tendency that it involved a large group of researchers and even researchers from different countries .
However , for the serendipitous discovery , it more seems involves a smaller group of people , sometimes even individual .
Researchers involved in these two kinds of technologies are almost the same with slightly differences between them .
Last but not least , their effects on the society also have similarities and differences .
Both are promoting social development and people received lot of benefits .
If doctors use organs which are obtained by stem cells , many technical problems can be solved , like rejection reaction and the shortage problem .
The differences lie in the time of how long it will be widely used by the majority of people .
The technology developed via research will use shorter time to be accepted by the majority of people while technology developed via serendipitous discovery may be rejected by people when it was first invited .
There are similarities and differences between technologies developed via research and via serendipitous discovery in the aspect of impetus to the invention , researchers involved in the innovation development and the effects on society .
In the future , more and more useful technologies will be developed and they can give us a lot of benefits .
The world has become much more richer and more complete with inventions or innovations .
Putting these ideas into actions and facing obstacles that come along with way leads to technological innovation .
During this process , technological innovation was affected by economical and social factors which contributed in shaping the innovation .
One of the many innovations that how made our lives convenient is " Refrigeration " .
This was a technology that had been shaped by the society in the past who were desperate to preserve their food .
Ice from mountains or snowy areas were transported to warmer regions where it was wrapped in cloth and placed in cellas .
Soon ice box , which was made up of a metal linked box insulated with cork or snow dust with one compartment to put the ice and another to store the perishables .
The civil ware in US interrupted the ice trade .
The idea of refrigeration was built based on the principle that when a liquid changes to a gas , it absorbs heat as it expands in a self contained cycle , the air or other fluid surrounding the device can be reduced in temperature .
With this principle , soon the gas refrigerator and the electric refrigerator was built to carry out the ideas of regrigeration .
Gas refrigerators used ammonia or the compression refrigerant and a water jacket or the heart absorbed that could be circulated to the area to be cooled .
The gas refrigerator did not compromise of any moving parts and therefore it would not spoil or beak down easily .
Electric refrigerators used an electric motor to pump the coolant or the refrigerant around the enclosed system .
Unlike the gas refrigerators , the electric refrigerators were noisy and a disruption in the supply of electricity would mean that the refrigerator would strop working .
When the gas refrigerations developed a leak , the gas was irritating and slightly corrosive .
Since the gases used in a gas refrigerators were usually poisonous and flammable , people were not very favourable of such gases running through their houses in large quantities .
Therefore social factors , interms of safety concern , over ruled the advantages of gas refrigerators and made the situation favourable for electric refrigators .
Economic factor also contributed to the success of electric refrigerators .
Since it was believed that greater economic profits could be gained from electric refrigerators as compared to gas refrigerators , large firms started investing huge amount of research ad development ( R&D ) funding into the electric refrigerators as well as promoted the product aggressively .
Therefore small firms producing gas refrigerators could not compete with the strong competition and with insufficient resources for R & D , further developments to the refrigerator was not possible and it was also difficult to keep the prices of gas refrigerators were forced to go out of sales and the sales of electric refrigerator continued booming .
Therefore , economic profit grained from the product also affects the technological innovation .
In conclusion , the path of a technological inno0vation has been shaped by many factors .
In the case of refrigeration , gas refrigeration was invented first but due to corporate profitably , R &D fundings were provided to the electric refrigerations and hen it was further developed to meet the various demands of the people and brought into use widely around the world .
The production of gas refrigerations on the other hand were forced to close down due to lack of R & D funding .
The safety was also a main concern in this technological innovation .
As the gases used in the gas refrigerator were not safe , it was not preferred by the consumers .
Therefore , factors such as safety concern and corporate profitability have played a part in shaping the technological innovation , refrigeration .
The length of tank 's history is almost one hundred year since 1916 when the first time tank was used as a secret weapon of British .
If we trace back further , we can find that Leonardo de Vinci already drew a similar picture of tank in 15th century .
Although we are not sure what kind of materials and technologies Vinci was trying to use when constructing his " tank " , we are still astonished by his ingenious imagination .
However , tank is not a usual vehicle for the majority .
Most people never have a chance to drive a tank , but it seems that many people are very familiar with and interested in it .
Tank is tightly related to war since the first day it was born .
Inevitably , government and military demand play vital important roles in its developing history .
In World War I ( WWI ) , when the Triple Entente and the Triple Alliance were fighting against each other bloodily , they both got into trouble with the trench warfare .
The British government was very worried about this condition .
After a while , British government not only took his advice but also organized a professional group to design and produce the tank .
After tank was invented , since the technologies used in tank and common vehicle are quite same , the vehicle industry quickly became the pillar industry of many industrialized countries .
It provided tremendous job opportunities as well as markets .
However , after two more decades of peace since WWI , the leader of Nazi Party in German , Hitler , became very enthusiastic about mass production of automobile , because he wanted to use the technology to produce more tanks for World War II ( WWII ) .
( Because of the Treaty of Versaillers , Germany was not allowed to have tanks .
) In 1933 , Hitler met Ferdinan Porsche , the founder of the Porsche , and talked about " Volkswagen " .
Because of the government investment into the research , in 1936 , this new kind of cheap automobile called " beetle " was born .
After the WWII , the development of tanks has never stopped .
The most common type is main battle tank ( MBT ) .
Compared with the original tank , modern tank has navigation system , infrared night-vision scope , composite armor , etc .
It seems that all the powerful countries are involved in this technology competition .
Russia has T-72 .
The U.S. has M1A1 .
However , no matter how well they develop their tank , casualty is evitable in the war .
Maybe more people will die in the war after new tanks are introduced .
In conclusion , tank is a great engineering-design product which government , global politics and military industry shape it together .
It is a " weapon of mass destruction " but still ingenious .
Its quick development and adaptability in battle field is incomparable .
It is the main role in land battle in modern war .
The success of a technology not only depends on how well it resolves the targeted need but also the social considerations it incurs when introduced to the consumer market .
Based on " The network of power " , a book by Thomas Hughes , it addresses one pertinent problem on the way we view technology .
The associated issue is that we tend to be blinded by the benefits of a technology and oversee the importance of understanding it as an entire system .
By looking at the development of automobiles , from electric vehicles to gasoline-powered cars , we are able to understand how economic factors influence oil magnates , car manufacturers and the government who ultimately shaped this technological innovation .
With the rise of an alternate fuel source , not only would oil companies suffer a loss in profits , the possibility of getting put out of business increases significantly as well .
They even resort to underhand means like spreading false information about the new technology .
For instance , doubts were cast in the ability of batteries delivering 100km per charge .
Even if there is a more environmental friendly fuel , they would suppress it at all cost .
Car manufacturers are the next immediate culprit culpable for the continued devlopment of gasoline-powered vehicles rather than focusing on the environmental friendly electric car .
They know that their core group of customers , us , are a bunch of non-risk takers who are still uncertain about the new technology .
From a consumer point of view , it is not value for money .
The road users would not pay more for an underpowered vehicle let alone sacrifice more money to be environment friendly .
Furthermore , carmakers tried to promote cars using hydrogen technology which still requires years of development as claimed by experts .
This smokescreen failed to hide the truth that they just can not afford to lose the customers .
Government is another deciding factor in shaping the automobile technology .
For example , in 1998 the Carlifornia Air Resource Board mandated that any car companies capable of producing electric cars must ensure that 2 percent of their sales are emission-free cars .
However , despite 5000 electric cars were manufactured , 4000 were scraped after major car dealers pressured to cancel the mandate .
In other words , the governemnt take into account of the collapse of the automobile and oil industry and the consequences that will ensue , such as loss of jobs , increase in unemployment .
To sum up , oil companies , car manufacturers and the government considered issues from the economic view and realised that the consequences of making electric car a success are too drastic .
The oil and auto industry are too lucrative and at the same time crucial to the overall economy such that issues regarding pollution and environment are secondary to it .
Hence , the automobile technology is ultimately shaped by oil magnates , car companies and the government who are largely influenced by economic factors .
The two problems are attitude and funding which have severe impact on the local engineering process for innovations .
The engineering design process for innovations can be broken down into 3 stages , firstly creativity , secondly process and lastly materialization .
The two problems will be elaborated on how it impacts the engineering process for innovations .
This could be made due to personal and the society 's attitude .
We shall begin with the individual attitude and how it hampers the local engineering process for innovations .
Singaporeans tends to have an asian mentality which is prudence and stability .
Being prudent , Singaporeans tends to be less adventurous compared to their western counterparts .
One common scenario would be , parents who advice their children especially those with tertiary education to get a decent job and contribute to the family 's expenditure .
If their children , wants to go into the research and development profession example being a researcher in a university or students joining their local science competition that will not add to distinctions in the exams they will be advice against .
This will cause children who later grow into adults not to utilize their creativity the first step to engineering design process .
The second part would be the society 's attitude seeks to hamper the engineering process for innovations , an example would be Paddy Tan the creator who came up with a unique service can BAK2U a software that allows owners who lose their mobile phones to track down their lost mobile phone .
When he initially launch his software the response was lukewarm .
He had to bring his product overseas and made a break through before his product became recognize .
The local society does not have a positive attitude in accepting new engineering innovations this could affect the materialization stage of the engineering process for innovation .
If there is no one wants to accept a new creative product , it will be hard for it to exist in the market and will also deter people to participate in the engineering design process for innovations .
A good example is the formula racing car of National University Of Singapore ( NUS ) , the initial stages required the professors and his students to each come up with three hundred dollars to purchase the necessary parts .
However not all inventors had the luck of achieving initial success and thus receive funding .
Failure to secure funding will turn away inventors with engineering flare from even brainstorming for ideas affect creativity , in the process of coming up with innovations no funding seeks to terminate the inventors progress and with no funding its not possible to publicize about an engineering innovation .
, Serendipity is the accidental discovery of a new idea , and the 3M post-it pad is one example .
On 4 July 2009 ; The Straits Times reported the development of a new product , the Haptic Chair , by researchers from the National University of Singapore ( NUS ) to help the deaf experience sound .
For serendipity and research , the resources invested and how they are considered to be successful are different , but technologies of both nature bring benefit to the lives of people .
A case of serendipity occurred a few decades back when researchers from 3M laboratories discovered a new bonding agent .
Next , he distributed pads of the post-it notes to 3M 's president executive secretary , who also found them useful .
Eventually , the post-it pads were further distributed to different companies , leading up to its big marketing success today .
( Rogers , 2003 )
The product is made with the understanding that sound waves , apart from travelling through air , can also travel through solid matter .
( Grace , 2009 )
The difference between a serendipitous discovery and a researched technology are the resources invested in the development , and how the technology is gauged to be a success .
A serendipitous discovery happens by chance , and has no pre-allocated funds or project timeframe to be adhered to .
The post-it pads came about because the 3M researcher happened to have non-permanent adhesive , and he decided to come out with the new product on his own .
Before he gave the post-it pads to others , no funds or expertise were assigned to him for the post-its development .
In the case of The Haptic Chair , a team of researchers worked together with Suranga Nanayakkara , who also had the support of several working staff from the University .
A lot of time and effort has been put in by the team before they could actually come out with the product .
The post-it pads were only found to be successful after it was given to the 3M president 's executive secretary who found them useful and mass-distributed it to various companies .
It required the general public to see the item as something useful before it was deemed to be successful .
In The Straits Times article , it was reported that partially deaf musicians like teen piano prodigy Azariah Tan found various aspects of the invention intriguing .
( Rogers , 2003 , Grace , 2009 )
For the 3M researcher , he identified the need to stick notes on paper without leaving adhesive stains to damage original documents ; for the NUS student , he identified the need to create a product to aid those with hearing problems .
Both technologies benefit the lives of people , and have potential for profit .
In conclusion , we have come to learn that new technologies can come not just by research , but by serendipitous discoveries as well .
What we do need to bear in mind is this : technologies of both natures serve different groups of people in different scales , but they ultimately bring benefit to the lives of people .
Innovation starts when there is a need or when someone faces a problem and motivates people to find a way to solve it by generating new ideas .
As we need an equipment to solve problems .
Many technological innovations were formed by scientific research or by the interaction of scientific investigations and applied on practical needs and problems .
A new idea is created through results from rigorous process of research .
Others were serendipitously invented .
Serendipity means unexpected discovery of new ideas when finding something which is unrelated or in the process of researching in new inventions .
These findings are often unpredictable and uncertain .
Serendipitous discovery can happen to anyone as well as in many fields .
This stimulates development and research to create something in order to solve the problem or need .
For example General Motor 's electric car .
Besides that , GM wishes to reposition itself as an innovative company to the public .
These are the two factors that drive them to initiate the research and develop the electric car .
A farmer asked him to find out the cause of death of his cow which is caused by sweet clover disease .
He found out that an anticoagulation agent called coumarin is the cause of death of his cow when the hay stem punctured the cow 's stomach .
Years later he experimented it as a rat killer , and found out it is a very effective rodenticide .
The main contrast between technology created via research and technology created serendipitously is the former one has a clear direction of what they are inventing and the latter is created while in the process of researching or inventing something which is totally unrelated .
With the use of the findings through basic research and investigations , they are able to discover and create methods and develop a new tool to solve problems .
However , the latter does not have a specific objective , the discovery is purely unpredicted .
In conclusion , innovation occurs anywhere and anytime .
Through constant exchange of information about the problems , human needs and wants , we can come up with better ideas to solve problems and make our world a better place to live in .
Rogers ( 2003 ) defines that technology as a design for instrumental action that reduces the uncertainty in the cause-effect relationships involved in achieving a desired outcome .
However , some unpredicted technologies were invented by accident or serendipity .
The stove and microwave oven both are similarly used to cook our daily meal at home but they were discovered in two different ways .
Recognizing a problem or needs , basic and applied research and development are the 3 stages of the innovation-development processes , and we will use these stages to compare and contrast the two different technologies .
In the past , people started to use fire , coal , or heat from the sun to cook .
Stove was invented because people need to cook , which applied heat to prepare the food .
Dr. Percy Spencer discovered the microwave technology by serendipity when he found out that his candy bar in his pouch was melted when he was experimenting with his new magnetron .
The history of the stove and microwave shows that serendipity and researched technology came from a very different beginning .
Serendipity came from a branch of a problem or need , while research technology came straight from the problem or needs .
Subsequently , the technology needs to be further research on the basic application .
Stove has undergone a very long history and it has been tested and improved over the centuries .
Similarly , the microwave oven , although this technology is not needed or a purpose to begin with , but the research and basic application of the microwave oven is progressively improvise from the same technology as the microwave radio signal radar .
Thus we can see that both the technologies refer back to the previous basic and applications for further research .
Next , when the basic and application research of the technology has established , the development of the product will begin .
The first known stove was built on the ground with sticks foaming a tripod to hold the cooking pot above the heat source .
Today , it has become very compact and light , and features like the automatic functions to allow user to cook with just pressing a button .
In conclusion , we had compare and contrast the serendipitous and research technology using these three different stages of innovation-development process .
The results shows that both technologies was invented in two very different way ; research technology is a product created via recognition of problems and need , while serendipitous technology is discovered by pure accident and has no purpose at the beginning .
However , the two technologies are similar in these two stages after recognizing a problem or need : - further research on basic and application , and development stages .
It can be sub-divided into two categories : developed through research , the example being Bionic eyes or serendipitous discovery , the example being 3M 's Post-its .
Between the two categories , there are similarities such as achieving the aim of improving quality of life and numerous trials needed to be done before it is successful as well as differences like how this technology came about and the acceptance of the technology by other people .
One similarity between both categories is achieving the aim of improving quality of life for the people .
For Bionic eyes , it is developed as engineers are thinking of ways to improve visual displays in various fields such as gaming and in the aviation industry .
They hope to develop lenses such that they will allow players to be entirely immersed in the game allowing them to move without any constraints .
For the aviation industry , it is hope that through the new technology , pilots are able to know the speed of the plane almost immediately .
As for 3M 's Post-its , it comes in very handy when people want to remind themselves of events or when commenting on essays without having the need to write in the essay itself .
It is convenient to use as it can stick to almost any surfaces and also easy to peel off without leaving any marks .
In addition , both technologies have gone through numerous trials before it becomes what it is now .
In the case of Bionic eyes , the challenge was to choose materials that are harmless when used safe in the body and how to put circuit boards in contact lenses which are so tiny in size .
They also had to consider how to create the slim layer of circuit boards so that it can be placed in the contact lenses .
As for Post-its , it was initially to find a bonding agent that allows paper to bond but along the way , another type of bonding agent was discovered which was deemed as useless at first since it did not achieve its original aim .
One of the differences was how this technology came about .
For Bionic eyes , it was done via research after seeing it in a movie called 'Terminator ' , where a woman is able to zoom on places that are far away .
This gave the engineers the idea of whether what they see in the movie is able to become a reality .
As for Post-its , it was discovered accidentally by researches who were trying to find bonding agents that can be used to bind papers firmly to a surface .
It was a by-product of what they are trying to achieve .
It was once deemed as " worthless " until people found uses for it and it become one of the most commonly used product in our daily life and one of the products that makes the most revenue for 3M .
For Bionic eyes , it is easier for the public to accept it as this was done with the aim of developing lenses that will help improve quality of life .
In this sense , it will also be an easier task to find people to help market this product .
In the case of Post-its , it was initially being seen as a 'failure product ' since it did not achieve the aim of developing a bonding agent that will allow papers to be tightly bonded to the surface .
It is only accepted and marketed by the company after sending samples out to each Fortune 500 companies for them to test the product and received good feedbacks on the product .
If not , it may have just been abandoned and 3M may not be making such huge revenue each year .
In conclusion , both technologies , be it developed via research or resulted from a serendipitous discovery , it has achieved the aim of improving the lives of people .
Though initial acceptance to the two technologies was different and it all depends on the mindset of the public whether the technology being discovered is worth marketing or not as seen from the case of 3M Post-its .
One of the earliest inventions brought about by mankind was the wheel , ever since then we have never looked-back .
Over the past half decade , a new term " skunkworks " has surfaced .
This term describes the environment where small groups of researchers are not bound by corporate rules and politics .
There are several similarities and differences between the technologies generated by the " skunkworks " environment as compared to conventionally generated technologies .
Products generated by each environment may appear similar but actually differ in many ways and the environment plays an important part in shaping its distinctive features .
The first similarity that conventionally generated technologies and " skunkworks " environment generated technologies share is the ability to produce cutting-edge technology .
Take for example , the IMPACT car developed by General Motors ( GM ) and the Toshiba laptop .
The IMPACT car was conventionally generated by GM was set to change the fate of automobiles .
The second similarity is that in both environments , generally large amount of money and support has to be put in by the head company .
Hence long hours are required before any results are visible .
A few examples include , GM developing the first electric car named IMPACT , Apple developing their first Macintosh computer and Xerox 's attempt at developing the world 's first personal computer .
It is thus evident that huge amount of financing and support is generally required in both environments .
However , things do not always go as described in the above paragraph .
There are instances where " skunkworks " environments have little financing and support from the head company .
As a result , the Toshiba laptop has very little marketing as compared to the IMPACT car by GM .
This has resulted in very different products developed by each environment .
The " skunkworks " environment has been able to provide the developers the flexibility and freedom required to break traditional barriers and develop cutting-edge technologies .
Furthermore , " skunkworks " environment is very stressful as compared to the traditional corporate environment due to the lack of financing and hence room for error becomes much smaller .
The last and perhaps the most significant difference in the environments have to be the difference in the features of technologies developed by each environment .
An example of such a difference is again present between the IMPACT car and the Toshiba laptop .
Under the stressful skunkworks environment , the researchers from Toshiba are able to think critically and design the product to fit the needs of the society .
On the other hand , the researchers from GM have failed to realize that the public and society was not ready for their invention .
In conclusion , it is clear that the technology churned out by a " skunkworks " environment differ greatly to that of a conventionally generated technology .
The features and characteristics of the " skunkworks " technology set them apart from conventionally generated technology .
An innovation may come from different ways .
The idea of such an innovation can emerge though some research or it may be from some serendipitous discovery .
On one hand , one technology may be developed and polished through numerous research and experiment with a lot of effort .
On the other hand , some technology may be discovered purely by chance .
Two typical representatives are the electric cars and the Warfarin .
The electric car is invented by some hardworking engineers , while Warfarin is discovered serendipitously .
Although they are initialized differently , there are several similar stages of developing process .
Generally , one technology that is developed through research often begins with the need for practical uses or recognition of a social problem .
The electrical car is not an exception .
As the situation of the earth environment becomes worse , and the energy resources are exhausting , the need for inventing nonpolluting and energy- saving cars is urgent .
Some government encourages automobile companies to produce environmentally friendly cars .
Engineers ' motivation to design electric cars is obvious .
Nobody knew that the chemical in spoiled sweet clover key that led to cattle hemorrhage could actually be used as rat poison until the scientist Link accidentally found it .
Even he himself was surprised when he found this chemical was highly lethal to rats .
Despite the huge difference exists in identifying and initializing the innovations developed through research and via serendipitous discovery , there are similarities in some aspects throughout the process of development .
Serendipitous discoveries can not be put into use straight away .
Innovations and technologies are for the public use , and without the confirmation from lab work and data , they are not completed .
Besides the same basic applied research , technologies develop via research and from serendipitous discovery are similar in the way they benefit the society .
Both technologies are globally adopted by public , and bring benefit to the whole society .
To sum up , technologies developed via research and from serendipitous discovery are quite differently initialized .
However , they are similar in the sense that they have to undergo the same process of experiments and research , and both can be very successful and bring benefit to the whole society .
During the process of developing innovations , regarding every little detail seriously and never letting go any chance discovery are most important .
There are numerous problems faced by the world today .
Governments of different countries may have different agenda list , however aging population is definitely an issue present in the list .
Engineers play a huge role in assisting the government in achieving the aim of creating a better and safer environment for the elderly to live in .
With a safer environment , the welfare of the elderly will be improved and less social problems will be resulted .
Examples of such engineering design are the building of ramps at the main entrance of the flats , building handrails at the side of the stairs and also the wheelchair bound bus .
For example , the Housing Development Board ( HDB ) had implemented several designs to improve the convenience of the elderly , such as installing lifts on every storey and build wider internal corridors and hallways .
The designs had been proven useful by the flat holders who lived in the flat with all these facilities when the HDB first implemented them .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , after each solution is generated , it must be tested and implement to see the effects brought by the solution .
In this case , there is positive effects associated to the engineering designs made to the HDB flats , thus the government had implemented the solution throughout Singapore .
Many different countries had come out with many different innovative designs to facilitate the objective .
One such design is the wheelchair bound bus , whereby Singapore SMRT Corporation Ltd ( SMRT ) had provides bus with such service on the road .
This wheelchair bound bus is first implemented in the European countries , and people from other countries find that the design is not only innovative , it is also a very thoughtful design , in the sense that it benefits the elderly and also the handicap .
There is a engineering design process that is mentioned by Khandani ( 2005 ) that when engineers are thinking of the solution to the problem , they should actually research on more information on the relevant issue and observe how the others approach the problem .
Hence , in this case , SMRT observed the good response from the other countries that implemented this form of transport , and decided to try out the transport in Singapore .
Generally , the engineering design process consists mainly of the five procedures mentioned by Khandani ( 2005 ) which includes defining the problem , gathering the relevant information , think of solutions to the problem , analyze and select one solution , and test it out by implementing it .
Although all the steps mentioned by Khandani ( 2005 ) is crucial for designing a good engineering product , the most important step is to test out the solution and see how is the public response to it .
This is because every engineering product is designed to serve the people so as to bring a greater convenience to their life .
As a conclusion , engineering design is a never ending process , and it is the duty of the engineers to keep on coming up with solution to solve the pressing issue of creating better product for the aging population .
Increasing number of death rate due to traffic accidents have become a major problem in many countries .
The World Health Organisation ( WHO ) states that traffic accidents are in the ninth position among the reasons which leads to death .
When considering European Union , 1.3 million road traffic accidents occur each year , resulting in 1.7 million injuries and over 40000 death annually ( Ref : International Journal of Health Geographic ) .
Another alarming fact is that , even Singapore which implements strong traffic laws and regulations is also affected by this traffic accident problem .
The accident rate per 10,000 vehicles has increased from 2.34 in 2006 to 2.60 in 2007 in Singapore ( Ref : Singapore Police Force : { http : //www.spf.gov.sg } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.spf.gov.sg ] ) .
The most important three features in the engineering design process will cater to the need to form a new traffic system .
Firstly , the first feature in the design process is the identification of the problem and to gather pertinent information .
This step will allow us to identify the reasons for the traffic accidents problem in different angles .
It will help us to pick the problems found in the current system by doing various studies of the current traffic system .
The studies of the current system include the gathering of relevant information which will be useful for us to analyse the situation .
For example , doing traffic counts , area-wide surveys , parking surveys , identify speeding rates of vehicles , analysing the queue length and the junction delays could be part of the studies to get a better understanding of the problem .
For instance , the times of India states that there was a survey taken in India regarding the percentage of vehicles in the road and the percentage of people taking public transports ( Ref : { http : //timesofindia.indiatimes.com } [ HYPERLINK : http : //timesofindia.indiatimes.com ] ) and this survey has really helped them understand which cities have high rate traffic jams and the reason for them .
Secondly , the second important feature is the idea generation process .
This is a very important process as it is the point where we will be able to come out with solutions to the problems .
In the process , we will be able to analyse the statistics/surveys we have obtained and generate new ideas to solve the problem .
These solutions may include device to identify those speeding at turns and install sensors to make sure that there is sufficient spacing between vehicles .
Netherland was the first country to implement such road safety devices and it proves that these solutions really help as their road accident rates dropped by 25 % in 2000 when compared with accident rates in 1985 ( Ref : { www.ictct.org/dlObject.php ? document_nr = 217&/Kraay.pdf } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.ictct.org/dlObject.php ? document_nr = 217&/Kraay.pdf ] ) .
From this we can understand that it is essential to come out with a system which is useful in various ways .
So it is important to come out with ideas which will be a useful and economic solution to the problem .
It is the point where we will be selecting the solution which best suits the current situation and perfectly fits to the road of the country .
To conclude , it is very clear that engineering design process will be a useful method in solving the current human problem which is the traffic problem .
The three important features mentioned , problem identification part , analysing part and selecting the best solution , are the key features of the design process which will be really useful in solving the problem .
In the world currently , there are many pressing issues that need to be addressed by human beings .
They consist of problems like global warming and an aging population .
Solving these problems are human needs that we need to do as soon as possible .
The human need for better health care that should be the given the priority above the rest since it will affect us directly and its effects are much more immediate .
Hence , many health care products have been created and modelled by engineers to meet this need .
First and foremost , in recent years , we had two virus attacks that affected us badly , namely the Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome ( SARS ) and the Influenza A ( H1N1 ) virus .
Since these viruses are very contagious and their victims have a common symptom , fever .
The engineers had to come out with new thermometers that can help to contain the spread .
In the process of developing them , engineers can follow the engineering design processes described in Khandani ( 2005 ) .
Firstly , by understanding what they need , described as " designing the problem " , engineers will know that the new thermometer has to minimise contact between users to prevent spreading of the virus .
Other than that , engineers will also need to go through the process of " analysing and selecting a solution " to make sure that the new product is fairly accurate and it will not cause any health problem to the user before releasing it to the market .
As a result , the ear thermometer was introduced which is safe and fast .
It also minimises contact by using a plastic cover on the detector that will be disposed after use .
From the original design that requires manual operation by turning the wheels with hands to the wheelchair that can be moved with a single button , the wheelchair has undergone many changes .
Every change is made possible not by chance , but by following a set of engineering design process like the set mentioned in Khandani ( 2005 ) .
After the first wheelchair is made , it has benefitted many people .
However , engineers are not satisfied because they felt that it can be still improved after looking at how the users used it .
They started the process of creating an automated wheelchair by starting with " defining the problem " , that some users do not have enough strength to push the wheelchair .
After that , engineers have to " gather pertinent information " to make sure that this problem is real by doing a survey on the users so that they will not waste time designing something that the market does not need .
And when they have ideas how to solve this problem , they need to ensure they select the idea that is achievable with the current technology by " analysing the solutions " .
Some wheelchair users will try it out and give comments on it to find out if it has met criteria like user-friendliness before it is released into the market .
In conclusion , the two examples we mentioned have shown that engineering processes can play a big part in the designing phrase of a product , like how they make the thermometers safer and the wheelchair better for us .
Specifically , in the operating system ( OS ) market , there are two well-known examples , the Mac OS developed by Apple and the free open-source Linux OS .
These two OS reflect the obvious difference between the two ways of developing technology in their hardware platform , interface and price .
Meanwhile , Linux , coded in the skunkwork environment , does not have that much funds and ability to compare with Mac at that perspective .
The second difference between Mac and Linux lies in their structure .
Mac users , on the other hand , are restricted from the entering system files .
This makes the Linux OS more preferable among computer programmers and others who work in the field of information technology .
It is agreed by programmers from largest IT corporations such as IBM and Sun Microsystems that Linux is so far the most suitable environment for high-performance computing .
Despite their different structures and platform , the two operating systems are quite secured .
Being a skunkwork project , Linux sure has the advantage of price .
Its high requirement of computing knowledge makes Linux not popular among average computer users .
Mac , on the opposite , was designed for an entertainment and easy-to-use purpose .
Apple is also very efficient at advertising their product worldwide , so even when Mac and its software are much more expensive than for a normal OS , it is still one of the most wanted .
Furthermore , with the forth coming price drop , Mac is expected to be the operating system of choice for education and business .
However , research shows that the world is fast approaches two billion cars ( Sperling & Gordon , 2009 ) , and this poses a problem in the form of environmental pollution as well as causing adverse effects of our economy .
According to Nieuwenhuis and Wells ( 1994 ) , " In the early 1900s , when gasoline cars starting gaining popularity , resources like gasoline and steel could still be found in abundance " ( p.53 ) .
Every time a car is driven on the road , it is actually draining the world 's conventional petroleum resources , and contributes more to global warming .
Hybrid cars solve part of these problems by using more reusable material like plastic , as well as making them lighter and rely more on electricity to reduce fuel consumption and carbon emissions ( Berman , 2006 ) .
With the depletion of natural resources , funds have to be diverted into researching a cheaper alternative to gasoline as a fuel .
While the damage done by our continued reliance on cars and gasoline is severe , it is still not too late to do anything about it .
Comparing Tamiflu with Penicillin , although they work differently on different micro-organisms , both of them do benefit to the human population .
Most species of bacteria have a rigid cell wall , which prevents them from bursting when they are placed in solutions of low salt concentration as compared to the cell .
However , the viruses do not have cell walls and thus Penicillin has no effect on them .
With Tamiflu , which is also known as neuraminidase inhibitors , neuraminidase is inhibited and thus the virus is unable to exit the host cell and dies ( Roche , 2006 ) .
Due to the distinct difference in the structures of virus and bacteria , Tamiflu and Penicillin perform differently on them .
Penicillin benefits greatly as it has the ability to cure people suffering from once-fatal bacterial diseases .
Similarly , Tamiflu is also proven to be effective in the treatment and for the prevention of influenza in adults and in children .
Regardless of whether the technology is developed via research or discovered serendipitously , they have significant contributions to mankind .
For instance , there is always a need for new and better anti-flu drugs as virus gets mutated very easily and will soon acquire resistance to Tamiflu .
Who knows , may be in a few years time , the real cure for influenza virus will be discovered serendipitously and till that day , influenza virus will no longer be a threat to us .
It would be most appropriate to explain this phenomenon from comparing the key features of the two different types .
In contrast , the Sony VAIO AR , a laptop for Sony that is created in a conventional environment , has a battery life of 2.5 hours only hence it is not as popular as the Macbook Pro .
However , in a conventional environment , there were restrictions and standard procedures to follow closely .
In fact , this technology was accepted by cement industries and environmentalists CITATION Alo09 \ l 1033 ( Jha , ECO Worldly , 2009 ) .This clearly illustrates that a well researched technology gathers more support as it is perceived that a technology that has solid proof ( via experimentations and research ) have lesser unexpected outcomes in future , compared to a serendipitously discovered invention .
The interesting fact is that this project is funded by the government-backed Technology Strategy Board .
In my opinion , serendipitously discovered technology faces problem when it comes to gathering support and marketing while a well researched technology faces problem during the research and development stage .
The online video sharing website , Youtube , for example managed to grasp this concept and gained immense popularity within six months , hitting a peak 4000 from 200 daily page views per million in May ( Anderson , 2006 ) .
The website is developed to integrate Macromedia flash player software tool that enable internet users to view youtube videos from their web browsers directly , without having to download it to their computers and view it with secondary video playing programs such as window media player ( Sandra , n.d. ) .
Thus , the time and computer hardware space needed to view a video is effectively being shortened to provide greater convenience .
This convenience and ease of use , appeals to many internet users whom do not have very fast and stable internet connections by allowing them to watch their videos online as it downloads .
Since anyone can upload any video on to Youtube and allow anyone on Youtube to view it , many uploaded videos containing inappropriate content were easily accessible to minors .
The exclusive right granted to its original author to be credited for his work is valued to the extend it became a law in many society .
However , A huge amount of videos posted online consisting of television shows , music videos , movies and animes that were without the permission of their creators .
Subsequently , this forced Youtube to introduce its " Video ID " system which will check uploaded videos with a database of copyrighted material and denial any uploading if it finds a match ( Youtube , 2009 ) .
It is also intensively consumer focused and very flexible , able to adapting to the needs and demands of internet users quickly .
In addition , regular novel upgrades to its website continue to entice more webs surfers as well as generating more internet traffic to their website .
In this essay , we will discuss an innovation of a Bluetooth communication system for cyclists and one of the problems that the Bluetooth innovation faces and the impacts the problem has on certain stages of the process .
This Bluetooth communication system ( bike bug ) encounters the challenge of a lack of market demand which affects its likelihood of the commercialization process occurring which is being launch into the market .
Although , the number of cyclists who ride in large groups has risen over the years , number of official members of " joyriders " stand at 120 in May 2007 ( JoyRiders , 2006 ) , compared to Singapore population of 4.84 million people in June 2008 ( Singapore Government , 1871 ) , the number of cyclists that cycle in groups are insignificant .
Therefore , this indicates that the demand is low as cyclists who travel alone , in pairs , or in small groups and those people who do not cycle do not require and have the need for bike bug .
The structure of the bike bug 's earpiece does not look capable of fitting snuggly to the cyclist 's ear .
Third , it is the bike bug level of acceptance to consumers .
Even though 33 million of Bluetooth headsets were shipped in 2005 and the figure is expected to increase to over 55 million in 2006 ( Bluetooth special interest group , 2006 ) , compared to the world population of 6,808,515,373 people ( Geohive , 2009 ) , people who use Bluetooth headsets are considered the minority .
Hence , as bike bug is a Bluetooth headset gadget , I predict a not so bright future for its sales record .
With this two sub-factors plus the slow acceptance of Bluetooth headset compared to other Bluetooth devices , potential manufacturers of bike bug is deterred as it is not economic practical to mass produce bike bug .
It is therefore shown that for bike bug to be successfully launch into society , much is needed to raise bike bug popularity among the public .
One difference is on the problems the invention was being considered the past .
Being one of the manufacturers who wanted to outwit IBM , the inventors of Compaq pondered how to develop laptops computers that were faster , being superior in qualities , and offered additional features to please consumers .
For this case , Compaq was in the mainstream of developing portable computers , but exceeding what IBM had for offering to consumers with just an awesome BIOS System .
When Tetsuya Mizoguchi , the inventor of Toshiba laptop computer envisioned developing a product which was compatible to an IBM system , he was obstructed by the fact that corporate leaders at Toshiba deemed the development of such a product were difficult ( Rogers , 2003 ) .
Moreover , the company back then suffered huge losses in marketing their personal computers .
18 engineers examined IBM 's BIOS system and figured the development their own by reverse engineering .
