According to jobstreet.com , a statistics report done by 3.5 million members in terms of the numbers of years working experiences in the engineering world shows that the longer the experiences , the higher the qualification , the higher will be the monthly wages .
As the ageing-population in Singapore over the couples of decades will increase tremendously , as well as only 40-45 % of graduates in ITEs , Polytechnics and Universities are trained in some form of engineering ( said by Patrick ( p.8 ) ) , organizations in Singapore , in order to proceed with their innovations , they have no choice but to turn their way to the more senior and experienced engineers .
