Engineering design process is usually a cyclic process where decisions making are required .
Often , engineering sciences , basic sciences and mathematics are applied to convert the information available optimally to achieve the desired deeds .
Basically , this process can be divided into a various steps including identifying objective , defining problems , conducting researches , analyzing solutions , making decisions , presenting the products and finally , selling the products .
These are the universal steps in the process which followed by most of the engineers .
In Malaysia , the corruption in the politic system has leads to slow development in design process .
Besides , the education system introduced leads to lack of creativity and innovation on engineers .
Undeniable , politic system in a country plays an essential role in development of the country .
Statistically has shown that Malaysia ranked 47th out of 180 nations on Transparency International 's 2008 Corruption Perception Index .
Under most circumstances , one needs to bride in order to accomplish his or her objective .
For example , bribing is necessary and people usually got to pay under-table money to establish an engineering company , or to conduct a project .
One of the crying shames is the defects in Middle Ring Road 2 ( MRR2 ) fiasco , which happened on October 2004 .
The British engineering consultancy firm , Halcrow Concultant Ltd , had found that there were structural defects of piers on the MRR2 highway due to design flaw .
Then , the Work Ministry and the Cabinet had decided to replace the British with a German consultant , which costs RM40 million and at last , the Work ministry admitted that the repair cost was RM70 million .
Therefore , it was not shocking to say that the money had been bribed by the higher authority .
It is painful to hear that the repair works have to be deferred as the Anti-corruption Agency ( ACA ) stepped into the investigation of the fiasco .
Indirectly , these corruptions had hampered the engineering design process in the stage of analyzing solutions to get the repair work done as fast as possible .
In addition , lack of creativity and innovations have been identified to be the main problems in hampering engineering design process , which might due to the current education system in Malaysia .
Most of the students now were so used to be spoon fed .
They were usually spoon fed with dictated notes , and they expect that every solution will be provided .
They were overindulged by teachers as knowledge or information was provided to them in an oversimplified way , causing students to be too relying on teachers .
Students were treated in a way that discouraging independent thought and learning process , thus indirectly hindered their abilities to analyze and interpret problems due to lack of creativity .
Consequently , the two reasons have caused lack of development in engineering design process .
The corruption in politic system and abuse of power by the higher authorities hinders one 's motive to design a product as the steps to run a project is so cumbersome .
As a result , there will be less and less engineering products being develop , causing people might not have opportunities to enjoy the conveniences and leisure that bring by the products .
On the other hand , inadequate of creativity and innovations on engineers has leads to lack of knowledgeable engineers to design a product .
An engineer might have difficulties in interpreting solutions and making decisions during design process if he or she is lack of creativity .
Indirectly , insufficient of human resources in engineering field might leads to poor economy , due to lack of progression in engineering field .
In conclusion , corruption in politic system and lack of creativity on engineers , indisputable , significantly hampers engineering design process .
Therefore , action should be taken to prevent further corruption in politic system so that engineering design process would not be hinder .
Hence , government should encourage independent learning so that students will be more creative and innovative to facilitate engineering design process .
Before 1870 , people could communicate with one another in a distance away only by the mean of writing .
