The long and tedious journey in finding the key to save mankind now lies in a tiny microscopic life , that are extracted from mammal 's embryos , called stem cells .
They are believed to have the ability to create brand new organs , curing an array of serious diseases and even perhaps solve human ageing problems , simply by replacing .
Although after 30 years of research , scientists are still unable to solve the mystery of these cells , but there has been fruitful development where this stems are now being used to repair important tissues in the human body , etc. bone narrow .
But due to the nature of these cells , as a result scientist now faces both technology and scientific problems which hindered them from unleashing the full potential of these cells .
Technology played an important role , to aid researcher on their work .
We need the right tools for the right kind of job , we ca n't possibly use a screwdriver to do a hammer 's work , and right now this problem is being faced .
We need better technology to increase scientist 's capability to understand this cell better , like how it differentiate ( Transform ) into specialized cells which will later transform into an organ .
With current DNA technology , it has proven insufficient to precede any faster .
This is serious factor that scientist are now looking into , and once succeeded , imagine the amount of life would be saved .
Meeting the demand in the organ 's market and reducing the cost of medical treatments bringing an infinite possibility to the medical-industry .
One of the fascinating problem faced , is the human body itself .
Firstly human body has an extraordinary capability to identify foreign objects and purging them out from the system ( Rejection ) .
This has lead to serious complication to patient who is receiving this life-save treatment .
Without , this would result in an uncontrollable and misdirected growth of unwanted cells , etc tumor , or even cancerous cells .
This is a major obstacle that scientists are facing now .
I believe this would be most valuable scientific breakthrough .
The world food crisis would be solved by merging these cells with the current cloning technology to create fast and vast range of food supplies .
Take the aspect of electric devices as an example , refrigerator was studied for a long time in the laboratory after people had the desire of reserving things in a cold temperature longer .
On the other hand , the theory of microwave oven was discovered by Percy Spencer by chance .
He noticed that candy in his pocket melted while he was doing another experiment and by using this technology microwave oven was invented .
As technologies of modern society , both refrigerator and microwave oven have practical meaning .
Refrigerator helps to keep food fresh and microwave oven helps to heat food quickly .
They are used in the way to make our life better and more convenient .
Actually , they both become essentials of daily life .
In this way , standard and quality of life are improved by a large degree .
Firstly , refrigerator has a strong purpose in real life before it is invented .
As a result , the product will sell well because the aim of the technology is a common desire and meet the demand of the public .
Microwave oven , on the contrary , its function is not known before the theory is discovered and the equipment invented .
Thus , sometimes there will be a risk to produce a large amount of equipment applying the serendipitously discovered technology because the market of this field might not be large since before it is invented , other ways of the similar aim may have already existed .
Secondly , developing the technology of refrigerator in the laboratory needs a long time of work .
Since the idea is brought up , generations of people used various methods to improve the machine and make the technology perfect .
