One of the current human needs is to find an environmental friendly vehicle as a substitute for the gasoline vehicle .
Thus , an environmental friendly vehicle needs to be created and should be given priority for this creation to save our earth from pollution and to lessen the impact of the air pollution .
Electric generated vehicle can be designed to overcome the air pollution problem .
Electric generated vehicle will not exhaust gases when it is being driven .
It is because mining and refining processes of the petroleum will emit fumes that will pollute the air .
To build an electric generated vehicle that can have longer lasting battery power and powerful pickup , it should have a special battery , light weight material and well designed shape .
The battery of the vehicle must be able to recharge within short hours .
It should also be able to store higher amount of energy in order to last for longer period of time .
Furthermore , having an aerodynamically styled shape , the vehicle can move faster and has a powerful pickup .
The electric generated vehicle should be fully tested and examined .
Test drive for the successful electric generated vehicle can open to public and ask for feedback from them and make improvements for it .
After that the electric generated vehicle can be introduced to the market throughout the world .
In conclusion , the creation of electric generated vehicle can reduce air pollution problem that is becoming more and more serious nowadays .
Engineers can make world different by their expertise and knowledge .
Ecommerce : the Socially Determined Technology
Picture a scenario in mind : a man sitting in front of a computer is busy using email , eBay , online banking , and teleconferencing .
This is ecommerce , which consists of the buying and selling of products or services over electronic systems such as the Internet and other computer networks .
CITATION wik09 \ l 2052 ( wikipedia , 2009 ) Thanks to this burgeoning technology , people can almost fulfil all their needs without moving a step .
With the initial to achieve a more convenient human life , ecommerce is considered to be socially determined rather than technologically determined .
Basically , the origin of ecommerce is due to public 's desire to facilitate their life and work .
CITATION Ken08 \ l 2052 ( Kenneth , 2008 ) These were the very first types of ecommerce .
Later on , as the rapid spread of internet , the utility of this technology quickly varied and extended to global scope .
This concern soon results in the appearance of online store .
CITATION Jul08 \ l 2052 ( Julie , 2008 ) Till now , people can nearly do whatever they want simply by clicking the web browser .
During the speedy development of ecommerce , corporations realize the potential to gain huge interest and participate to shape the direction of ecommerce 's growth .
Comparing with the traditional selling styles , ecommerce manages to broaden the market as well as obtain a cheaper but more efficient publicity .
Thanks to the technology of ecommerce , these shops can now do publicity to a much larger target group .
By the same time , the online banking system also facilitates the procedure to make deals .
In the 1990s , as a result of the rising development of ecommerce , the usage of this technology gradually became out of control .
Directed by public 's requirement , enterprises ' intention , and government regulation , ecommerce is now still developing .
If continuing the efforts of these three aspects , we have confidence this technology will sooner or later develop to a certain stage which satisfies the whole society .
Singaporeans live in the comfort of their own homes believing that all the things that can be invented are already made .
These are a few traits that are hardly seen in the Singaporeans .
Therefore , only by overcoming the two major problems , Singaporeans will then be able to create and innovate .
The republic 's physical landmass of approximated seven hundred and five kilometres squared is ranked one hundred and eighty- seventh internationally .
In addition , even if there were potential solutions , it would be a tough task to carry out experimentation or trials , either as a mean to gather data or to implement a solution , simply because a local test group might not exists .
This deficient in raw materials and useable land as well as to a lesser extent , wealth and labour , limits the magnitude on the engineering solutions to be pursued .
Such an enormous amount would be several annum of Singapore 's gross domestic product in the current economic climate .
In conclusion , Singapore 's unique size and state of available resource are obstacles in the engineering design process .
The educational system is based more towards theory and not practical .
The amount of time spent in lab for practical is minimal .
Since the birth of car at the end of last century , its development has gone through ups and downs over the last one hundred years .
Zaochu Benz at that time only had a speed of 18Km per hour , but now , a sport car can accelerate from zero speed to 100Km per hour within 3 seconds .
The car industry ' development can not be separated from the adoption of car by the people .
So again , what is the factors influence the adoption of car ?
Actually , after Henry Ford 's Model T automobile was invented , cars just gradually become a vehicle that can be adopted by people .
The { Model T } [ HYPERLINK : http : //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_T ] was introduced on October 1 , 1908 .
Economically , because the Model T was so cheap that by the 1920s a majority of American drivers learned to drive on the Model T. Apart from this , in order to make the Model T more universal , Henry Ford also created a massive publicity machine in Detroit to ensure every newspaper carried stories and ads about the new product .
He also created a network of local dealers , which provided a good marketing channel to his company .
If we analysis from a bigger view , then we can see that there were also other economical factors influence the cars ' adoption .
One of the most important factors was that declining cost of oil at that time .
The daily output of this site was more than 1 million barrels o oil , which was even more than the sum of output of other sites in the United States .
This made the price of oil in United States decrease very fast at that time .
But the Model T was just a beginning of the adoption of cars , another factor which made the technology of producing cars became more mature was that the military demand .
During the wars , vehicle and armored transporter became essential for every country .
For example , a very popular hydraulic actuator which is still used today was developed in the early World War 2 .
All this inventions not only increased the useful time of engine , but also improved the overall situation of car industry .
Government policies and priorities also play an important role to the development of car industry .
After the United States won the war , many ordnance factories became civil factories ; this made the expansion of car industry faster .
Especially during the Cold War , in order to demonstrate America 's superiority and wealth , the government became more encourage the car industry .
In conclusion , the adoption of car and this technological innovation was not only technological determined , but also shaped by economic factors , military demands , and government policies and priorities .
An engineering design process , which includes mainly five stages-defining the problem , gathering pertinent information , generating multiple solutions , analyzing and selecting a solution and testing and implementing the solution , plays a very important role in improving the quality of people 's life .
Take China for instance , the culture for innovation in engineering design is severely lacked .
Even they have the motivation , their ideas are unlike to come true due to lack of funding from the government .
When a student finds out an alternative method of solving a problem , there is usually no reward for him and he still has to answer the question in the standard way to avoid losing marks in examinations .
Another problem that poses obstacles to innovation in engineering in China may be the lack of funds from the government for research and development ( R&D ) , thus engineers are hardly attracted to R&D industry and they lack of funds to implement their new ideas .
Mr. Yuan Long Ping , who is known as the " Father of Hybrid Rice " , had contributed to tremendous increase in the level of world 's rice output through cultivating species of hybrid rice during 1970s .
However , the Chinese government only awarded him the State Preeminent Science and Technology Award of China in 2000 which valued merely 5 million yuan .
This was very little if it was meant to reward him for his more than twenty years ' hard work .
This lack of government support means , engineers will not able to get resources , raw materials , precise equipment for research during engineering design process .
Thus the stage of testing and implementing solutions during engineering design is greatly hampered
In conclusion , rigid education system and government 's very little incentives to innovations limit the number of innovative engineers and hinder the realization of innovative ideas if any .
They are hence the two prominent obstacles that hamper the engineering design processes for innovations in China .
Skunk works projects do not have access to the full resources of the company , have their own rules and have to maintain confidential about their projects .
The research funds and human resources were not made available to them .
Hence the rules of the company need not to be enforced in their secret working environment .
There had been extreme examples of rules set by project managers where both emerged successful in their innovations .
Personnel will have to maintain double life for this project .
Personnel often have to stay back late after office hours to work on their secret projects and no claim of overtime are allowed .
There will also be media coverage and time to time update on their projects .
However they faced equal stress on their projects .
Singapore 's education system has been structured in such a way that it is rigid and text based and does not teach students to apply what is taught .
Another portion of the design processes involve commercialization .
Sadly , society as a whole are generally not that receptive of new ideas and innovative products .
In sum , a society which is less receptive of new ideas and innovative products could lead to the hampering of engineering processes for innovation .
Two problems are identified which might hamper creativeness in engineers .
However , several decades earlier , few people dared to declare that they were sure these innovations would surely be popular around the world in one day .
Despite of the poor environment , tough stress , and high risk , skunkworks indeed value more than conventional technology .
To some extent , conventionally generated technology usually improves our life , but innovation in skunkworks often changes our life .
Skunkworks , defined to pioneer the development of a technological innovation , normally has a tougher working conditions .
Usually skunkworks can not get enough support to create a satisfied working environment .
Due to the uncertainty , R&D group in skunkworks often can not find enough people to conduct the innovation .
Just like the team of design Macintosh , they were working day and night under the aggressive leadership of Steven Jobs .
The starting points of innovation in skunkworks and conventional technology are different .
However , Conventional is made for solving the existed problems or needs .
When NOKIA upgraded its N series hand phone annually , iPhone of the Apple company surprise the world , because it give a different definition of touching the phone .
Skunkworks takes a high risk in innovation process , but it is rewarding .
Just like " Post-its " of 3M was initially considered as a failure , which was finally proved to be a great success in other fields .
In the contrary , it is more stable and reliable for conventional technology .
Furthermore , it is often at a high risk for investing in skunkworks .
Compressed Natural Gas ( CNG ) vehicle is an alternative fuel vehicle .
By 2008 , there are roughly 7 millions of CNG vehicles on the roads worldwide .
Unlike the normal gasoline vehicle which emits greenhouse and harmful gases , the power of CNG vehicle can emit 70 % lesser CO2 and little harmful gas .
Therefore CNG vehicle is more environmental friendly than gasoline vehicle .
In the context of global warming becoming more and more serious , the development of such environmental friendly vehicles becomes a must .
Apart from reducing the air pollution , Natural gas vehicle also produces lower noise levels than gasoline vehicle .
This is another positive feature of CNG vehicle .
Moreover , the intention of reducing the fuel cost also shaped the development of CNG vehicle .
The oil embargo resulted energy crisis in the U.S. during the 1980 's .
Such situation motivated the discovery of alternative fuels that could reduce our dependence on foreign imports .
From 2000 's , the oil price grew tremendously , but the price of natural gas was much less .
More owners of private cars country wanted to convert their petrol-driven vehicles to also run on CNG .
Lastly , the development of CNG vehicle is also influenced by the government policies .
Due to the increase of the oil price and the necessity of improvement of the urban environment , many countries ' governments support the development of CNG vehicle .
Many countries which are abundant of natural gas introduce CNG cars and buses to their public transportations .
Some other governments provide tax rebate for the owners of CNG vehicles , so that to incentivize the using of eco-friendly vehicles .
For instants , the Singapore government provided 40 % discount on the Open Market Value ( OMV ) cost of newly-registered green passenger vehicles from 2001 in order to build up the intensity of CNG vehicles ( wikipedia,2009 ) .
With the help of the favorable policies and sponsorship from the government , more talented people are attracted to the CNG vehicle industry research .
As a result the CNG vehicle technology is shaped by the government policies .
Without the requirements of cheaper and cleaner vehicle and the governmental support , it might not as well-developed as now .
In recent years , with its growing prosper and affluence , China is investing more on science and technology development .
In the so-called cramming method of teaching , teachers paid particular attention to memorization , even at the cost of comprehension .
During the examination , the students were not evaluated by how much they memorize , but not on how they think .
In conclusion , the lack of research funding and exam-oriented education system is the two most significant factors which have hampered engineering design process in China .
For example , in 1970s , a new tomato variety was launched by a research team in California .
This tomato variety could be harvested by machine , which was a big success .
After about ten years ' research , he discovered Warfarin one day in an unrelated experiment , which turned out to be the most impressive progress in the whole research .
Not only should the scientists figure out how to breed the variety , but also they needed to do other non-research works in order to successfully put the variety into practice .
Finally , they came up with their research results after many years ' research , in due time according to their plan .
Besides , although both these two technology were successful , the keys to their success are different .
In conclusion , the mechanized tomato program has different start , process and key to success from the discovery of Warfarin .
Technology is progressing every day , and different products are created following these new technologies .
Our life become more convenient with these technological products and companies can benefit from producing these products .
However , not all the technological products can bring profit to their companies .
Before manufacturing a product , companies have to evaluate its profitability and denied those products with an uncertain future .
Engineers who are enthusiastic with these " no future " products form a group to work out the products , and this kind of groups are called " Skunk works " .
Conventionally generated technologies and technologies in " Skunk works " are of great difference while they still have features in common .
Technology in " Skunk works " is like a double-side sword , which not only can become a great success but also can be a super failure in future .
Working in a " Skunk works " environment is much tougher than in a conventional way , engineers working in " Skunk works " would not be rewarded unless their work turn out to be a success .
Nevertheless , both of " Skunk works " technology and conventional technology make contribution to technology development .
Comparing to conventional generated technology , " Skunk works " has a great possibility to become a big failure , while it also has a potential to be successful .
It is comfortable for engineers to make technology work and to optimize a design under given condition .
Whereas , a well optimized design is worthless if it can not meet the desires , or at least needs , of the customers .
On the other hand , a talent " Skunk works " can also be a success in market .
Like E.M. Rogers mentioned in his article - " the Birth of the Laptop Computer at Toshiba " , laptop is a good example of successful " Skunk works " .
The environment of " Skunk works " and the conventional one are of great difference .
Though engineers in " Skunk works " are enthusiastic about their project , it is very hard for them to find financial support , and other experts may criticize their works .
" Skunk works " and conventional projects are different , but both of them are making contribution to the development of technology .
Conventional generated technologies are closely connected to our life .
By doing sufficient market research , technologies are controlled to provide things that can fulfill our desires , and these technologies make our life become more and more convenient .
Therefore , " Skunk works " can promote the innovation of technology , and it also provides a big platform for creative engineers .
In sum , " Skunk works " environment is much tougher than conventional environment , and " Skunk works " is more like a gamble for a company for it may either be a big success or be an absolute failure .
The conventional generated technology plays an important role in fulfilling people 's need and bringing profit to companies , so it is a surety of technology 's steady and continuous development .
Therefore , both of them are indispensable for technology development .
Two problems of the innovation in my country
However , nowadays new technology is playing a more and more important role in the whole society and replacing the importance of resources .
One of them is that the intellectual property rights in China are not protected well ; there are many illegal copy phenomena in China .
The other problem is that the normal employees in many companies are not valued much by the employers .
Illegal copy phenomena block the innovation of technology in China .
One of the reasons is that the rate of the popularity of computer is much faster than the rate of the increase of consumption level in China , which means that the price of the software is relatively higher than that normal people can accept .
Subsequently , the inventor of the very software can only get a little profit , which will not impel him or her to continue paying much attention to the innovation .
When we compare the software area and the space flight area , we can easily find that space flight area of China develops extremely fast because of innovation while software develops slowly with little innovation .
Therefore , illegal copy phenomena restrict the development of the technology in China .
There is no doubt that China has developed fast and well since the foundation of the country .
However , when we change our focus on the enterprises in China , we will find that most of the huge enterprises are public and relied on resources and monopoly .
Huge enterprises which relied on high technology are very few .
One of the reasons is that normal employees are not inspirited to take part in the innovation .
In many companies , only some certain research staffs take part in the innovation of technology while normal employees just do their routine work .
Compared to professional research staffs , normal employees have more experience about certain productions .
As the employers do not show much respect to normal employees , few employees will try their best to provide their experience to research staffs .
We probably know that IBM employers value every employee in the company .
Many employees have a chance to put up a suggestion to the company .
With the large amounts of outcomes of experience and observation , research staffs can achieve new production relatively more easily .
Therefore , that normal employees are not inspirited restricts the innovation of technology in China .
Therefore , China should pay more attention on intellectual property rights to encourage people to innovate .
Unite everyone can maximize the ability of the whole unity .
China needs to solve these two problems to clear the way to innovation .
Another major problem that engineers might face in Singapore is that people are less receptive to innovations and ideas as compared to the Western countries .
For example , the education system now has definitely improved in terms of its rigidity .
Since 2005 , Ministry of Education ( MOE ) has introduced Project Work ( PW ) to junior colleges in order to improve communicative skills of students , as well as to encourage building of teamwork among students .
Hopefully in the near future , more effort will be put in to encourage society to be more accepting of new innovations that would greatly change their way of life for the better , and also to implement in not just aspiring engineers but students in general , skills that they are able to use and apply in handling problems in the real world .
Since the 1960s , there was a paradigm shift from the low end industrialization to a high end industrialization thus resulting in a rapid depletion of the already scarce resources .
Engineering design processes are therefore created to meet the above mentioned human need .
One of such engineering design processes is gathering pertinent information .
According to Khandani , " efforts spent searching for information about your problem...reveal facts about the problem...discover mistakes and false starts " , researching on the land scarcity problems can help one to prioritize by deciding on the more important infrastructure to build and strike a balance between social and economic needs .
For example , high rise flats are built to help prevent overcrowding and sustaining the population while mega infrastructures like the Integrated Resort are for economic purposes .
According to Khandani , " creative abilities can be developed if one is willing to take risks and not afraid to tackle problems " , the lack of land is a challenging problem to the leaders of Singapore thus engineers have to come up with innovative solutions to tackle land scarcity .
Some of these solutions are Land reclamation , condensed structural landscapes and the construction of sky scrapers .
Construction of sky scrapers is relatively safe despite its height due to deep analytical insights in the construction of these buildings .
One is via research and the other is the result from some serendipitous discovery .
But history shows us sometimes the fates of the two kinds of technologies birthed in different ways are also not the same .
The " designs " are thought highly by people at the beginning , though the importance of the " accidents " is realized much later .
Actually the major cases of engineering inventions coincide with the " design " way .
Though it 's may just a matter of few second 's time for the final success of a new technology development , the process from its infancy to maturity can be very long and tough .
With the coming out of a technology people will , of course , show their high concern on it , because it already cost a lot .
Take the atomic weapon test as an example , decades years ago the military of USA intent to make use of the power of atomic , they employed a lot human and non-human sources to complete numerous experiment and test , plenty of money was spent to invite talented scientists and engineers to come to help them make the most powerful weapon all through the human 's history .
According to the information from Wikipedia " The Manhattan Project cost 2 billion dollar , this includes the cost of the two bombs used as well as the test bomb .
" Then US treated this new technology as their most precious weapon , of course it was deserved .
In many cases , the technology which was created via research will be thought much at the beginning .
Because of the completed and formal research process , like the atomic bomb , many others technology which was developed via research will draw people 's attention .
As we can see that during the process , people know its property , figure out its purpose , understand its advantage and disadvantage , at last master the way to make full use of it , we 'd feel more confident to take some more steps .
Another reason is that some human and non-human sources have already been expended , and we do n't want to see these sources turn into nothing .
So the technology which is designed purposively will draw more attention .
Sometimes people will get unexpectable outcomes from their experiment or research .
Even some greatest discoveries come from accidents without any indication , for instance , the discovery of penicillin and the invention of gunpowder .
Gunpowder is invented by an ancient Chinese alchemist accidently .
One day the guy wanted to find some medicine called elixir of immortality aiming to give people a permanent live .
Dramatically , what he encountered was not the success of the magic drug , but an explosion and the birth of gunpowder .
However , the a bit foolish guy did n't set enough value on this great power as it should , so did n't the other Chinese people .
Gunpowder did n't have a chance to step onto the stage of the history until the famous adventurer and merchant Marco Polo introduce it to Europe from China .
Only after that the world began to pay enough attention to this powerful chemical medicine gradually .
Compared to the development of atomic bomb , the discovery of gunpowder is just an accident or something unexpectable that no one plans to make it realize before it really happen .
In my opinion , this must be very crucial to explain why nobody attaches importance to this new technology at first .
That 's to say , though , technologies like that may somehow change the world , it is not in people 's contemplation , time is needed for people to realize the existence of them and learn more about them .
Our world always improves along with the progress of technology step by step .
No matter whether their existence is a design or an accident , as long as it benefits us , that 's what we 'd like to see .
In 2005 , one of the most dreadful news revealed that { Kuwait } [ HYPERLINK : http : //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kuwait ] 's { Al Burqan Oil Field } [ HYPERLINK : http : //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Al_Burqan_Oil_Field ] , which is the second largest oil field in the world will be depleted before the middle of this century ( AME Info , Inc. 2005 ) .
Meanwhile , the up-going oil price also indicates an undoubting truth that we are facing a tough challenge , energy crisis .
According to oxford English dictionary ( 2006 ) , engineering is defined as the " science , discipline , art and profession of acquiring and applying technical , scientific and mathematical knowledge to design and implement materials , structures , machines , devices , systems , and { processes } [ HYPERLINK : http : //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Process_ ( engineering ) ] that safely realize a desired objective or inventions .
" Overwhelmed by the demand of energy , to increase the energy efficiency should be viewed as the priority of the desired objective or inventions of engineering design .
Primarily , energy is the fundamental base for all human activities which exploit the nature to meet our needs .
For example , if there was not sufficient fuel for automobile , then we would go back to the era of antiquity when walking and riding were the only means for transportation .
On the other hand , it is very irresponsible to squander the energy otherwise our posterity would face the consequences of our behaviours .
Hence , to maximize the energy efficiency should be taken into the priority of all the technology development so that human beings and the whole society will develop and move forward sustainably .
Moreover , to take the energy efficiency in priority will prosper the engineering design process resulting from the multiple and more prudent choices of solutions .
It is defined that there are five stages to solve an engineering design problem , " to define the problem , to gather pertinent information , to generate multiple solutions , to analyze and select a solution and to test and implement the solution " ( Khandani , 2005 ) .
If all the engineers are trying to design the technology with higher energy efficiency then they probably will gather more information , generate more efficient solutions as well as to select the solution which is more efficient .
At the time when engineers take the energy usage into consideration , the design process is upgraded to higher standard , which meets our needs and fulfill the vital objective of engineering design for technology .
If all the solutions are capable solving the problem , then the one which is the most efficient should be chosen .
The real example is that people now are pro to hybrid gas-and-electric-powered automobile instead of the conventional ones .
In one word , energy efficiency should be the prior concern for all the engineers due to its positive impacts on the design process .
Equipped with the high efficiency , all the innovations of engineering technology will be more dynamic and practical to meet our ever-increasing needs .
Toshiba 's laptop and Microsoft 's operating systems are two technologies that are created under different conditions and environment .
Toshiba 's laptop is often known as a skunk work innovation whereas Microsoft 's , as a conventionally created product .
According to Rogers , due to the fact that Toshiba 's laptop creator Tetsuya Mizoguchi failed to convince his superiors in Toshiba to support his laptop project , he was not able to receive any research and development funds .
It would be useless if there is no hardware for Gates ' program to work on .
According the article ( 2 ) , Gates actually wrote to computer hobbyist demanding that they pay for the usage of his program so as to allow him to continue to write quality programs .
In May 1998 , Microsoft is accused of abusing its monopoly power to keep rivals out of the market .
On the other hand , Mizoguchi idea was to create a laptop that is compatible with IBM 's platform despite the fact that they were competing for the same market share .
He recognised that IBM is dominant at the time and it would be fair to the consumers to allow them to use IBM compatible peripheral Toshiba 's laptop .
( 1 ) If Mizoguchi had done otherwise , we would probably have to buy only Toshiba 's laptop for its convenience .
Similarly for Microsoft , Gates rode on the success of IBM 's personal computer by becoming the full owner for a program that was written especially for IBM 's personal computer .
This had allowed them to be a monopoly in the industry .
In conclusion , despite the fact that both skunk work and conventionally created technologies differ in environment where they are being produced , they will still be successful if their creators have the determination and are full of ideas .
The birth of new technologies and inventions came about in different forms and through different processes .
Although the innovations maybe comparably similar , the conditions where they were created maybe totally different .
An example would be in the case of conventionally invented electric cars by General Motors and the first laptop that was invented in a skunk works environment by an engineer from Toshiba .
Differences like , risks involved , working environments , marketing strategies while similarities like the visions and goals of both innovations .
The first difference between the two types of innovations is risks involvement and work stress .
For skunk works environment 's created technology , the person who suggested the innovation has to take very big risks because it is a project of his own , he was not supported by companies , only his own team .
As said in Rogers ' article on the 'Birth of laptops ' , Tetstiya Mizoguchi , a Japanese technologist , disobeyed orders and risked his career for the sake of innovation-development which in the end , he succeed .
Secondly , the processes in which the new technology are designed and carried out between the two types of innovations are totally different .
Therefore , people who are working under skunk works environment have to gather their own team and a substantial amount of money before they can actually start on their project .
As such , because of limited funds the team or individual have in skunk works , they possessed larger stress because they could not afford to fail .
Because of disapprovals from companies , the working space for skunk works innovation is usually smaller and limited as compared to those who worked under companies to create new technology .
As said in Rogers ' article , Tetstiya Mizoguchi and his team went 'underground ' and work at a factory which was far away from the headquarters of Toshiba .
In the case of the creation of electric motor cars by General Motors written by Rogers , General Motors had gone to the extent of putting advertisements on the newspaper and came out with marketing campaigns to publicise their new product .
On the contrary , products or technology created from skunk works environment do have the capabilities to roll out massive campaigns to advertise due to the lack of funds .
They had to depend on their own network to publicise their product and introduce their prototypes to the public .
Comparing the two articles written by Rogers , the target group for skunk works prototypes testing usually started small , and then eventually became bigger as more people accept the product ; whereas in the case of conventionally created products , the target group is very large in the beginning due to large scale marketing campaigns .
The similarity between the innovations created under different environments is that both had wanted to come out with solutions to solve problems that were present .
In the case of Toshiba first laptop invention , Tetstiya Mizoguchi wanted to solve the problem which most Japanese companies faced , the crowded offices which prevented the usage of more desktops due to the lack of space ; while , electric motor cars were created to lessen pollution .
In conclusion , for innovations by conventions or skunk works environment , there are various differences and similarities between them , but at the end of the day , both produced products that helped to solve problems and bring benefits to the people in the world .
In 1943 , Abraham Maslow published a theory on what he believes is the hierarchy of needs of people .
In his study , he defined five stages of needs ; they are , in descending order of importance , physiological , safety , love and belonging , esteem and finally self-actualization.1 In view of the world today , we engineers should tackle the most important human need that needs the most urgent attention .
This is of course one of our basic physiological needs , water , which is imperative in sustaining lives , especially in harsh environments .
The five stage engineering design process , as proposed by Khandani , will guide us in making solutions that solve this problem .
Potable water , the source of life , has become the largest demand in third world countries .
Drinking water that has not been treated clean can lead to life threatening diseases .
According to the World Health Organization report in the year 2000 , Africa , home to a population of 784 million people , faces dire shortages of clean and disease free , drinking water .
3 Furthermore , it is the continent with the least supply of potable water .
It is important that engineer realize the true need of the problem , so as to waste resources on a solution that does not work .
For instance , one may think of solving the water shortage by building desalination plants throughout the coast of Africa , but only to realize that he or she did not address the problem it at all .
Because the water shortage may not lie in the quantity of water , but rather , lies in the ease of access to potable water in Africa .
The second step is to research on the shortage of potable water .
Engineers have to understand why current technology has failed to solve the water shortage , and the oversights engineers of the previous technology .
For example , a company has produced " LifeStraw " , a portable device that processes safe drinkable water to by removing microscopic bacteria through its filters .
4 Something like this may seem like a godsend to the people of Africa , but quickly follows its downfall is its cost and the problem of transportation of filtered water .
5 Therefore , a thorough understanding of the limitations of technology can guide engineers to invent a product that fulfills all criteria of the need .
Subsequently , in the forth step , they would have to rate and outweigh all of their ideas and determine the best one to implement .
This ensures the product meets expectations of the problem .
In a nutshell , we can see how the five stages of engineering design introduced by Khandani can help engineers plan and develop solutions to solving the water shortage in Africa , thereby saving countless lives in dire need of safe drinking water .
Date back to 1943 , one of the team engineers in Lockheed Martin Corporation , Irv Curler answered a call by saying " Skonk Works , inside man Culver speaking " when the secret project of P-80 Shooting Star jet fighter was being carried out .
The name was soon adopted for usage in engineering , business and technical field to describe small group of people with working on secret projects .
( How Skunkworks Got Its Name , par.2 ) Skunkworks have been a huge contributor for our invention for many decades .
Therefore , skunkworks drive comparable innovation to conventionally generated technology .
Therefore they are often used to roll out a product research before it is developed according to usual business processes .
With minimal management constraints , inventors are given freedom to research on the area they want .
Facebook was started off as a small networking site for college students , which slowly extend to be the most popular networking site globally .
With the help of his few roommates , Mark created Facebook with limited resources .
With no management pressure , Mark can add on any application on Facebook , which soon turn out to be the main ingredient in fueling up its success .
As mentioned , skunkworks are always lack of resources , which funding ranked first out of others .
As a start-up , Facebook did n't have the funding which its competitor , Myspace has .
As the history suggests , Myspace has everything in control when they first launched , including funding .
Thus , they get instant popularity in the beginning .
However , Facebook trounced Myspace recently , setting its user number to a record high .
Clearly can be seen , skunkworks are no loser to conventional technology despite funding problems .
While conventionally generated technology are opened to public , skunkworks undertake secret project .
Before Facebook was created , Mark hacked into Harvard School system to get the information of all the students while others are sleeping soundly .
Instead , he scarified his sleeping time to program another program to replace Facemash , which is Facebook we all are using today .
While Myspace took a different approach to show the public what they were doing .
The reason lies beneath could be the confidence Myspace had over their program because of the size of their resources which Facebook did n't have .
Despite the fact that the approaches they take are obviously different , they share the same goal , which is to innovate the future products .
Either Facebook or Myspace , we can use them to share information without borders .
They are competing between each other by introducing new features .
One of the few positive impacts arose by Iraq war is that governments as well as individuals came into awareness of how our dependence on oil , gas and other petrol products can trap us into serious situation once the supply of petrol is limited .
Moreover , the importance of finding new , sustainable and eco-friendly energy sources is now aware by people .
Indeed , the utmost purpose for the existence of engineers is to improve the living standard and satisfy the higher requirements of human beings by creating or improving the products used in daily life .
In daily life , energy supply is so important because almost all the human activities , like cooking , working , heating and even water supply can not work normally without electricity , and the emerging energy shortage is impossible to solve without the development of new energy source .
Thus , government should give priority to the research of economy , environmental-friendly and sustainable energy .
The basic steps for engineers to find new energy is shown as below .
For engineers to discover the suitable sort of energy , firstly , it is essential to have a clear definition and criteria of the problem and to gather enough relevant information .
A clear definition instructs engineers the direction in which their research is going on ( Khandani , p6 , 2005 ) .
And knowing more of the information makes our design process more effectively ( Khandani , p10 , 2005 ) .
In this case , the definition statement is : New energy sources : energy sources except the fossil fuel have a reasonable price , are sustainable and belong to green energy .
The criteria are : the new energy should be safe ; the energy should be sustainable ; the energy should not create pollution ; the price of the energy should be acceptable .
Then , engineers have to list down all the solutions and select the ones that satisfy the criteria .
When judge a new energy , the engineers have to think about the questions , such as " Is the energy able to replace petrol ?
" and " Does it have any potential problems ? " .. .
The energy crisis appears to be increasingly serious as human beings ' consumption keep increasing while the increase in energy supply is slow .
Since engineers are the most important in discovering new energy sources and the aim of their work is to meet people 's needs , they should give priority to the development of new energy .
On one hand , much effort and fund has been put into our education system to prepare our people for the Knowledge-based Economy .
On the other hand , Singapore has always been encouraging companies , regardless of their size , to do more in Research and Development ( R&D ) .
The reason for doing these is our government has realised the importance of R&D in our progress as a nation .
Although much effort and fund has been spent on R&D , some problems still exist to significantly hinder engineering design processes for innovations .
The first problem that hinders engineering design processes for innovations is the great influence of monetary profit .
In the past , around 1930 , there were two prototype refrigerators .
The other one was gas refrigerator .
Gas refrigerator did not produce the humming sound and had overwhelming advantages over the electric refrigerator .
But , electric refrigerator was selected over gas refrigerator because General Electric believed that larger profit can be made from the electric refrigerator .
Because of such influence , it affects the commercial , diffusion and adoption stages of the engineering design process .
Thus , many great innovations have been destroyed prematurely because of its lack of promotion to the public .
The second problem that hinders engineering design processes for innovations is that we , Singaporeans , are not as creative as our counterparts , such Americans , Japanese and Taiwanese .
It is because , in the past , our education system was more exam-oriented and theory-based learning .
Thus , we only applied our knowledge in examination , without applying it in real-life situations .
However , in recent years , our government has been actively promoting creative thinking in us .
Although the plans that promote creative thinking in us have been started years ago , it is still in its initial stage .
In addition , in this imperfect world , engineers are always solving the arising problems to make a better world .
Over the last couples of years , with the developing of China , all industries , especially manufacturing industry , are developing into a large scale .
However , it is strange that not so much big companies like Lenovo and Haier exist with such a large-scale industry and such a large home market .
Instead , millions of small companies are operating their small business everywhere , and large transnational corporations are enjoying their profit in Chinese market .
Many companies , especially the small ones , are following others ' steps to design and manufacture their products , expecting some profits in the market are still there , left for them .
Then , another question rise : what hamper innovations in engineering design ?
I think there are two primary reasons , high costs in engineering design with relatively low rewards and unsatisfying engineering education system .
As I mentioned , many manufacturing companies in China are running their business in a small-scale .
What they manage to do is making their designs slight different from other similar ones , which make their products quite elastic in the market .
For most case , the circle continues until they shut down .
In Chinese emerging market , not all invests in innovation are rewarding .
Instead , just following others is proved to be more profitable sometimes .
Secondly , the engineering education is not focusing so much on innovation but memorizing .
Other steps are neglected unfortunately .
Behind prosperity of the products " made in China " during the last few years , it is lack of innovations in products of Chinese local manufacture companies .
And the main reasons why we lack innovation are high costs and low rewards of innovation in China and unsatisfying engineering education system .
The common challenges faced by every developed and developing countries are the daily demands for improvement in various areas , be it economy , infrastructure or even society .
Engineers plying their trades in Singapore , however , will face two major problems amidst the common obstacles , in which they are potentially critical in the future development of the city-state .
Singapore , besides being famous for its airport and topping many surveys for the best , most recently named as the best place for business by the World Bank , it is also famous because of its size despite being termed as a " developed country " .
Hence , local engineers encounter their first major test in their quest : limited land spaces .
Despite plans ongoing to build a third plant , we are still rather reliant on Malaysia for the sale of water .
Reclamation of land from the ocean was also limited due to sensitivity border issues , thus hindering any designs that require huge spaces .
Past engineering miracles in housing now require an upgrade in innovation and design due to the cultural shift in our society , as the younger generation now demands quality unlike the past , when the more crucial task is providing a roof for every citizen .
There is another common global issue , especially worst in Japan , and that is the ageing population crisis in Singapore .
The entry into the 21st century provides the world with a whole new set of problems : pandemic flu , terrorism and the emergence of a group of senior citizens .
( The Straits Times , June 28 , 2008 ) Adding on to this problem Singapore , being a small country , has always faced a talent crisis .
Low birth rates coupled with the outflow of local talents force the government to resort to adopting a foreign talent scheme in order to increase the talent pool in the city .
However , as what our short Singapore history has shown , we have faced countless daunting tasks and have proven to be up to the mark ; therefore it will be no doubt our engineers will strive and succeed in their tasks ahead .
The problems that affect the engineering design
Nowadays we are living in a fast developing world which provides not only abundant goods but also convenient and functional productions .
Now focus on the things in my home country , China , there are two main factors : the overflow of copying and lack of money .
When a famous company releases a new product , some small companies or just workshops will soon copy the design of the product and sell " their products " at a much lower price .
Moreover , the customers may take both product as the same and the " fake " ones are more attractive with incredible price .
To design and produce a new product , the company will spend a lot of money and a lot of time .
The engineers keep working and working , trial and error , wishing to invent a best seller and have a good benefit .
While , the workshops who simply copy the design just do the procedure directly with low prime cost .
Usually customers will not discriminate the products and they consider the price as the main point .
After the great effort , the company will not receive the benefit as they wish , which will definitely cool down their desire to innovate .
Thus , the overflow of copying really hamper the processes for innovation .
For most companies in China , they are still on the pace of development .
They badly need to focus on the mature products to accumulate the property .
It seems too extravagant to pay for the designing .
Yet the innovation is full of risk which may push the company to the edge of cliff .
Just like gambling , company bet all what they have on the future .
In this way , the lack of money actually affect the stage of process for innovation .
Everyone is afraid of losing money on innovation , then , no new designs will come out and our world will not develop .
The government can do little on the copying incidents .
The poor quality of products hamper the interests of customers and yet affect the fame of the famous company .
It is hopeful that government will invest money in the projects with good prospect .
Since USSR 's Obninsk Nuclear Power Plant was established on June 27th 1954 , nuclear power has becoming one of the most important energy resources in the world .
By 2007 , an estimated of 14 % of the global electricity come from nuclear reactions according to the International Atomic Energy Agency .
And due to the ever increasing consumption of oil and its limited reserves , it is predicted that there would be a further surge for nuclear energy .
Nuclear power was first discovered scientist in 19th century .
As a result , it is perceived as an alternative of liable energy resources .
Recently , Iran and North Korea are facing sanctions from various countries and continent because of their nuclear development .
In this case , it clearly presented how political factors structured the advancement of important technology like nuclear power .
In North Korea 's case , they started the development of nuclear technology because of the raise of tension with South Korea .
Hence , they regarded nuclear development as a way to sort out the disputes over policies .
At the same time , Iran makes use of nuclear power to resist American policies and its influence in the region as well .
For nations like Iran and North Korea , the development of nuclear power is mainly determined by the political forces .
Despite the political impact on the nuclear technologies in the less developed world , military forces are likely to exert a similar impact on development of nuclear power in those more developed countries .
For instance , the US military force considers nuclear power as viable source to provide energy for the military uses .
Due to logistic reason combined with the unstoppable depletion rate , scientists in the United State is diverting most of their funding into research of how to make nuclear power as a readily mobile and less dangerous energy source for military uses .
In conclusion , the recent innovation and development have showed the impact of political , military and other social factors .
As the development of technology , the abilities of innovation have becoming more and more important all over the world .
In order to survive and develop in the competitive world , it is crucial for not only many countries but also the individuals to fully develop the process for innovations .
According to Rogers ( 2003 , the generation of innovation ) , there are six main stages of this process , namely the needs and problems , research , development , commercialization , diffusion and adoption and the stage of consequences .
Take China as example ; there are two main problems in hampering the development of innovation .
First of all , the education system has great effects on the process of recognizing the problems or needs which is the fundamental stage of innovation-development process .
It is true that the Chinese special education system has excellent achievements in laying the solid foundations of knowledge and skills which are also very important in doing the deeper researches and studies , but the lack of flexibility and creativeness of Chinese education-system is still a big problem .
As a result , many students get used to accepting the information in the references without thinking and investigating by themselves .
Consequently , it becomes quite difficult for them to discover the potential problems even when they try to to do it .
However , Innovation requires students to develop the ability of discovering problems instead of easily satisfying with the current situations or just following the rules .
In fact , most of the famous inventions or significant scientific discoveries are based on the ability of questioning .
If Watt did not realize the shortcomings of the traditional streamer , the age of stream may be can not come so fast .
If Galileo did not challenge and simply accepted the statements presented by Aristotle thousands years ago , people may still not realize the nature of free fall motion for a long time .
Without the awareness of recognizing or discovering the problems , the innovation process can not proceed smoothly .
In addition to the education problems , the economic development is also one of the important limitations for China .
General speaking , the success of innovation needs a lot of premises .
Not only the human resources , but also the financial resources have impacts on the development of innovation .
The implementation of many big projects or innovations requires large amounts of economic foundation .
Indeed , the economy of China is accelerating at high speed recently .
However , it is really hard to meet all the needs of the rapid innovation-development in the past .
Comparing with some developed countries , China still can not provide large amounts of financial aids in encouraging and supporting scientists and engineers in doing the process of research and putting these innovations into practice .
In a nutshell , for the importance of developing the processes for innovation , it is quite necessary to solve these existing problems nowadays .
Only if China try to minimize these potential limitations , will the innovation-development processes success and flourish .
It is a serendipitous discovery made by Alexander Fleming from a petri-dish with bacteria left behind from his experiments when he went for a holiday .
In-vitro fertilization is the process of making fertilization of eggs with sperms outside the womb of the mother and the technique is invented through researches .
Many may think that serendipitous discoveries are just by luck , but through the comparison of penicillin and in-vitro fertilization , we will realize that serendipitous discoveries are just as complex and impactful as technologies created through research .
Rogers ( 2003 ) suggested that researches with the objective of providing solutions for one problem might result in solutions that are useful for another problem .
Indeed , for the case of penicillin , Fleming did not anticipate the discovery of penicillin , a type of antibiotics , when he was making researches on the characteristics of bacteria .
On the other hand , In-vitro fertilization is researched upon and invented with the primarily objective of conceiving babies outside the wombs of mothers .
After the discovery of anti-bacteria substance , Fleming did his researches to improve on the results just like what the researchers for In-vitro fertilization did .
Both the technologies have to go through laboratory testing and many other processes before the final formula is derived .
Hence , both the technologies are developed in a laboratory environment with sufficient equipments for their testing and both requires extra steps even after discovering the correct method of making the technology .
In addition , both the technologies are developed not only by the person who founded the technology .
( " Alexander Fleming " , Wikipedia ) Also , in-vitro fertilization would not be successful if not for other researchers such as John Rock , Patrick Steptoe and Robert Edwards besides Carl Wood .
Furthermore , both penicillin and in-vitro fertilization have similar impacts on mankind .
They both brought benefits to people in the medical field .
Thus , in terms of the effects they brought for the people , they are similar in enhancing the life of mankind .
In conclusion , even though penicillin 's discovery was accidental , we can see from the comparison of the two technologies that the invention is actually comparable to those developed by researches .
The developments of both technologies are similar in terms of the complexity of the processes and the impacts of the technologies are equivalent .
Many countries are stepping into the Greying Societies .
As the elder population grows larger and larger , the burden on the younger generation and government becomes greater and greater .
I think the government can carry out positive policies to limit the money spent on the elderly indirectly .
Encouraging the later retirement and giving out subsidies based on the financial need are efficient ways to lessen the amount of money spent on the growing population of the aged .
Government has to limit the money given to the elderly for the reason that the expanded population of the elderly can lead to serious problems in economy , society and productivity .
( { http : //bbs.chinadaily.com.cn/redirect.php ? gid = 2&fid = 6&tid = 58116 } [ HYPERLINK : http : //bbs.chinadaily.com.cn/redirect.php ? gid = 2&fid = 6&tid = 58116 ] &goto = nextoldset ) Encouraging the later retirement is a effective method to solve this problem .
As the aging population becomes larger , more people retire than the usual .
It can be predicted that more people will leave their work and fewer people can enter .
On the other hand , the amount of the tax will go up as the productivity increases .
For some people , they save enough money when they are young or they can still make their livings as they are old or they are supported by their children .
Giving everyone pension means that some people 's living standard will be influenced but giving out money based on the fanatical need means everyone can live in a good condition .
The pension is not important to the people who are able to live a good life in their late life .
Although more and more countries are faced with the aging problem , the government can make some policies like encouraging later retirement and giving out money based on the fiscal need .
Throughout the process of aging , people will face certain problems relating to health , finance , and social and so on ; and many of these problems are usually interrelated .
With the help of these technologies , many possibilities are formed .
All these have helped to make the process of aging easier ; whereby the aged can lead better lives with fewer health problems .
Also through research and development , many lifestyle guides that help create healthy lifestyle , becomes available .
It is known that by having a healthy lifestyle , one will have fewer health problems ; and thus , spending less on healthcare .
As these new technologies involve the usage of newer , and more advanced equipments , the costs of using such technologies tend to be higher than the past .
By prolonging the life of the victim , it can be financially draining on the family , and cause financial and social tension within the family .
Financial aids can be made available to these families ; and help relieve the financial stress .
With these , the aged can have longer working life , and thus accumulating more wealth to support themselves through their old age .
Also , the government helps relieved financial stress by subsidizing healthcare costs , and providing financial aids to the elderly needy .
New technologies have been created to help eliminate many of the age-related health problems .
However , not every elderly in the society can get to enjoy these perks , especially those who are bounded by financial problems .
Therefore through current research and development and policies , the aging process has been made easier , but it is only to a large extent .
Until recently , the problems of aging population have become a major concern among all the nations throughout the world .
Governments of many countries have come up with policies and solutions to decrease elder dependency and slowing down the process of a fast aging population .
Aging statistics taken from the United States of America administration of aging shows people above the age of 65 represented 12.4 % of the population in the year 2000 but are expected to grow to be 20 % of the population by 2030 .
The statistics have shown that in time to come , the problems of a fast aging population will be too overwhelming for the society to handle , therefore we have to slow down the aging process .
The country 's economy will also suffer as a small amount of young working population will have to support a bigger umbrella of elder generation .
A lot of resources will also have to be spend on the elderly people .
In this way , the working population will not be stressed on too much by the elderly population .
This will help the elderly to be more in touch with the society and keep their physical health in good shape which will in turn reduce diseases .
Singapore has also help working adults to save money when they are working so that when they retire , they will still have money for living expenses .
To meet healthcare needs , Medisave was introduced to allow CPF members to use their CPF savings for hospitalization .
In this way , most problems of the aging population is taken care of .
Singapore has also emphasize and instill filial piety to the children of the aging population and to support their parents through meeting their financial needs and emotional needs .
The children of the future should provide for their parents as much they can even though their financial status looks bleak so that the aging population will not have to rely too much on government help .
Singapore has encouraged people to buy a HDB flat near their parent by subsidizing a substantial amount of money .
This will definitely reduced the fiscal cost of elder dependency .
No matter how much we encourage young people to care for their parents , it 's still their personal choice , the society or the government can not force them to do their part .
This is because what the aging population needs are their children providence and their care and concern .
In conclusion , I think that many developments and policies have helped to reduce the aging process and also solving the problem of a fast aging population .
Although this problem can not be solved in a short period of time , theses policies and development will help to curb the problems of an aging population .
Many pessimistic predicts were made by people about this problem .
However , with the assist of Information and Communication technology ( ICT ) , the situation could be fundamentally shifted through mainly three ways .
This change effectively eliminates their disadvantages in lack of mobility compared to the young people .
Nowadays , fewer and fewer jobs are requiring certain level of performance .
Those repetitive and tedious jobs are now performed by machine and jobs become more of management people and resources , especially with Information Technology as the medium .
This change of job nature makes a huge difference to the aged people 's captivity for their body conditions are no longer their employer 's top concern .
Besides by changing the workspace , ICT also brings good news to the aged by changing employment relationships .
9 out of 10 employers would be reluctant to hire an old people because they are in fear that they can not work as efficiently ( which is always not the case ) .
However , with the introduction of ICT , many more new jobs are created , large percentage of which are self-employed jobs .
So for the elderly , a new choice is offered to them : after their retirement , instead of heading into the job market and compete with people probably half their age for a post , they can start up their own business .
What matters is their smell , not their age .
The previous two points are mainly about ICT 's impact on the elderly jobs .
Thus , being re- educated becomes a prior task for them .
Importantly as it is , very few old people managed to get back to school and receive education again .
The main reason for that is firstly they may feel embarrassed studying together with young students who are at their early twenties .
Secondly they may not have sufficient money or large piece of time for their re-education .
The opponent may probably argue that ICT is a privilege that only benefits the young people .
Although young people have an advantage for they are exposed to the technology from early ages , the aged people still stand a high chance to succeed , as long as they can adapt to new features quickly .
After all , the internet is a common property which every one can enjoy a share .
Current research and development in the field of ICT has largely shapes the society .
Since people have longer life expectancy , the number of elders increased .
This caused the event that we called the aging population .
The aging population caused a lot of disadvantages , since a lot of money will be used to support the elderly .
Consider if there is an elderly has been sick for a long time and his/her spending has already reached the limit ; are we going to tell him to die because we will not provide him with anymore money ?
Secondly , the elderly has the right to be protected because they have worked for the country before .
Would we like to be treated as a burden and given a lot of limitations ?
It is really selfish if we treated the elderly badly but still want to be treated nicely when we grow old .
It may be objected that elderly might misuse this service and fully rely on the public funding rather than trying to cope on their own .
There are a lot of people that could only rely on this service to survive .
We should remember their deeds and we should also remember that we will be an elderly one day .
In other words , the government will spend more on creating jobs and educating the population .
It might be true to some extent , but we should also consider that the government will only limit the public spending on the elderly , and they will not eliminate it .
Government will still take care of those who can not take care of themselves .
Friedland and Summer ( 2005 ) stated that the meaning of " retirement " and " old age " nowadays is different from what it is in the past , as future groups of older people are likely to be even better off .
Furthermore , the country will also lack of trained labor force .
For instance , Indonesia , the world 's 4th most populous country , has 109,900,900 labor force , but the rate of the unemployed is very high ( 9.10 % ) in 2008 ( CIA , 2008 ) , due to low education participation rates .
The current situation is concerning as when this generation ages , the government will need to provide a certain care for them .
Hence , it is again the government 's role to subsidy the education so that everybody at least could get the standard level of education .
Education alone is not enough because even if the society is better-educated but there are not adequate jobs available , it will give the same problem of unemployment .
The government plays the role to create and maintain new jobs .
Besides increasing the number of new jobs , the government can try to invent a new type of job , which can be done by people regardless their age , including the elderly .
For instance , telecommuting part-time jobs , which do not require the workers to be in the workplace , is good to be implemented nowadays , by means of our advanced technology .
Governments and policy makers will take the main role to invent the best policies to deal with the long-term economic and social challenge of global aging , so that we are fully prepared to face this concerning issue .
Aging is becoming a hotter problem when the percentage of the elderly in the society is continuously increasing .
Certainly , when the number of aged people raises , public spending on this group will have to be raised as well to take care of this group .
However , I think there should be a limit on how much shall be spent for the elderly , because government needs to emphasize the money more on country development .
Actually , the problem of more population getting aged does not lie in the demographic change , but in the fact that the productivity of the nation will get declined .
When the government try to spend more and more for the aged , it will leads to a lack in money for development , then a slower economic growth , which finally leave the government with less choice to spend for the elderly people .
Secondly , imposing a limit on public spending for the aged can make people spending money more responsibly .
For most people , bearing in mind that they will have to take care more for themselves when they are old will force them to save money for the future .
They therefore will have to think more when spending money , and reducing wasting extra money on unimportant things .
Moreover , nowadays , with better living condition for the whole life of a person , attributing old people with bad health seems to be not so true for many cases .
Hence , extra care such as extra health diagnostic may not be necessary for many elderly people .
With less money received , social organizations which host these activities will have to choose people to serve more carefully and this can also save much money .
From the opposing view , many people argue that the aged are the most vulnerable group in the society and thus needing more and more attention .
However , to help these people become less vulnerable , it is not so good to do so when they are already aged .
Thus , focusing on social development as a whole , and improving living condition throughout the life of people is actually better way to help people gain a better health and become less vulnerable when they are aged .
The productivity of the country will therefore be increased , and again , with more wealth earned , public spending in general , and on the aged , in particulars , will be increased as a certain result .
In conclusion , although the population of the earth in general is getting aged , which could lead to certain consequence , the government should not be panic to address that problem in a short term way by increase public spending for the aged as high as possible .
Rather , the government should focusing on develop the nation as a whole , especially maintaining the economic growth , because this is the long term and most effective way to solve aging problem .
In my opinion , I agree to a large extent that current research , development and policies have helped eased the aging process .
In the course of my essay , I will first show how economics , medicine , architectural , technological inventions and social policies have helped eased the aging process while financial constraint can limit the effectiveness of easing the aging process .
Firstly , economics have helped eased the aging process .
The various products available helped to minimize the impact of unforeseen events so that an individual can save resources to meet aging needs .
In addition , as education opportunities increase , economies around the world has transformed from labour intensive to knowledge-based .
Secondly , architecture has also helped eased the aging process .
With the growing advocate for obstruction free building design , the mobility of the senior population is significantly increased .
The safety features in household appliances has enabled the elderly to take care of their own needs safely .
Overall , technology allowed the elderly to reduce their dependency on others , and improves the quality of their lives .
In this way , the elderly will have a sum of money available to support themselves in their golden age when they retired .
In conclusion , economics , medicine , architecture , technological inventions and social policies have helped to ease the aging process but they required financial resources to achieve .
The problems of an ageing population have led to these countries coming up with measures to counter effect the problems .
One of which is to increase public spending so as to ensure that the aged are taken care .
We have to prepare more healthcare teams to specialize in treating illness related to the old as it is commonly known that the old are more prone to illness .
Thus , by increasing the amount of healthcare workers focusing on treating elderly illness prevent the situation of the lack of healthcare workers for the elderly in the near future .
Even though so , some of the elderly may not have saved enough to last them till death or their children are not willing to take care of them .
Nevertheless , if the government leaves elderly who are fighting old age alone without care , it would be too cruel of the government .
These unfair treatments that the elderly faced may be pose a psychological problem to them .
For example , the old aged face discrimination when finding jobs as compared to the young and also , the old age may receive less all-rounded treatment in healthcare sector based on the stereotype that they are in the natural process of aging and that they are less likely to recover .
The government then has to interfere to educate the public to be less prejudiced against the old aged .
If the economic improves , people would earn more money and thus the burden on the children taking care of their old-aged parents would be relatively less as they could better afford the costs of taking care of elderly .
Those elderly who are unfortunate or those without kids may face problems as they would have no one to take care of them and would be worse off without any help from the government .
As a result , public spending on the aged should not be limited as it is needed to help these elderly .
To sum up , the government has to assume responsibilities in taking care of the elderly and to ensure that the country is adequately prepared to accept an ageing population , public spending on the aged should not be limited and money should not be diverted into other areas of the country 's development .
I agree to a large extend that current research and development/policies have helped to ease the aging process .
Technology plays a significant role in providing aid and improving the lives of the elderly .
It is also important that ageing related problems are highlighted into the national development and policies for example introduction of the pension system and encouragement of late retirement to reduce elder dependency .
Firstly , the goal of personal health technologies will be to change from a centralized model where the elderly would go to the hospital where healthcare is provided , to a distributed model where by healthcare involves the places where the elderly lives .
Information technology applications have enabled elderly to initiate communication , keep track of their personal health record and also make follow-up appointments which can be conducted through Telemedicine .
Telemedicine was introduced to provide care for the patient from any location with the help of transferring electronic information through various technology applications and equipments ; such as the web camera .
This technology delivered care directly to the homes of the elderly at an affordable rate and provide right information at the right time which benefits decision making of the medical officers involved .
It involves elderly to be more active in taking care of themselves at the comfort of their own home .
It may be objected that telemedicine might not be as effective as contact monitoring and hands on attention .
Nevertheless , such applications have helped to reduce the time spent in hospitals and cost of medical , improve record tracking practices and speed of communication .
Next , national developments and policies such as pension systems are arranged to provide the retired elders income .
The fund may be set up by a corporation , the government , or any other organization to pay the benefits of retired workers .
Critics of this position pointed out that the cost of providing pensions leads the increased taxes on the workforce .
However with the help of pension system , it has provided the elderly with a retired fund , thus reducing the elder dependency on the children of the elderly .
Opponents of this position argue that there would be an increase in the wage base with a lower retirement age , because people will save less as they need less wealth and lower savings , thus by increasing the retirement age .
Moreover , lifelong learning empowers elderly to lead a better lifestyle through social interaction and contribution to the community .
In conclusion , technology and the national development and policies have helped ease the aging process .
Technology applications such as Telemedicine which aids the tracking and handling of medical reports and appointments which in return , encourages elderly to keep track of their personal health through a cost and time effective system .
In recent years , aging population has become a serious demographic challenge to many countries around the world .
Many governments are concerned about an aging population as it leads to problems such as shrinking workforce , decrease in economic growth due to a drop in productivity , increase in societal costs and many more .
With an increase in the number of elderly , it can potentially lead to increase in healthcare costs .
With higher demands and costs for healthcare spending , it will pose as a great challenge for both family and public resources .
Government spending on healthcare amongst countries around the world has always taken up one of the biggest fraction for the budget to be spent by the government .
However , have you ever thought that , if there was a decrease in the amount of government spending on healthcare costs , where will the money be better used to ?
Money can then be diverted to other areas of the country 's development which maybe of better use for the future generations , it will also make society more independent when looking after their own health and lastly instil stronger filial piety and willingness in today 's youth .
Firstly , with a higher budget to be spent in other areas such as education and defense , a country may develop even more rapidly .
With little economic growth , society may be faced with fewer options on how to take care of people who are least able to take care of themselves .
However , with sufficient economic growth , this would not be the case as there will be more options and lesser persons in need of the help .
With more educated youth , the size of the economy and tax base will be higher and the cost burden of an aging population may be spread over a larger and more productive future generation .
Such as the case in Scandinavian countries where generous public funding for prenatal incentives and investments in children for example in education as helped curb the problem a population 's aging and declining .
Furthermore , with a more educated society , more people are acquired with the knowledge to better take care of themselves and hence help lessen the amount of healthcare spending .
Elderly dependency can be reduced when it is enforced or encourage upon them to plan and provide in advance for their own old-age dependency .
When enforced by law or encouraged to save and invest more of their income while still in the work force , people will then of sufficient amount of money to take care of their health issues when necessary rather than depend on the government spending to support their health spending .
Dependence on the government can also be reduced by encouraging later retirement dates , longer working lives and lower requirements to elder employment which can be achieved alone with an increase on the eligibility of age for pensions and government incentives for the elderly .
In Singapore , the government has tried using schemes such as CPF ( Central Provident Fund ) , Medisave , Medishield and even scrapped away the pension scheme in order to encourage more Singaporeans to take better control of their own health issues .
Lastly , with limited public spending on healthcare , it will encourage more working adults to take better care of their elderly parents .
With elderly to look after for , there will be more stresses on filial obligation and also increases the willingness of adults in the future to take care of their elderly parents by all methods .
In an increasingly paper-chase society , working adults often have no time , attention , care and even financial aid to take care of their elderly parents and eventually abandon them in homes .
However , with the support and care from the proper channel from the family , it may be a better and cheaper alternative to take care of the elderly by yourself then depend on the nursing home 's nurse to take care of your parents .
However , detractors may disagree that money public spending should be limited on healthcare and diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
The society may face with a wide range of social issues on education , housing and many more which may not be solved by setting limits on healthcare expenditure on the government 's part but instead create even more problems .
Yet , in the first place , spending on healthcare may not be a good way to solve societal issues such as the lack of filial piety amongst youth and over dependence on the government to solve every problem one might face with .
In a nut shell , government spending on the aged in the healthcare should be capped at a certain limit to take care of people who may really be in need while the rest of the budget are to be shifted to other areas of the country 's growth .
With a limit on healthcare expenditure in the government 's budget , there maybe a better investment in the area where the government 's budget goes to , people would be more self reliant and lastly it will instill a stronger sense of filial obligation in youth .
If the government decides to cut its expenditure on aging population , the elderly will be struggling for their survival as many welfare benefits will be limited .
This increase burdens on the younger workforce as they have to bear the cost of healthcare services required by the elderly .
This is because the older generation has contributed to the workforce during their younger days .
It is their hard labour that had paved the road for us today .
As a result , the younger people and the government should return favour by helping the elderly .
Even if the elderly is able to support their own , the government should continue in assisting through other policies .
However , priority should be given to the needy elderly ; especially for older people with less education background and savings .
A handful of old people are left stranded on the streets without shelters .
Some are abandoned by their families while others can not afford a house because of their financial difficulties .
Therefore , the government should not limit public spending on aging population .
As they aged , their body constitution becomes weaker .
They have to make occasional visit to the doctor for diagnostics and remedy .
The cost is heavy , especially nowadays when new technologies and treatments are expensive .
The government can subsidize part of the healthcare expenses borne by the elderly .
This will lighten the burden of the aging population as well as the younger workforce .
Certainly , if the government diverts its spending to other areas of the country 's development , they would enjoy a growing economic growth .
Because of that , they will be able to collect more taxes , which can be used to aid the aging population .
Clearly , the consequences of cutting expenditure on the aged outweigh the other in many aspects .
A sizeable segment of the aged will be suffering through the process of achieving an economic growth .
Consequently , they will be struggling for survival with the limited welfare policies available to them .
In other words , if welfare programs for the aged are reduced due to limited spending , many problems will arise .
Subsequently , the government have to spend more resources to solve the arising problems .
Therefore , it is better to give equal if not more spending to the aged , keeping existing welfare benefits in place .
Current psychological researchers claimed that there are several pillars of being a healthy individual .
Therefore , to have pillars such as having sufficient social support and having an active engagement in life helps people to cope with the inevitable stressful elderly life .
Care at home is often the preferred choice of the elderly and is generally more affordable for care providers than sending them into an elderly institution .
The elderly needed some form of monitoring technology to help improve their safety where no one is able to be around to look after them all the time .
Remote health monitoring solutions such as to keep tabs on their blood pressure , body temperature and their heart-rate can alert for medical attention as fast as possible .
Technologies had also been designed to help the elderly maintain their own independence .
One invented device uses optical sensors to supervise how these elderly pick things up and how they use them .
It can tell if a person does something wrong such as mistaking a bottle of vinegar as drinking water ; or if they are doing certain things in the wrong order .
This technological invention can also be extended to monitor how the elderly interacts with other devices such as a television , DVD player or a washing machine .
Another invention uses Radio Frequency Identification ( RFID ) technology to track which medications were taken and when .
In addition , adding a motion sensor system to provide a daily update of the elderly can help bring peace of mind to distant relatives who are concerned about the safety of their elderly family members who might be injured or ill and worse of all ; unable to call for help .
We have seen how technologies were able to replace human supervision and to monitor elderly condition round the clock which was less possible with human care providers .
One may argue that these technologies could potentially isolate the elderly further from their families and keeping them indoors even more .
This is no longer true because advanced technologies had managed to put a face to high tech devices .
A technology called the Digital Family Portrait enables the elderly and their relatives to hang up a special digital frame on their walls to receive updates of what 's going on in the faraway houses .
This technology can also be used to receive video phone calls from neighbors within the elderly community .
Furthermore , elderly who have difficulties getting out of their homes can tap on various video technologies to draw themselves closer to their neighbors and faraway relatives by playing chess with them or engaging in a simple conversation .
Instead , it was meant to be a life enabler to increase the quality of life ; like helping the elderly stay indoors safely providing maximum possible social interaction and social support from their neighbors and relatives .
Therefore , current research on technology targeted towards the elderly will not only help ease the aging process ; it also increases the quality of life significantly for these elderly folks .
As Singapore 's population ages , there are many issues arising on how to help the elderly cope with the aging process .
Therefore , with the government 's emphasis on tackling the uprising problems of an ageing population , current research and development have helped to ease the aging process through introducing policies , upgrading of facilities and providing quality healthcare services .
These improvements can be seen in various context and we will be looking at the benefits it has provided to the elderly .
They introduced laws and encourage people to save and invest more of their income earned while they are active in the work force .
The government created public awareness on early planning and proper saving strategies which are necessary to ensure that we have enough money to last us through our old-age after retirement .
The government has also setup a mandatory saving scheme for all working Singaporeans .
However , to some people , especially the younger minds , they disagree with such scheme .
They believe that they should have control over their money earned instead of being 'forced ' to contribute a portion of their income to such a scheme .
Thus , with the public awareness on saving for old age and the CPF , one will have sufficient savings for their old-age dependency .
Therefore , with the development of an elderly-friendly environment , it has helped to ease the aging process .
An elderly is not afraid to walk around the housing estates or travel in public transports as these facilities have become more accessible to them .
One of the architectural developments that we can see is the building of lifts to serve all levels of new and existing HDB flats .
This eliminates the need for an elderly to climb the stairs in order to get to the level that the lift has no access to .
The elderly will have an easier time walking up and down to get to their destination .
Public transportations such as the MRT and buses have similar concept implemented to their facilities .
MRT stations have built lifts to allow the elderly to travel up to the platform and down with ease .
Public buses have steps-free entrance and exit for easier mobility of the elderly .
However , some people are concern if the spending on all these upgrades to increase accessibility for the elderly is necessary .
But if we do not maintain a good infrastructure that caters to the elderly , no matter how good the economy is , the elderly will not be able to enjoy accessible and user-friendly facilities that ease their life .
However , now we will be able to get the proper care and rehabilitation from improvements to healthcare facilities such as public hospitals , nursing homes and polyclinics .
We have a team of well-trained doctors and nurses who are committed to take care of the elderly who needs special attention .
We also have groups of medical specialist who are always finding ways to improve the healthcare of the elderly through better medication and rehabilitation .
As a result , more day rehabilitation centres and nursing homes are built to handle the demands for increasing healthcare .
In my opinion , the elderly does not need to worry about getting good healthcare services as it is easily found anywhere in Singapore .
The government policies are involved to ensure that proper saving for the future is in place , the upgrading of public facilities have helped create an elderly-friendly environment and the better healthcare services readily available .
Firstly , encouraging later retirement for elderly can drastically change their attitude towards work .
This in turn will provide a positive mentality to better prepare them in their older age .
For example , when the government announced measures to encourage later retirements , the citizens will be prepared for what is to come and will be more readily to accept it and thus reducing elder dependency in the long term .
Secondly , by extending working lives , it will often results in the accumulation of more wealth which can be used to support themselves in the old age .
In addition , it acts as a safety net to dramatically reduce the need for elder dependency .
For example , an elderly who worked for 50 years compared to one that worked for 40 years has considerably more savings .
With the ability to work and also a sustainable income , elderly will find themselves less dependent on others .
Moreover , their experience gained can prove valuable to the economy .
For example , with increased measures from government for putting elderly into the workforce , the elderly will be able to depend on themselves .
All in all , the strategy on reducing elder dependency through the 3 methods can prove to be valuable for an aging society .
Once you are abroad , there is nothing you can do " , said Golda Meir .
Indeed , perhaps everyone is afraid of aging because it not only marks deterioration in physical health and significant psychological changes , but also places more financial burdens on the government and the society , because obviously , the elderly need fiscal support , better health care and facilities specialized for their elder problems .
One example of necessary financial support is the investment on developing and upgrading the current facilities used in education , including information technology equipment , laboratory and library system .
This is particularly important to developing and less-developed nations ' education , like Vietnam , China , Philippine and Malaysia , where teaching and learning are still following the traditional method with less support by IT and using old textbooks , as well as laboratories with obsolete devices .
Hence , students will be able to approach updated knowledge more easily , experiment and apply what they have learned in reality .
By providing tuition grants ( of 80 % ) and financial aid for living costs for foreign students along with a career bond , Singapore will have a greater workforce serving them for at least 3 years after graduation .
Another area that the government needs to concern is the environment as hundreds of environmental projects ( such as reducing the level of green house gases and noxious fumes in the atmosphere or promoting the use of non-plastic carrying bag ) are waiting for capital and fiscal support .
In such small nations ( in terms of geographical area ) like Singapore , this issue is particularly important because every climatic change or pollution problem is likely to negatively affect the whole country , especially physical health of people , including the aged .
Moreover , environment is a global concern ; it influences everybody in the world .
Thus , protecting it means we are protecting not only the young but also the elderly , not only the current generation , but also the future ones .
Besides the concerns about environmental protection and education , public spending on the aged should be partly transferred to public infrastructure development projects such as public transportation , schools , hospitals because such developments are directly related to the improvement in living standards of senior citizens .
Firstly , a modern infrastructure will bring about higher capabilities , effectiveness and efficiency .
One example of this could be the extension of access to most public places and even on public transport vehicles for people with physical disabilities , such as designing paths or elevators specialized for wheel chairs , or placing special directions for the elderly with sight or hearing problems .
Secondly , due to higher efficiency , such system will help reduce the operating expense and subsequently decrease the living expenditure for citizens .
For instance , a well organized public transportation system will help minimize the use of private vehicles which is costly , and reduce traffic congestion and accidents .
And therefore , to some extents , the elderly will indirectly benefit from this policy .
In conclusion , people may be upset with this idea because they may think that the aged increasingly lack of care from the society .
However , if considering the positive impacts it brings about the entire society , obviously the advantages will outweigh the disadvantages .
In Singapore , it 's no different .
As the population continue to age , government spending on the aged would increase as more and more people would rely on the government for their needs .
