Their ailments and conditions could be resulted from their work , be it directly or indirectly caused , while contributing to the nation progress , thus it should not be ignored .
Because of that , therefore it is only reasonable that the country should look after these past contributors and not to overlook their achievements just because they are no longer as capable of contributing to the nation .
As this move will reflect badly on how the country regards its citizen , it may even discourage its citizen from performing their best , or even migrate and work in other country , as they are aware that state will not take care of them in their later life .
To sum up , without a doubt diverting public spending from supporting the aged population to the other development in the country may at first seem to be the best option , but eventually , it could in turn result in more harm than good , be it by upsetting the balance of wealth in the country , educating of wrong moral value and conveying the wrong message to its citizen workforce .
With the development of society , governments and policy makers pay more attention to the phenomenon of aging populations , especially in developed countries .
According to incomplete figures , in the European countries , spending on pensions , health , and related issues is 15 % of GDP ( gross domestic product ) currently .
However , although the spending on the aged is high , it should not be limited .
Some consider that public spending on the aged should be limited so that money can be diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
For instance , government should cut down the spending on aged , and use more money to attract talented immigrants .
However , the result what we will do that is that many immigrants who have different cultural backgrounds will pour into the country .
One country with the great influx of immigrants will become unstable , since cultures are different and cultural fusion need a long period of time .
Hence , it is not necessary to limit the public spending on the aged for attracting talented immigrants .
On one hand , limiting the public spending on the aged does not mean that we can spend less money on the aged .
Some of the reasons mentioned are " reducing the share of public support does not eliminate societal costs " ( Robert B. Friedland and Laura Summer ) .
At the same time , cutting down public spending on aged will shift the financial pressure to the families with old people .
Therefore , we should not limit the public spending on the aged .
On the other hand , it should promote a sense of humanity and come up with more ways to help the vulnerable group and it is the duty of government that pays more attention to the vulnerable group in the society .
The aged belongs to the vulnerable group , as the productivity of the elderly is relatively low , but their medical expenses and social costs are higher than other age groups .
Thus , public support on the finance for the aged is extremely important .
In contrast , some may say that it is obligation for children to show filial obedience to the older generation , so young family members need to take care of the older generation and government can bear less responsibility for older people .
Due to this , the public spending on the aged should be limited .
If we just cut down the public spending on the aged and divert the money to other areas of the country 's development , this is contrary to the purpose of the government .
In other words , why do we divert the money to other areas of the country 's development ?
In consequence of the same aims , diverting the money to other areas of the country 's development is an extra and needless job .
In conclusion , public spending on the aged should not be limited so that money can be diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
However , it does not mean that the aged can totally dependent on government 's support .
The aged are advised to solve their problems as possible as they can and put the public support as their second choice .
" Although we are moving towards a a fast aging population , public spending should be limited and diverted to area like monetary reward to encourage parents to have more babies .
Besides , if we were to slow down the country 's development , this might hinder our economic growth which in turn , will affect the public spending on the aged indirectly .
As we are now facing the problem of a fast aging population , healthcare expenses incurred by the elderly needs funding .
Therefore , if public spending on the aged were to be limited , less budgets would be set aside for the elderly , which would affect them as healthcare is very important to them as they will face many health issues .
With the limitation of public spending on the aged , the elderly might not receive essential healthcare due to insufficient funding , which may leads to undesired outcome .
If public spending on the aged were to be limited and diverted to funds to encourage couples to have more babies , many people will plan to have more babies since their worries of not having enough money to bring up or to support so many babies have been partially subsidies by the fund .
As the increase in the fund for baby bonus leads to more people planning to have more babies , this would eventually reduce the problem of having too many elderly which make us move towards an aging society .
In this way , it indirectly reduces the problem of having to set aside a big amount of money to aid healthcare services for the elders .
Another reason to limit public spending on the aged is that the children of the elderly should pay for their parent 's healthcare expenses .
If the funding for the aged are limited , this will result in children bearing the responsibilities to look after their own parents .
As people can no longer depend on the society to look after their parents , they will have to take up the responsibilities of looking after their own parents .
In this way , people will be setting a good example to their children by looking after their own parents which would in turn indicate to their children that they should look after their parents in the future .
Although funding of healthcare services for the elderly is essential , it should be limited and diverted to other areas , especially baby bonus .
With more babies born , it would mean more people to look after their parents in the future , which would in turn cut down funds needed for the elderly .
In addition , having more babies will reduce our median age and also solve our problem of moving towards an aging population .
I do not agree with the statement that public spending on the aged should be limited so that money can be divided to other areas of the country 's development .
As Singapore 's population is aging , it is the best time to provide for them to provide for the aged .
Critics might think that as someone is aging , the person is can no longer provide for the society anymore .
Firstly , the elderly can provide for the society by imparting values to the younger generation .
The elderly has spent many years of their youth on this earth .
Therefore they are in the best position to impart values to their children as they are the wisest person each family .
Furthermore , even if someone is old , they can still provide for the society in terms of decision making .
With the amount of life experiences , they will know the consequences of implementing different kinds of solution .
A very good example is our former prime minister , Mr Lee Kuan Yew .
Despite of his old age , he still contributes to the society by making major decisions for the country .
This shows that an elderly is never a useless person in the society .
On the other hand , they are the ones who can make the wisest decisions .
In addition to the above mentioned factors , the elderly has already contributed many years of their youth to the society .
If not for them , Singapore will never become a developed country .
In conclusion , I do not agree that public spending on the aged should be limited so that money can be divided to other areas of the country 's development .
The elderly can contribute to the society by using their life experiences to make important decision for the country .
This may seem impossible but it can be made possible if each elderly begins imparting these values to their own children .
In due time , Singapore will become the safest county that can make the best decision .
Until recently , there is always much concern about the consequences of over spending on the welfare of the aging population .
Although , the welfare of the senior citizen may be important but it should not be in an extent where the other areas of the country 's development are being hindered .
What is therefore needed is to take a close look at the current situation and evenly distribute the public spending into different areas to ensure that the country is being able to prosper .
If the government does not invest enough on these areas , the country will lose its competitiveness , productive capacity in the economy and decrease in public services which will greatly harm the economy .
Education is a need to educate the future workforce of the economy , and also to create a workforce which is truly competitive and productive .
Japan is a country with little natural resources and yet with a very highly educated population , which resulted them in being one of the most foremost and advanced country in the world .
A population with poor education background will find it hard to compete with other foreign talents with quality education background , thus losing out when it comes to employment and resulting in a huge percentage of the population being unemployed .
Furthermore , foreign investors will not set up factories in countries that are equipped with poorly educated workforce .
Thus the importance of education is equally important .
Singapore is a country who is constantly being the target of the terrorist .
There were several terror attempts on Singapore , but it was foiled mainly due to the contribution from an effective and strong defense system .
For example , New York City was once a major financial center in the world , but after since the September 11th incident , majority of the investors left New York seeking safer alternatives .
This particular incident costs New York billions of dollars and also millions of job lost overnight .
Singapore being a small country and yet having one of the strongest economies in Asia has always been the target its neighboring countries .
Therefore , defense is one of the most important areas which safeguards interest of a country and the allocation of budget on this area should never be overlooked .
Critics often said that the senior citizens were the country 's pioneer and they had been through the process of nation building and it is our responsibility to ensure that the welfare of the aged should never be overlooked .
For the financially strapped elderly , they will receive the necessary subsidies for medical cost , transportation cost from the government .
Therefore , for those who are financially capable will have to rely only on their retirement savings .
Otherwise , it would be a huge drain on the tax payer 's money which will not be utilized to its maximum potential .
Clearly , public spending on the aged is required , but other areas which will affect the development of the country are also equally important , if not to say more important .
With this ever changing and competitive society , Singapore needs to make the necessary investments on other areas to ensure that it remains its foothold in the global economy .
If we do not limit the spending on the aged , Singapore may risk the possibility of losing its current global recognition status that it has always had .
With the current research and development and policies , I agree this has helped to ease the aging process to a large extend .
This has indeed become a global problem with the extensive number of medical research going on and the various policies that are being developed .
Thus in the next few paragraphs , I will explain in depth on the various research and government policies being developed has help to ease the aging process .
An example is that there has been quite a number research on the kind of food which one consumes will help to slow the aging process .
An example of the previous sentence is a research done by Pusan National University in Korea stating that eating kimchi could reduce the risk of heart disease and slows the aging process by reducing the amount of oxygen the body burns ( Hankook Ilbo , 2000 ) .
Another discovery in a research was found in the last few years that drinking red wine in moderation helps to preserve good health and slows the aging process .
This is because of red wine contains a substance known as " resveratol " .
" Resveratrol " is considered to be so effective when it comes to slowing the aging process is due to the amount of [ pic ] antioxidants that are present within it .
It is these free radicals that wreak havoc within our bodies due to the fact they damage cells , which not only causes disease but also aging .
Thus , one can see how extensive these research are being carried out to ease the aging process of mankind .
Secondly , the government has come out with various policies to ease the aging process .
As a Singaporean , we all know of a term called " CPF " .
The government also implemented the " Minimum Sum Policy " to ensure that one have a specific amount in his or her CPF before allowing them to withdraw at the age of 55 .
At the end of April 2007 , 411 companies have already adopted the scheme .
This shows how effective the government pushes the policy .
Therefore , one could hardly see how the policies do not help to ease the aging process .
Controversially , citizens have argued that these policies do not help them in the aging process because it has taken a toll in their gross salary after having money deducted to their " CPF " contributions which makes monthly living allowances even lesser for them .
An example is the raise of the " Minimum Sum " scheme .
This has been proven to be untrue as majority of Singaporeans supports the " CPF " schemes which encourages safer retirement and there are many citizen who even went to sign up more policies from the government on their own accord .
Finally to conclude , due to the fact of a globally aging population , various research and development carried out to slow down the aging process and the policies implemented by the government for late retirement .
It is hard to see how these research and policies does not help to ease the aging process in the modern day context .
In present day Singapore , the number of ageing people continues to rise at an alarming rate due to the high fertility rate in the past .
With the sharp decline of birth rates that we are facing now , majority of Singaporeans will be faced with harder task- in taking care of elderly family members .
" There are three areas that we will discuss that are contributions that elderly have made the different needs and problems of the aged and the responsibility within the children .
In the past , Singapore was an under developed country with swamps and kampongs around the island .
If not for the elderly members of Singapore who contributed in helping to mould Singapore into a highly developed country , today many will not be enjoying the fruits of the labor .
Ageing is viewed as an inevitable phase of life that we are compelled to live .
Despite the challenges surrounding the ageing society , it is still depicted as the best part of our lives - 'the golden years' .
One policy mentioned to deal with the financial challenges of an ageing population is to enforce a compulsory saving scheme for citizen old age .
Alike with many countries around the world , the Singapore government has implemented the Central Provident Fund ( CPF ) whereby a fixed percentage of its citizens ' salaries is set aside to the fund .
However , some may argue that no matter how large the nest-egg one has carefully managed to put by , the sum is not sufficient to cover the rising cost of everyday life and healthcare services .
As a solution , government also invests a considerable amount of resources in health promotion and disease prevention .
It is regrettable that when we think of old age , what automatically come to mind are visions of loneliness and neglect .
These studios are built in such a way that it allows for elderly to be independent .
Some facilities include the construction of lifts at every floor instead of alternate floors and the installment of elder-friendly features such as non-slip tiles and grab bars .
Railing , ramps and passage way access to building are also made available .
With this , elder who have difficulty walking can get help by holding on to railing and at the same time exercise their leg muscles .
Ramps are also built for those wheelchair bound so that they can go in and out of the building without any help .
Children may not find the need to visit as they assume that the elderly have already had proper care .
Another problem faced is the lack of public recognition of life-long and continuing contributions of older people to the human .
Earlier , those who have reached a ripe old age held an enviable place in society , but now they are only seen as senile , frail and useless old people .
This will not only make them feel worthy , the continued employment also enhances their financial security .
The elderly would feel more at east knowing that there are helps provided for them in their twilight years .
Singapore may suffer from long term economic loss while possible government support for the elderly could cost a portion of its Gross Domestic Product ( GDP ) to decline .
To deal with the limitation of public spending for the aged , a budget amount should be set aside to allow enough funds to be used for building and developing infrastructures , creating employment opportunities and improving standard of living to benefit the nation , as well as to increase its economy and its GDP .
Firstly , by having more funds , Singapore can build and develop new infrastructures .
Public transportation systems including light rail system , mass rapid transit system , as well as the current new railway network , Circle line , are well advanced to make the public accessible to any locations in Singapore .
Constructing of overhead bridges and expressways has made the citizens benefit too .
Currently , the government has set aside an amount to build integrated resorts , the casino , and tourism attractions to attract tourists to come to Singapore .
This would enable foreign money to come in and improve the economy .
Having hotels , shopping centers , transportations or other amenities would generate improve economy .
Tourists got to spend their money on accommodation in hotels , shopping and entertainment , food and beverages in restaurants , cultural shows and souvenirs and transportation would generate foreign money .
Employment opportunities would then be created to the local people such as hotel attendants , tour guides are needed .
Thus , these people need to be hired and they can contribute to the society and sustain the economy .
Lastly , the government can use funds to improve standard of living for the citizens such as to build more schools to provide better education , have advanced healthcare technology so that citizens can enjoy the excellent healthcare services , etc. With such rising affluences , people would expect a better quality of life .
Given the current situation , most of the people in Singapore would able to go beyond meeting their basic needs such as food , shelter , water , electric power supply sanitation health care and education .
If there 's an improvement in Singapore 's economy , Citizens would receive high income to have good food , modern housing .
When people have an improved standard of living they will be able to contribute and sustain the economy .
Even though with the help from the government and fund raising campaigns set up by charity organizations , there will be still a sizeable segment of the population the government has to consider to continue to aid the aged .
With the rising cost of basic necessities and medical costs due to inflation in the future , those with no or low income aged group will suffer as these factors will cause the elderly not having enough savings or income to overcome the current economic climate .
Another point is that the elderly in their younger age may have contributed for the society and the economy .
Therefore , the government has to play a part to help the aged if they have any difficulties financially or in any other ways .
In conclusion , an aging population may decline Singapore 's economy .
However , since the elderly in their younger age may have contributed for the society and the economy , we should spend a certain amount of money for their needs if they have problems dealing with money issues .
But , the amount must be balanced and have to take into consideration for other needs such as improving and developing infrastructures , creating employment opportunities and the rising standard of living of the nation .
The extent to which limitations of public spending on the aged has always been a complicated issue in many developed countries .
Over spending may result in a shortage of resources in the development of the nation while under spending may imply a negligence of government towards the aged .
We will discuss on the differences on whether to limit the public spending of the aged .
Upon having better technology and infrastructure developments , the country will be able to attract more Multinational Corporations ( MNCs ) to invest , and thus increasing job opportunities .
For example , Singapore had attracted MNCs such as Las Vegas Sands Corp. and Genting International & Star Cruises to invest in the tourism sector .
Integrated Resorts ( IR ) that are built will generate an approximate of 50,000 to 60,000 additional jobs .
Hence , it can be clearly seen that with limitations to public spending on the aged , the money diverse to other areas can help in boosting the economy condition of the country .
Secondly , there is no transparency in regards to the distribution of public spending .
Since no publications are made known , tax payers may be doubtful about the usage of their payable taxes .
People may make use of charity opportunities to obtain money from public and use for their own personal benefits .
For example in recent news , Ren Ci ex-director had been embroiled in a complicated money scandal .
It was reported that the ex-director was supposed to loan an amount to Mandala Buddhist Cultural Centre but it ended up with his former personal aide .
This incident led to the distrust of public towards charity organizations .
As a consequence , there was a dramatic drop in the Ren Ci donations from 9.3 million to 1.1 million .
Limitations and transparency can be made to gain back the confidence level towards public spending .
Thirdly , another reason to limit the public spending on the aged will be that the aged population today is different from the past .
Many of them are within the top management in the corporate ladders .
They hold high post such as Chief Executive Officer ( CEO ) , Chief Operating Officer etc .
They are capable of taking care of their lives and do not need the government aids .
For this reason that the aged population are able to take care of themselves , public spending can be limited so that it can be invested to other areas for enhanced development .
Finally , without limitations on public spending on the aged , it will lead to an increase in dependency on the public spending by the aged .
Apparently , some aged will try to abuse the public spending policy .
They will have this mindset that since government will be taking care of their lives , why would they need to work .
However , they may be a small minority of aged who are physically unfit to work .
Hence limitations on public spending should be implemented so that only this needy group of the aged will be the only recipients .
In conclusion , with proper limitations on public spending on the aged , the excess money can be made to the development of country thus improving its economy conditions .
Aged population will also be encouraged to take care of themselves instead of over-relying on public spending .
In the modern societies , the aging population is increasing as a truth which can not be denied .
Therefore , the government should consider carefully about the way to treat this special kind of citizens .
