The use of psychology in design processes reduces problem by enabling an engineer to consider the pros and cons of his decision .
The use of psychology would seek to improve engineering designs by preventing the human errors associated with the process .
As more engineers feel stressful from their high workload , psychologist plays an important role in their work .
Designing products should considering psychological factors for consumers and operators .
An inadequate industrial design may lead catastrophic consequences .
( Bernhard , 2006 ) Many people argue that psychology is non-related with engineering design ; companies do not need to spend extra money on the unnecessary outcome .
Human error has been recognized as the main reason for industry accidents ; psychology can prevent human error happening .
( Woods , 1994 )
The amount is a large outcome .
Three Mile Island accident was resulted by human error and design problems ( Backgrounder on The Three Mile Island Accident , 2009 ) .
The whole factory was in ruin , all the residents living in the villages that close to the Three Mile Island must move away .
It is much expensive then S $ 144000 , and thousands of lives were threatened .
People who do not agree that psychology is useful in engineer work demonstrate the purpose of engineering design .
The engineering design is to apply technologies to help people solving problems .
The issue of how to attract consumers is none business with engineers .
Furthermore , they think the job of design engineer is to build factory structure , how to operate is something belongs to operators .
It sounds correct in some extent .
Depending on Prof. Dominic 's Journal , engineers must consider safe factors when they design the structure .
( Dominic , 2002 ) The safe factors include psychological component .
If the arrangements of products and instructions are incomprehensible and complicated , purchasers will be confused when using these gadgets .
( Bernhard , 2006 ) If people do not like using the product , the product is a failure .
Design engineers always overestimate the ability of users ; the design may not give sufficient help to operators .
( Bernhard , 2006 ) Three Mile Island 's tragic consequence is caused by the inadequate structure design .
When the radioactive gas and coolant were leaked , the valve should be closed immediately in order to prevent radioactive materials draining away .
The operator thought that the valve has been closed , but there is no instrument showing the position of valve .
( Three Mile Island 1979 , 2001 ) Then this accident happened .
If designers have designed an instrument to show the process of cooling circuit , then operators may know that the valve had not been closed , and this disaster may be prevented .
People hold the opposite views insist that psychologists can help engineers release their high working pressures out of company .
The work efficiency is different when people work in different feelings .
Psychology can help them to have an active attitude and optimistic emotions to work .
Psychology has prevented accident happened in some extent , it has guaranteed the workers ' mental health .
Incorporate the Psychological factors when they designing products is convenient for purchasers to use .
Furthermore , psychologists can persuade engineers to have good attitude towards their work and help engineers to release their pressures .
Nuclear power deserve the research funding
This is resulted from the emissions of greenhouse gas , such as carbon dioxide , in energy generation using fossil fuels .
As a result , there is an urgent need to find substitute for coal and oil .
Under such circumstances , scientists and engineers find out a new kind of energy-nuclear energy .
According to Butler ( 2004 ) , partial reactor melted down in 1979 at Three Mile Island , Pennsylvania , and of the 1986 accident at Chernobyl in Ukraine , during which the reactor core exploded , killing some 31 people immediately [ 1 ] .
Moreover , " Laws and statues exist in most countries to ensure the safe operation of nuclear plant " ( Lillington , 2004 ) [ 2 ] .
Hence , security of nuclear energy generation can be guaranteed and it is no need to worry too much about security .
According to Stephens ( 2006 ) , the US spends $ 1 billion on FutureGen project which aims at development of carbon capture and storage technologies ( CCS ) [ 3 ] .
In addition , the global warming effects may result in droughts which will reduce crop production and air pollution can result in acid rain which can corrode many properties .
Substitute must be found before fossil fuel is totally run out .
In conclusion , the opposition reasons of nuclear power technology can be overthrow .
The nuclear power technology can solve not only environmental problem caused by the combustion of fossil fuel , but also energy shortage at low cost and in environmental-friendly way .
Many skeptics oppose the idea of building nuclear reactors as they fear similar incident to that in Chernobyl might happen again .
However , I believe this is not very likely as supercritical-water-cooled reactor is designed differently to avoid such incident from reoccurring .
This reactor back then work on a positive void coefficient of reactivity .
CITATION Sat08 \ l 1033 ( Baindur , 2008 ) This makes the skeptics ' worry redundant as the structure is designed to specifically operate under the high temperature and pressure .
Lastly , the benefits that a supercritical-water-cooled reactor could bring make it worth further researching and funding into the reactor .
The reactor is much more efficient than conventional light water reactors : the supercritical-water-cooled reactor has a thermal efficiency of 45 % which is approximately one-third higher than that of conventional light water reactors CITATION Sat08 \ l 1033 ( Baindur , 2008 ) .
Among the six prototypes of nuclear reactors designed , the very-high-temperature reactor ( VHTR ) is one of the most promising candidates proposed in the GIF .
( Umeda , 2008 ) However , many people strongly oppose this new prototype due to their inherent fear about nuclear plants .
( GIF Forum ) Moreover , this technology has been furthermore improved to meet higher temperature requirement .
For example , Japan 's Atomic Energy Research Institute based in Kashiwa has already operated a similar reactor as the VHTR which is able to reach a record high temperature of 950 Degree Celsius in 2004 .
( Butler , 2004 ) Therefore , developing materials that resist high temperatures is no longer a problem for building the VHTR .
The core of the VHTR with multiple protection layers inside is able to withstand stresses at temperatures up to 1600 Â° C without cracking .
( Rachael Elder & Ray Allen , 2008 ) Thus the VHTR will be a very safe prototype given it multiple protection layers and effective backup system .
Moreover , waste reprocessing is expensive and fuel consuming as it requires continuous burning of the wastes .
( Declan , 2004 ) Therefore , the benefits of not reprocessing the waste overweigh the costs of storing the waste .
