The development of nuclear weapons has being condemned by several countries and organizations like the U.N ( United Nations ) .
Although some might claimed that the security of these nuclear resources will not be misuse , however it is almost impossible to guard against such cases ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Moreover , the ever increasing risk of terrorism will result in a much threatening situation if nuclear weapon is been stolen .
It is unimaginable the amount of damage that will occur if the terrorists are able to get their hand on a nuclear power plant .
In fact this is not true at all .
The amount of money that is required to build these is usually an astrological amount ( James , 2002 ) .
Not to mention there are many underlying cost such as the nuclear plant maintenance fee , the land required to build a reactor and the waste management system .
The maintenance fee that is required for each nuclear reactor is much higher than for a conventional energy plant as the safety measures for these plants are much more detailed since it is handling highly reactive substances .
After a certain amount of usages or a period of time , a nuclear reactor will have to be decommissioned and the cost incurred is not only just large sum of money , land spaces are needed too .
All these costs incurred by the nuclear reactor is much more hurting to the economics rather than easing the financial factor for countries .
In conclusion , all the following aspects such as the security , safety and costs component for a nuclear reactor indicates far more disadvantages and risks compared to the advantages that nuclear reactor brings about .
Thus , in my view , there are much better technology and energy than nuclear power around , so there should be more emphasis and support for other technologies .
