So , it is easy to find that after long period of running , the total cost of VHTR will not exceed that of other existing reactors any more .
In conclusion , the VHTR has own safety features , such as very high system temperature , enhanced reliability , low system pressure and so on .
The similarities between these two reactors are both using helium as a coolant , no need working at high pressure and producing same output of hydrogen and electricity .
We will be comparing which reactors should have more emphasis to have further research and development funding for it .
the waste material produced by GCFR is being recycled .
So a higher operating temperature of VHTR would allow for more electricity to be produced as compared to gas cooled reactors .
Not only that , the waste material being produced by gas cooled fast reactors is pure plutonium and this material is mainly used for weapon making .
Such system does not exist in gas cooled reactors that operates at lower temperature .
In the event of sudden shutdown due to malfunction , VHTR still can produce energy .
It is especially useful for country like France , which 80 % of the electricity generated is dependent on nuclear energy .
For GCFR , there is a presence of safe accommodation of low thermal inertia and poor heat transfer properties of coolant .
In terms of cost , for VHTR , it can be implemented five years earlier than the gas cooled fast reactors .
( Butler 2004 ) Currently , there are no operators for the GCFR in the current market .
At the meanwhile , the globle warming and other environmental concerns are pushing the entire world to some more powerful , sustainable and clean solutions for future energy .
Our future method should also be safty , economic , efficient and flexble for applications .
Firstly , the main public concern on nuclear power is its safty .
The molten salt reactant has a advantage in this aspect .
( [ pic ] Mathieu , L.,2006 ) Although MSR work in relatively high tempreture it can still be stable,for example , for FUJI-12 , The maximum fuel temperature for two rod insertions of 0.344 % dk/k was 1220K at the rated power .
Therefore it worth more research on its development .
People hardly link engineering problems with psychology since the previous one belongs to pure technology problems while the later one is a branch of social science .
However , as time comes along , psychology is gradually applied in various fields , including law , medicine , architecture , design and so on .
People nowadays have fierce controversy over the use of nuclear power due to the appalling nuclear accidents happened at Three Mile island and Chernobyl , or even the recent nuclear accident at Sellafield , England .
These accidents destroy cities , take people 's lives and leave many deadly post-effects in the future decades .
Therefore , facing this benefit , safety becomes the main concern when people choose to continue using nuclear power .
Even though SCWR has not been tested yet , it is proved to have less possibility to cause nuclear accidents that happened before ; it is easier to implement compared to other generation VI reactors , and it has a relatively high thermal efficiency which makes its long-term cost relatively low .
The nuclear accident happened at Chernobyl was mainly because the nuclear plant utilized positive void coefficient of reactivity , causing it impossible to stop the working process when things went wrong .
( Bodansky , 2004 ) On the contrary , SCWR uses negative void coefficient instead , which could effectively reduce the possibility of this kind of fatal accidents ( U.S DOE Nuclear Energy Research Advisory Committee & the Generation IV International Forum , 2002 ) .
The other is supercritical fossil fuel fired boilers , which is also under use now ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2007 ) .
To sum up , although there exists disagreement of the use of SCWR due to its issue of reliability and safety , SCWR is worthy for further research because it bases on two current technologies , which increases its reliability , and its design principle improves its thermal efficiency compared to LWR and reduce the possibility of causing nuclear accidents .
Hopefully , SCWR could be better improved on current problems in the future development .
Given the memories of the two accidents happened in 1979 at Three Mile Island in Pennsylvania and in 1986 at Chernobyl of Ukraine , some people may still have not recovered from the great horror when they hear nuclear power .
On one hand , people are facing the challenge of energy shortage because fossil fuels are nonrenewable .
On the other hand , burning fossil fuels produces the " green gases " such as carbon dioxide that have resulted serious problems like global warming .
One is that the reactor and the gas turbine system are separated from hydrogen production plant , which is aimed to isolate the hydrogen plant from reactor system during the abnormal events of hydrogen production plant .
To conclude , it should be evident the arguments against the safety and cost of VHTR are invalid .
Since VHTR uses helium as coolant , the research of the materials for VHTR is also ongoing , and also there are unique designs for VHTR , the safety of VHTR would be enhanced a lot .
Furthermore , VHTR produces hydrogen as future fuel , which is environment-friendly and can effectively solve the energy shortage as well .
Therefore , VHTR is the promising and practical power .
Firstly , the VHTR has a core outlet temperature of about 1000 degrees Celsius this high temperature increases the efficiency of reactor and also enables us to use it for applications such as hydrogen production ( VHTR , Generation IV technology forum ) .
The hydrogen produced can be used in automobiles , which in turn help decrease the carbon emissions by 30 % when compared to modern day diesel engines ( Jack Ewing , Business Week , September 2009 ) .
This is the same material which is being used in the Japanese , South African and Chinese high temperature test reactors ( Bill Corwin , US Department of Energy , 2003 ) and has proven to be very successful .
The VHTR is designed to operate on a pebble bed core in which the fuel is coated with silicon carbide which ensures that the radioactive fissile material never leaves fuel spheres or pebbles ( Andrew C.Kadak , MIT study on the future of nuclear energy ) .
The reactor is helium cooled and uses graphite moderated core , which takes advantage of the fact that the helium coolant is inert and has no reactivity effects and that graphite has a high thermal inertia and is stable at high temperatures ( VHTR , Idaho National Laboratory ) .Also , any waste produced goes directly to the repository and this means an additional waste recycling process can be avoided ( Butler , Nuclear Power 's New Dawn , 2004 ) .Thus , in case of any failure the damage does not spread to the surrounding regions but is contained within the plant itself .
Lastly , most of the technology involved in the VHTR is already in its development phase and the reactor can be shelled out as early as 2020 Butler , Nuclear Power 's New Dawn , 2004 ) .
There was a train disaster occurred on 3 June 1998 near a small town in Lower Saxony , Germany .
Such a super fast , state-of-the-art Inter Express trains of German Railways rolled out of tracks and split in two , due to a bridge falling onto the train .
It resulted 101 dead and 88 injured .
Although there were many causes to be pointed out to cause this train accident , I think the biggest cause is that no one is aware of the importance of the use of psychology during the design process .
It was reported that the directly cause was a wheel with a composite construction which is relatively common on light railway transit vehicles , but are unique to ICE 884 in high speed trains replaced the original wheel .
It can not be denied that this is a human mistake which can be avoided by applying the psychology .
Psychology can make engineers aware that they are not only the normal person , but also are professionals .
If they understand that , I believe that the engineers would not use those composite construction wheels and wheels which have not been checked properly and approved that can be used without any potential problems .
Observing the pictures which recorded the scene of accident , there at least one of the cars detached its underframe .
If designers considered more about that for the high-speed trains must take into account the forces to be absorbed in the event of the vehicle being in a collision , there would not be so many people who were thrown through the air to injure , even die .
Only considering the constructions of train is not enough , the environmental element can affect result as well .
The designers never anticipate that a bridge which was expected a lightly used , demanded a less substantial structure than if it were to carry a major trunk road fell onto the ICE 884 to split it in two .
They completely ignored environmental element which was the speed and weight of the train passing under the bridge as a result of such a horrible disaster .
To sum up , any design process is applied psychology can minimize a probability of danger , even can avoid .
Because all design processes are to fulfill needs of human ; and all products are produced by human .
Therefore , anything as long as people-oriented will get the biggest benefits .
Of course , can avoiding accident occurred is the biggest benefits for people .
The Chernobyl accident that happened on 26 April 1986 , has led everyone to realize the damages and consequences that we might face when we built a nuclear power plant .
The six nuclear reactors are not only sustainable and economically viable solutions ; they are also safe and reliable source of energy .
Among the six concepts of nuclear reactors , the Very High Temperature Reactor , ( VHTR ) and the Gas Cooled Fast Reactor , ( GCFR ) are quite similar , but has more benefits than VHTR in terms of performance , sustainability and cost .
[ European Union ( EU ) Energy Research , 2009 ] GCFR is a concept which uses the reference design of VHTR , thus it is also a reactor of high performance .
Since GCFR operates at 850 degrees Celsius , therefore there are more choices of materials that can be used in the construction of GCFR .
[ Idaho National Laboratory , 2002 ] Because GCFR operates at a lower temperature as compare to the VTHR , therefore the materials used for construction is cheaper and there are more choices of material available .
[ Generation IV International Forum , 2009 ] The reduction of radioactive waste uses processes called pryo-chemical or hydrometallurgical .
[ Commissariat Ã  l'energie atomique , 2007 ] With this there is a great reduction of nuclear waste , and money can be saved on building a storage site for nuclear waste .
Therefore , GCFR not only can have efficient energy conversion with the current design but also has an economic benefit outcome .
In conclusion , although the there are several advantages of the VHTR but however there are factors that makes it difficult to implement as it is more expensive and limited by choices of construction materials as compared with the GCFR .
Nonetheless , the decision to implement the reactors still falls in the hands of the countries that are highly interested as budget for every country is different .
Nowadays , since the fossil fuel is running out at a very high rate , people are seeking another alternative energy resource to replace the traditional fossil fuel resources , which have been used by human for hundreds of years .
However , public is very concern about the safe operation of nuclear reactors .
This is because that once a nuclear reactor accident happened , it would be a huge disaster to both the creatures and the environment within that area .
A very famous accident , which is also used by public to oppose building nuclear reactors , is the accident at Chernobyl which happened on 26 April 1986 .
Moreover , according to the estimation , there would be thousands of people dead from cancer in the next forty years .
Another famous example is the accident happening at the nuclear power station at Three Mile Island in Pennsylvania on 28 March 1979 .
Furthermore , as the technology has improved so much , even an accident happens , the damage is probably not that big .
For example , in the Three Mile Island accident , nobody was either dead or injured .
Besides safety , economy is also a very important aspect which people should take into consideration .
However , since we can eliminate the need for an intermediate heat transport circuit in lead-cooled fast reactors , and lead is relatively cheap comparing with other materials used in other fast reactors , a large part of cost would be saved through this .
Chernobyl explosion is one example showing the seriousness of those dangers .
Chernobyl accident , happened in 1986 , was a nuclear reactor accident .
CITATION Int08 \ l 2052 ( International Atomic Energy Agency , 2008 ) Because of that , the safety of engineering design is very important .
In current stage , most design team uses the safety laws and rules as their gatekeeper and thinks that is enough .
However , some psychologists argues that those rules are not enough as all the procedures are carried out by human , there is possibility that a human error may occur .
Therefore psychologists are necessary to be involved in the design process to detect the human error and to be the new gate keeper of engineering design .
Chernobyl accident can be a good example to see how the use of psychology helps to prevent the accident .
However , though with such rules , accidents still happens consecutively all those years .
This of course implies some imperfect of the safety gatekeepers now .
CITATION Ber06 \ l 2052 ( Wilpert , 2006 ) Those human factors mainly include the irresponsibility of operators and human error during the design process .
Chances are this accident may not happen .
To follow up , some designers may also consider that a team member without strong technical background may become a disturbance during work or decreases the efficiency of the team .
Therefore they may cause more problem than they can solve .
However , in present engineering groups , team members are always from different majors .
This is because that today 's design requires consideration from all aspects .
A team with single major can not satisfy such requirements therefore will lose the ability to compete with others .
Considering all those facts , a psychology can never be a disturbance in the team .
Rather than , the presence of psychologist in a team can keep the members work at their best condition and avoiding the chance of having human error in design process .
By doing this , hopefully there are chances to prevent accidents because of misuse caused by the misunderstanding of instructions , like the operator in the Chernobyl accident .
However , considering the serious results of Chernobyl accidents and other engineering accidents , such wondering is of no point .
In conclusion , psychologists may become new gatekeepers of engineering design process by helping correct the human error in design process and increase the team efficiency .
And the increasing safety will make people enjoy the benefits of engineering design products much better .
Some insist that insights can be gained when analyzing design process using psychological approach .
No matter what the designers are to work on , complex systems or everyday products , psychology is helpful to gain insights of problems that may be encountered or prevent undesirable accidents .
For everyday products design , it is quite understandable that if the technical configurations are similar for all , psychology could help designers make a difference by humanly consider making improvements that are more user-friendly in design .
More impactful consequences of not applying psychology in design are that serious failures can happen in complex projects and systems hence cause loss of life .
For instance , the collapse of Nicall Highway , two stretches of highway road linked by Merdeka Bridge , located in the Central Region of Singapore ( Vernon , 2000 ) , could have been prevented if psychological approach were adopted in the design and construction process .
For the Nicoll Highway incident , some argue that it is merely constrained by technology and only causes are engineering problems .
While it is true that the restrictions set by technology limitations are direct cause for the engineering failure , the application of psychology could help to overcome the negative effects of technology difficulties .
Numerous journals written by engineers and professionals analyzing this disaster were all very absorbed by civil engineering details and theories after Nicoll Highway collapsed , but the disaster was concluded to be unexpected as technology should have been sufficient for this construction project ( Thansnanipan & Aung , 2005 ) .
This means that it is not shortcomings in technology that necessarily lead to engineering failure , but lack of psychological analysis .
When some were arguing for objective difficulties in technology , it was admitted by the main contractor that major cause is the overload temporary works and their low quality ( New Civil Engineer , 2005 ) .
The contractor admitted that they had foreseen the potential problems that might be caused due to overloading temporary work and their reckless plan , but they somehow still did not pay enough attention and continued with it .
The primary goals being to improve nuclear safety , efficient thermal performance , reducing cost .
Many reactors are considered to design to meet the generation IV goals today .
Two of the generation IV reactors called Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor and Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor are highly appreciated and accepted in modern nuclear power plant system .
In terms of performance , security , cost , both of two reactors are well designed .
( M.J. Lineberry & T.R. Allen , 2002 ) Comparing with the Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor , Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor has the thermal efficiency about 48 % , which is generally higher than sodium-cooled fast reactor .
van Rooijen , 2009 ) In addition , under the high performance , both of two reactors need to work under high temperature .
In thermal performance , both of two reactors have quite nice feature especially for energy conversion ; Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor may have additional advantages .
Then , it is a primary system that operated near atmospheric pressure .
Meanwhile , Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor is based on safety countermeasures for self-controlled shutdown function and controlling function .
( M.J. Lineberry & T.R. Allen , 2002 ) For Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor , it not only includes basic self safety control function but also many safety approaches are applied to the system to make it work safely under high temperature with additional safety devices being added to the equipment .
Recent research and development with depth studies for safety case , the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor system has been demonstrated experimentally in security aspect .
Newton & P.J. Smith , 2007 ) Hence , it is safer when works properly .
Furthermore , in terms of cost , Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor enhanced economics achieved with the use of high burn-up fuels , fuel cycle benefits .
It uses advanced materials and innovative design options to reduce in power plant capital cost and lower operating cost .
However , Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor is also well designed especially for waste recycling ; GFR tries to minimize the release of gaseous and liquid effluents to environment .
GFR system is designed to allow for self-treatment by applying fuel manufacturing operations .
In conclusion , both of Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor and Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor achieve generation IV primary goal to satisfy the requirement of energy .
Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor works with quite good thermal efficiency under a lower temperature when compares to Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor .
Moreover , it is designed well in safety case and cost aspect .
Similarly , GFR system offers significant potential to advance generation IV sustainability goals through its thermal efficiency , direct energy conversion , safety arrangement and proper cost .
Over all , Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor has advantages over Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor with respect to thermal efficiency , security case and cost .
According to Cambridge Advanced Learner 's Dictionary , the word " accident " means something bad which happens that is not expected or intended , and which often damages something or injures someone .
Let us have a quick scan through one of the world 's deadliest high-speed train accident- the Eschede train disaster , which hit a death toll of 101 .
Post accident investigation has shown that the main factors that contribute to this severe train accident are the wheel design of the train , maintenance of the train , and failure to stop the train .
Could this accident have probably been prevented if the usage of psychology as proposed by Bernhard Wilpert in " Psychology and design processes " is being applied ?
Psychology is the study of the behavior of human 's mind .
In most of the accidents , the main causes are errors in human judgments or simply known as the human problems .
For example , the faulty design of " wheel-tire " in the Eschede incident .
As Wilpert mentioned in his article , human can make mistakes .
Psychologists might make mistakes but at least they can lower the probability of errors caused by human 's irresponsible act or carelessness .
Besides that , it is found that accidents are usually caused by chain reactions of a series of factors according to Heinrich Domino theory .
In the case of Eschede train accident for instance , if the wheel of the train was designed in a better way or well maintained , or if the train could be stopped at the right moment before the crash , the accident could probably be avoided .
But on the other hand , not all factors are within the control of human 's capability .
Bad weather conditions , earthquake , and et cetera are all hard to be predicted .
It is quite true that these factors are beyond human 's control but we do not have to prevent them from happening .
All we have to do is taking all the necessary steps and precautionary methods to prevent these " uncontrollable " from triggering an accident .
As mentioned in the very first paragraph , accident is usually unexpected .
Moments before the accident of Eschede happened , one of the passengers on the train had noticed that the tire on a wheel broke and peeled away from the wheel , punctured the floor of the train .
He informed the conductor about what he saw but the conductor insisted to further investigate the incident and thus refused to pull the emergency brake .
Psychologically , the conductor did not want to be involved with any troubles because pulling the emergency brake would definitely cause much hassles .
If he chose to give safety the most priority , he would have pulled the emergency brake and the accident could probably be prevented .
However , when things come to emergency , the most important thing is often the individual ability to react rationally to resolve the problem .
The more one gets trained , the more readily he is to face an emergency .
Concisely , the approach of psychological knowledge can prevent or at least reduce the probability of accidents occurring .
Studies of human behavior , stages of an accident , investigation on industrial accident , together with some necessary and suitable psychological approach would definitely help in minimizing the occurring of severe accidents , especially those that are due to errors in human judgments .
The drastic industrial development and advancement in science and technology has led to the rising energy demand nowadays .
The invention of Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) is one of the latest Generation VI nuclear reactors that have high potential to replace the coal and fuel as energy source .
Nonetheless , debate on the using of this nuclear reactor becomes a hot issue today due to the negative effects that would be brought to human as well as other living organisms on the earth .
First and foremost , Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) has good security system and is safe to be used.TS Much have been said about the danger of using nuclear reactors as power generators such as emission and leakage of radioactive waste and explosion of nuclear reactor , where Chernobyl and Three Mile Island emerge to be famous for that reason .
Furthermore , this reactor 's pressure vessel is incorporated a core arrangement with three passes to avoid overheating effect and thus , minimizing the probability of the explosion of SWCR .
Moreover , the cost of construction of Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) and cost of its power output are cheap and reasonable.TS It is undeniable that uranium oxide , the main input for SWCR , and the construction materials used are expensive .
Although uranium oxide is expensive , it has a very long half life , about 24000 years .
Last but not least , Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) has high efficiency in term of electricity and power generation.TS According to Nuclear Engineering and Design ( 2007 ) , Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) promises to have high thermal efficiencies of approximately 45 % , which can generate about 1,700 MWe of thermal energy per hour .
Further researches have shown that Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) can achieve great safety by its design modification , lower and reasonable cost of its construction and power generation and has high efficiency in terms of electricity and power generation .
Therefore , further research and development funding for Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) should be provided as it stands in a good stead to become the future 's power generator in the near future .
Most scientists have agreed that we have to reduce the mission of green house gases as the impacts of global warming being more serious .
The nuclear power will not produce the green house gases and it will provide vast amounts of energy .
However , The U.S gave up building reactor since 1979 because of the defects of nuclear power and reactor such as the high cost of reactor , no appropriate coolant for reactor and wastes recycling system is not perfect .
Therefore , it is spark a significant controversy of whether the nuclear power should be rehabilitated .
For first aspect , SCWR is still facing the financial problem .
If the government use this money to build more fossil reactors , the increasing fossil reactors plants will help the situation of lack of energy .
It is true that the initial cost of building fossil plant is low , but the long-term costs which keeping it work are high says PBMR Company international marketing manager Gert Claassen .
Furthermore , the SCWR reactor efficiency and relatively simple design , it would be cheaper to build and run than normal reactors .
The second aspect , it is too difficult to find an appropriate coolant for nuclear reactor .
The third part , people are worrying about the waste of nuclear power , because the waste of reactor is radioactive normally .
Therefore , this waste are not radioactive and it is much safer compared with the wastes of last generation of reactor .
Moreover , SCWR build a system for water purification through supercritical oxidation .
Therefore , the SCWR is feasibility and reliable .
For pubic , the problem of global warming and other environmental problem made by emissions of fossil fuel will be eliminated .
For political , the nuclear power will maintain their energy source independence and reduce the conflicts of energy possessing .
To engineers and scientists , the applications of nuclear reactors would encourage them to find more efficient way to generate energy from reactors and the improve the safety of reactor in case of some accidents happened .
The question of whether we should have nuclear power plant as an energy resource is controversial .
People stand against it as they have little idea about the nuclear power plant .
Cost , safety and performance are three major aspects for opposition to this technology ; nevertheless , there is still an unyielding need to support further research and development funding for VHTR .
Still , in point of fact , nuclear power plant can reduce the expenditure in producing more energy in the long run .
Comparing with conventional plants , VHTR can bring out 50 % more electricity from the same amount of fuel .
Since that VHTR uses lower amount of fuel to produce higher amount of energy , it is much more economic than other power plants regardless the start up cost , as the start-up cost can be compensated in the long run .
Therefore , when sources of conventional plants are severely depleted , its cost will soar up high and become uneconomical ; on the other hand , VHTR uses half the amount of fuel to produce equal amount of energy , hence it can last longer .
Safety of a nuclear plant is the issue that public concerns the most .
It raised public 's uncertainty about the safety of developing new nuclear power plant .
VHTR is coated with a layer of graphite which can be used to slow down neutrons in order to control the nuclear chain reaction and it is covered with ultra hard ceramic layer .
Furthermore , it uses helium , an inert gas as coolant .
Therefore it can avoid any escape of radioactive material if an accident happens .
Moreover , a back-up emergency core cooling system ( ECCS ) is designed .
ECCS can remove excess heat and avoid damage to power plant in emergency cases , such as terrorism .
In addition , VHTR would be able to function without the need of reprocessing plutonium waste .
This would be able to prevent creation of nuclear power weapon as plutonium is an ingredient to produce advance nuclear weapon .
People assume that VHTR has lower performance compare to other kinds of Generation IV power sources .
This gives people a wrong assumption that VHTR is not highly performed .
Furthermore , VHTR is designed to efficiently produce both electricity and hydrogen at the meantime .
Likewise , VHTR is being designed with adequate safety precautions to prevent the happening of tragedy .
It has better performance as well since it has high efficiency and both electricity and hydrogen as its reaction product .
Consequently , more research and development funding should be subjected to VHTR .
As the society develops rapidly , the demand for energy also increase in tandem .
SFR is basically to use the sodium as coolant to produce nuclear energy .
On cost , building a SFR is estimated at US $ 610 million , while the VHTR would cost US $ 610 millionU.S .
Therefore , in a long run , the VHTR is more economical in producing a large amount of energy .
Some people also say that the efficiency of the SFR is about fifty percent at a temperature of 500 centigrade degree .
It is higher than the VHTR which is about forty percent at 500 centigrade degree ( Very high temperature reactor , 2009 ) .
For the SFR 500 centigrade degree is the suitable working temperature , which means the maximum efficiency for it is fifty percent .
However , for VHTR , the suitable working temperature is about 1500 centigrade degree .
At such a temperature , the efficiency of the VHTR is about 65 percent , which is much higher than the SFR ( Very-High-Temperature-Gas-Cooled-Reactor-Systems , 2009 ) .
Under the same standard , we can clearly see the efficiency of the VHTR is better .
What we should do is to plan what should we do when bad things happen .
Besides that , it can also do harm to the human beings .
Even though the coolant is leaking out , it will not do any harm to the environment and human beings .
To conclude , the initial cost of VHTR is higher , but in a long run its cost is much lower .
By considering the cost , efficiency and safety factors , we can judge that the very high temperature is a better choice in a long run .
With the speeding development throughout the whole world , the raising energy needs becomes an unavoidable problem nowadays .
In order to satisfy the needs , the generation IV reactor concept is brought forward for further research and utilization of nuclear power , and the Very High Temperature Reactor [ VHTR ] , which uses a graphite-moderated nuclear reactor with a once-through uranium fuel cycle under an outlet temperature of 1000 Â° C , is one of such concepts .
However , even before VHTR has been made use of , the public start to debate whether this concept can do more good than harm .
Although quite a number of people have no faith in the concept and provide some reasons , there exist solid evidences to show VHTR is worth of developing and can benefit the society .
As they state , in order to generate as much electricity as it is expensed in the U.S. every day , almost 400 nuclear power plants should be constructed and utilized .
The great discrepancy as if draws the end of VHTR 's development already .
In fact , this analysis is due to the mis-illustration .
One fact need to be clarified is that the opponents misuse the capacity of the conventional plants rather than that of VHTR .
Scientists suggest that the new generation reactor can squeeze 50 % more electricity from the same amount of fuels compared with the conventional plants .
Instead , this should always be a combination of complex methods .
In that case , whether VHTR can fulfil one country or even the global needs of electricity is unnecessary to be concerned .
As long as the concept is feasible and is better than the old ones , VHTR deserves for further research and thus can bring more advantage to the society .
In addition , opponents are also concern about the safety of the reactor especially when they recall the Chernobyl nuclear accident .
The great { thermal inertia } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.territorioscuola.com/wikipedia/ ? title = Volumetric_heat_capacity ] graphite and the single-phase , inert helium coolant can not react .
This can to a great extent ensure the safety during its reaction .
On the other hand , the corresponding design of the constructions of the nuclear power plants can prevent from nuclear leak even when disasters occur .
Simultaneously , the system will also bring the stuffs a safe environment .
In that case , we can safely draw the conclusion that VHTR is worth of further research and development .
July 17 , 1981 in Kansas City , Missouri , United States , while dozens of people was gathering on the walkway in Hyatt Regency Crown Centre and seeing a dance contest , the walkway collapsed and caused 114 people died and 200 injured .
After the accident investigated , the main cause of the accident was a significant change in the design of the walkway .
The original design by Jack D. Gillum was using a set of steel tie rod to suspend the two walkways to the ceiling , but the contractor proposed to use two separate tie rods : one collected one walkway to the ceiling , and the other connected the two walkways .
Jack D. Gillum and associates did not calculate the alternate plan before they assigned on the paper .
( Hyatt Regency Walkway Collapse , message from { http : //www.engineering.com/Library/ArticlesPage/tabid/85/articleType/ArticleView/articleId/175/Walkway-Collapse.aspx } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.engineering.com/Library/ArticlesPage/tabid/85/articleType/ArticleView/articleId/175/Walkway-Collapse.aspx ] )
In order to prevent such accidents happening , psychology is suggested to be introduced to the design process .
For example , cognitive psychology focuses on ways to improve memory and how to increase decision-making accuracy and social psychology are interested in the impact that social environment and interaction has on attitudes and behaviors ( Kendra , V.W .
For instance , if we introduce psychology to the case above , then the designer and the contractor communicated well ; so that the accidents would not happen .
The new generation reactors are planning to run at very high temperatures or high pressures ( Butler , D. ( 2004 , May 20 ) .
The more complex the process is , more difficult to predict the problems .
Sometimes only after the process is implemented , the problems will be known .
For example , the " Prestige " oil spilling was mainly caused by the rainstorm .
Prestige carried 77,000 tons of heavy fuel oil and was traveling on the sea near Spanish when it met rainstorm .
Finally the tanker sank and spilled the oil ( { http : //www.xooob.com/359429_1043815.html } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.xooob.com/359429_1043815.html ] ) .
Psychology only can deal with human error , not other factors .
It can not prevent all the accidents , as accidents are not only caused by human errors and as for some new designs , they must be tried to see where will the problems happened .
On January 28th , 1986 , the US Space Shuttle Challenger exploded 73 seconds after launch , killing the entire crew .
In other words , not only the technical factors , but also the human factors caused this disaster to appear .
Actually , from the time it was first scheduled to lift off on January 22nd , to the when it was finally launched on January 28th , liftoff was delayed several times for various reasons .
Well , it is true that the errors can not be prevented completely ; nevertheless , we should try our best to reduce the risk to the least level that we can accept .
Apparently , the condition of Challenger was not what we can accept as safe .
Secondly , should the decision-making system be made better , the tragedy could have been avoided .
Furthermore , they also had policy failure on competitive bidding for manufacturing company and defects of supervision system .
Although NASA have to face the pressure from the public and the political , they should aware the consequences of the failure , which might make the situation even worse .
The NASA officials seemed neither to have been warned adequately of the danger of launch in cold weather , nor be told emphatically enough the need of redesigning the O-rings .
Besides , the warning of air blast from a Boeing 757 aircraft was also ignored before the liftoff .
Communication did not flow effectively , which indirectly led to the tragedy 's happening .
As discussed above , the Challenger disaster 's causes lie not only on the technical factors , but also on the human factors .
Though it was indirect cause , its influence is so large that it was more important than the technical factor .
Psychology in design processes , whose significance has been showed in this accident , should be paid more attention to in the future engineering design .
Only in this way , can the safety of projects be improved efficiently and guaranteed .
There has been a debate between two Generation Four reactorsthe Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) and the Supercritical Water Reactor ( SCWR ) , which surrounds the issue of which reactor had superior performance .
In one hand , engineers use the most advanced technology and concept to design the VHTR .
On the other hand , the technology applied on the SCWR is developed from conventional technology of older type of nuclear reactorLight Water Reactor ( LWR ) .
The supporters of VHTR attack SCWR for its " obsolete " technology and its incapability of generating Hydrogen as a coproduct of electrcity .
When people are comparing the two types of reactors , they tend to focus on the temperature at which reactors operates .
As a result , a misleading conception arises , which is the VHTR works much more efficiently than the SCWR does .
These two energy states of neutrons are closely related the fission of two fuels , U235 and Np237 .
For people who are obssesed with the VHTR , one main reason would be it allows an easy way to generate a clean natural energyHydrogen .
Furthermore , unlike technology of using Hydrogen , which has just begun developing and is far from matured , electricity has been with human beings for over a hundred years .
The technology of electricity can be found everywhere on Earth and big automobile manufacturers have started to discuss the possibility of replacing fossil-fuel-powered cars with electricity-powered ones .
The SCWR is built for generation of low-cost electricity .
In addition , the two technologies needed build the SCWR are already at hand , which are widely-employed to by current Generatioon Three LWRs .
Unlike the VHTR which uses rare gas Helium as coolant , the SCWR simply uses water to cool down the system .
As a result , the SCWR costs much smaller amount of money to build and greatly simplifies the nuclear plant .
In conclusion , the most advanced stuff may not be suitable in a certain condition .
The SCWR has proven itself to be more capable at either high performance and low cost .
In this sense , the SCWR is a better nuclear reactor compared to the VHTR in our future .
Competitive costs and financial risks of nuclear energy systems are constantly compared .
The current rat race to develop the best reactor for use is still questionable as all the reactors have their own strengths and weaknesses .
At the turn of the millennium , the rising of Asian countries such as China and India has intensified the competition of energy .
In 2007 , China consumes a third as much oil as the United States , which burns a quarter of the world 's oil every day .
New York Times ) By 2030 , China and India together will import as much oil as the United States and Japan do today .
( Pachauri , R , IPCC ) Hence , fossil fuels are not a viable means to meet the increasing demand of energy .
Acknowledging the need of nuclear power to meet the world 's energy appetite , several countries have formed the Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) to research on the possible nuclear technologies and to mitigate the risks posed by them .
Better heat transfer also allows the coolant to have a slower flow rate of the coolant , thus saving cost by using of smaller pumps and piping .
As compared with the SCWR , the sodium can be kept at normal atmospheric pressure .
Also , the reactor core is at a lower temperature , thus relatively easier to manage .
Moving on to the cost , SCWR do offer much savings .
Consequently , the research could be focus towards developing irradiation resistant materials to be used for the reactor .
Researches into fuel cycle and physically stronger and more radiation resistant structural materials would minimise the operating costs with improved operations and performance .
Also , with support of countries such as Japan , France , and Russia , the cost of research is shared .
Finally , nuclear-enriched materials being kept at high temperature would prevent them from being stolen and use as weapons by terrorists .
Though the deployment cost is high at present , the burden will be shared by the many countries support the technology .
Facing the issues of rising oil prices and the long term availability of fossil fuels , governments now are rethinking their national energy strategies .
In recent years , despite the contentious debate of using nuclear power to meet our ever-increasing energy needs , the world starts to consider nuclear energy as a future fuel source which is believed to be a more environmentally friendly fuel as compared to fossil fuels .
Hence , late in 2002 , GIF ( Generation IV International Forum ) announced the selection of six reactor technologies which they believe represent the future shape of nuclear energy .
These were selected on the basis of being clean , safe and cost-effective means of meeting increased energy demands on a sustainable basis , while being resistant to usage of materials for weapons proliferation and secure from terrorist attacks ( US Department of Energy , 2009 ) .
However , this may be an unfounded concern in years to come when we consider the fact that the Korean and the US government have worked for the past three years on developing and validating advanced computational methods for simulating LOCA in a VHTR , in an attempt to prevent such an accident from happening ( Chang , 2006 ) .
The fuel pebbles used in VHTR are also very 'durable ' in the sense that it is very difficult to extract the trapped fission products inside which rendered it a less favorable choice as a nuclear weapon .
VHTR also adopts a passive safety feature in which in the event of an emergency , it does not require operator 's action to shutdown the plant safely .
Concern of graphite being an easily-combustible material is also addressed by experimental results that have shown that graphite can be heated to 'white-hot ' temperatures ( ~ 1650 Â° C ) without incurring ignition or self-sustained combustion ( Lee , 2009 ) .
Firstly , in terms of burn-up rate of the fuel , for VHTR , it is possible to burn up to 65 % ( US Department of Energy , 2008 ) of its initial fuel as compared to SCWR which is capable of only burn up to 45 % of the initial fuel ( Buongiorno , 2003 ) .
This is unlike SCWR which can only produce electricity .
Hydrogen production , whereby the process is energy-intensive is important as hydrogen holds enormous promise as a power source for the future generation .
Hence , the plant can be operated at high temperature without having to worry about corrosion of the plant pipes .
This is different from SCWR which uses water as the coolant and hence there is a possibility of pipe 's corrosion by water .
Lastly , proponents of SCWR claimed that the construction cost of VHTR plant is much higher than SCWR due to its high operating temperature .
However , after the concept of Generation IV reactors were raised by GIF in 2001 ( Butler , 2004 ) , whether governments should solely focus on current nuclear reactors or split the funding for the new generation has become a controversy .
Despite the accident in Chernobly , Ukraine , which was mainly caused by man-made operating errors ( Chernobly accident , 2009 ) , no major accident occurred in the past two decades .
Compared with funding the Gen IV reactors , they think that governments should rather use the money to reinforce the safety of currently operating reactors .
These wastes take thousands of years to lose their activity , thus they are not environmentally friendly in the long term ( Radioactive wastes , 2001 ) .
On the other hand , the cost of generating electricity from current nuclear reactors is already quite low ( 2.3 pence per kilowatt ) , which is competitive with other major sources ( The cost of generating electricity , 2004 ) .
But with the technology of Gen IV reactors , the efficiency can be improved to 45 % to 50 % due to extremely high operating temperature ( 1000 degrees Celsius ) ( Daniels , 2007 ) .
Moreover , the heat produced by the Gen IV reactors can be used to produce hydrogen from water or supplied to petrochemical industry ( The very-high-temperature reactor , n.d. ) .
The cogeneration and applications make the total efficiency even higher , thus further reduce the operating costs .
In order to optimize its power to meet the increasing demand of electricity as well as to maintain long term sustainability , governments should fund the Generation IV reactors instead of the old generations .
Fossil fuels , being non-renewable , are being exhausted at a rate faster than it can be replenished .
Hence , in order to solve the energy crisis we need to look for other sources of energy .
Nuclear power is an important source of energy for the future , hence more funding should be provided for research and development of nuclear reactors .
The public is worried that nuclear waste or nuclear materials during transportation or storage could be stolen or sabotaged by terrorists .
Nuclear waste or nuclear materials meant for energy production is not suitable to be used as nuclear weapons ( European Physical Society , 2007 ) .
Furthermore , newer generation of reactors , like the VHTR , produces much less nuclear waste at terror-proof facilities ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Therefore , with these improvements in technology , we are able to minimize or even eliminate these security issues facing nuclear generators .
Hence more research and development should be put in to nuclear reactors .
People are worried about the radiation leaked from nuclear facilities or nuclear waste .
All the factors mentioned above maybe true and hence put nuclear power plants in a bad light .
Hence , problems such as nuclear waste is harder to process can be solved with sufficient funding for research and development of nuclear power plants .
It has been a known fact that nuclear power plants require high-start up costs .
Funds have to be inserted so as to support the high technology machinery and also create a safe environment with proper safety guidelines protecting the reactors .
In addition , operating licenses have to be bought from the government , so as to ensure safe operation of the nuclear power plants .
However , once the basis infrastructure has been laid down , nuclear power turns in to a readily accessible and cheaply recoverable source of energy ( European Physical Society , 2007 ) .
Furthermore , with 4 of the 6 Generators-IV reactors being able to use reprocessed radioactive waste ( Butler , 2004 ) , it would be no surprise if nuclear power is able to last much longer than we expected .
It is widely known fact that nuclear power is able to produce much more energy compared to traditional fossil fuels .
Furthermore , comparing the Generation-IV reactors with older nuclear reactors , the new reactors are much more efficient , some of them like the VHTR produce hydrogen at the same time ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Nuclear power will make an important contribution to our future energy needs together with other alternatives ( European Physical Society,2007 ) Hence , in order to produce nuclear energy more effectively and cleanly we must put in more support and funding for the research and development of nuclear reactors .
They were very much surprised by the unique design and were amazed by the stunning price .
Although it was a surprising package , both positive and negative arguments about the car were found at the Auto Expo 2008 .
The main issue discussed was concerning safety .
The big question raised was whether Tata 's Nano was safe to drive in normal roads or not .
They proof that it is able to withstand a crash on a solid steel bar at a speed of 48 km/h .
Besides that Hichman , designer of Nano , explains that their target was to construct a modular body where structure was added to the base of the vehicle so that Nano will be able to meet the European safety regulations ( Schedel , 2009 ) .
Moreover , a test was even done at Motor Industry Research Association ( MIRA ) in the UK to proof their claim .
Although many supporting evidences were given by Tata , it is said that Tata made critical modifications specifically to meet the European and Indian test norms .
Besides that , Americans feel that the test was not sufficient as it was only done at a speed of 48km/h because many vehicles travel at much higher speed especially in highways ( Jenks , 2009 ) .
Tata only provides warranty for a period of only 18 months which is much less compared to the other cars .
It is a big surprise that Tata has just neglected some of the most important features like airbag , parking sensors , fog lamp and traction controls in their design .
Many who bought the car are complaining especially about the safety aspect of the car .
For example , a citizen of India has stated that there are not enough safety features and that the Nano is a very bad design ( Gangadharan , 2008 ) .
But their argument was that these features were not a necessity in Indian roads ( Massey , 2008 ) .
However , Tata should realise that the car is not only going to be sold in India but also going to be marketed in other countries .
So , if other countries are not willing to purchase the car because that it lacks safety features than it will be a big lose for Tata .
Drivers will confirm have difficulties spotting the vehicles which are coming from behind and this may even lead to accidents .
Besides that the wheels looks small .
So , while travelling in slope or heavy traffic it could be dangerous .
The more comfortable the driver feels , the more easily he will find to drive the car .
So , clearly it seems that there are some features that needs to be changed .
It would be better if tougher materials could be used , more safety features are added and some required changes are done to the current design .
But I strongly feel that those who want to purchase the car will not mind to pay a little more if it is going to provide a safer ride in the roads .
The reactor has been invented because of the increasing demand for an alternative source of energy that can substitute crude oil .
Nuclear reactors can produce cleaner and higher energy than the crude oil .
However , there is always an intention of the public to reject using nuclear reactors .
The disaster that happened at Chernobyl , Ukraine , in 1986 is one reason of the public 's anxiety .
Nonetheless , a VHTR ( Very-High- Temperature Reactor ) , which is one of the generation IV reactor concepts , has the technology to prevent the disaster by using helium as its coolant and by producing waste with low radioactivity .
The VHTR also can produce both electricity and hydrogen with a very efficient process , so the cost of running a VHTR will not be as high as other reactors in the long run .
This argument may arise because of the lack of knowledge about the helium .
This is indeed true ; however , the ongoing HTTR ( High-Temperature Engineering Test Reactor ) project in Japan gives us a clue that it is not impossible to develop a new strong material in the future .
In addition , the operation of the VHTR does not depend on the plutonium reprocessing , which is a controversial issue ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Thus , the VHTR waste is much safer than the existing nuclear reactors .
They say that the money that government spends on building the reactor can be used for other purchases .
This is indeed true ; however , the cost of building a VHTR is in fact not as costly as the other generation IV reactors .
Therefore , in the long run , it is profitable to build the VHTR because it can produce both electricity and hydrogen with a very efficient process .
To conclude , in spite of claims that nuclear reactors are dangerous and costly , the VHTR with its improved design can overcome these issues .
Mention nuclear power and the general consensus are fear and rejection , and Chernobyl comes to their mind .
These reactors , still in the designing and testing phase , excel in areas of sustainability , safety , economics and proliferation resistance ( Bouchard and Bennett,2008 ) , all which is specially intended to address all issues and challenges that nuclear power faces in a world combating the production of greenhouse gases but in the safest possible way .
Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) emerges from the six as one of the most promising and is currently being heavily researched on ; but is it worth the funds and efforts when safety concerns are still present and worse , unaddressed ?
For its performance level , the operating core temperatures of the reactor is capable of reaching to an almighty peak of a 1000 ( Chapin , et al 2004 ) , figures that will not only raise questions about its viability as well as the safety measures in place for such a high amount of energy , since temperature is directly proportional to the energy level of a closed system .
And because of the heights in the Celsius scale , the materials used in the reactor can not be of regular quality , much less inferiority .
The use of high temperature creates an extremely volatile and sensitive situation which on one hand raises output efficiency ( OECD Nuclear Energy Agency , 2000 ) , but also requires a precise state-of-the-art monitoring system that further increases the production prices .
Throughout the six new reactors , they mainly differ only in their choice of coolant used in the system .
Helium gas is abundant on the Sun 's atmosphere but only at trace level in Earth 's surface ( AIR LIQUIDE , 2009 ) .
In addition , helium is not the only coolant that is chemically inert with the fuel ; molten lead is another viable option and yet plentiful in the Earth 's crust .
Last for but not least , gaseous coolants have low thermal transfer properties , hence requiring an intermediate heat exchange with a larger surface area ( Chapin , et al 2004 ) .
LFR on the other hand , is more suitable ; the relatively smaller scale of operation and hence energy output may be inferior compared to VHTR , but it is not feasible and unsafe for a large nuclear plant in a developing country where security and social unrest are issues .
LFR is a more portable option , thus more resistant against terrorism and weapon conversion since it is too stable to become a destructive tool anyway .
Maintenance fees for VHTR will also be a tight spot to a growing nation , an area of concern which can be resolved by the use of LFR , which requires refueling once every 20 years .
The system core temperatures of LFR can attain up to 500 ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2005 ) , almost 50 % lower than that of VHTR and present significant differences in the operations of the plants .
Molten lead , compared to helium , is a superior and cheaper heat transfer medium and hence increasing the portability of the power plant by reducing the need for a large intermediate heat exchanger .
In conclusion , LFR may not be as proficient in energy production when compared to VHTR , but it addresses critical issues that VHTR fails to achieve .
As the population 's reliance on technology advances and grows , a greater need for electricity energy to power these computer gadgets has since sparked an inevitably concern as many worry that fossil fuels , as being used over the years to generate electricity , are not sufficient enough to accommodate all the needs .
Moreover , global warming nowadays has been growing at an alarming rate , thanks partly to the excessive air pollution generated along by fossil fuels .
Therefore , a seek for higher efficient and safe energy supply is desperately needed and it is already on the agenda of all countries .
With this , nuclear power has since expanded to replace conventional fuels because of the higher efficiency it can provide to the world .
Many concepts are reviewed to improve the already competent nuclear reactors and so far , generation IV reactor concepts are among those which stood up among the crowd that are worth developed .
Safety factor is heavily considered because if accident occurs at nuclear reactor sites , it can result in massive releases of radioactivity .
And it , by means , includes the development of passive heat removal systems , low power density and easily cool-able geometry .
However some have argued that VHTR is unsafe as it is operating at a higher temperature and it would easily be the target of terrorist attack .
And some have also put doubts on the ability of passive heat removal system because if it fails to remove heats in the reactor , leakage of radioactive components will occur .
Certainly , accident disasters happened in Three Mile Island , Tokaimura and Chernobyl before should not ever repeat again .
But , according to Forrest J. Remick , professor emeritus of nuclear engineering and a former associate vice president for research at Penn State , he claims that VHTR is safe and this concept has been demonstrated in several test reactors in the United States , Germany , China and South Africa .
However , some experts have pointed out that if such high temperature is stimulated within a reactor , new hardy alloy may be necessary to protect the inside layer of the reactor .
To get those alloys it would already cost millions .
How about the construction cost of the entire power plant which is still unknown yet ?
When the cost is reduced , cheaper electricity can be provided to public .
But in term of performance , VHTR is a more efficient concept compared to others in generation four nuclear reactor concepts .
Even though it might proved costly at the beginning but it pays off well as it produces both electricity and hydrogen fuel instead of electricity only .
High temperature processed in the reactor can be used as a condition to yield hydrogen from sulphur-iodine cycle , which is a series of thermo-chemical processes that will fail without sufficient source of heat .
Hydrogen fuel produced can be used in vehicle as its onboard fuel .
Current stage for VHTR development is just at the very beginning point .
There are enormous items left to do in order for this concept to success in future .
Therefore , more research and development should be carried out so that in future this concept can become the energy supply for everyone in this earth .
However , as global warming is becoming a more pressing issue , we have now turned to nuclear reactor to provide us clean energy .
Here comes the question on which generation IV nuclear reactor we should choose .
One of the main reasons on LFR being safer is LFR , which operates at around 550 degree Celsius , has a lower outlet temperature than VHTR , which operates at around 1000 degree Celsius ( Butler .
In short , operating at 1000 degree Celsius is not much of a safety issue since VHTR is safe and reliable at high temperature .
In addition , in terms of the coolant used by the two reactors , VHTR is safer than LFR .
With the presence of the radioactive polonium and the corrosiveness of lead , it is not safe to use lead as a coolant .
In terms of cost to build the reactor , LFR cost around US $ 700 million ( Neil W. Brown .
2006 ) while VHTR cost around US $ 1.1 billion ( Butler .
In addition , in term of the cost of coolant , lead cost around US $ 0.24 per 100 grams ( MetalPrice.com ) while helium cost around US $ 5.20 per 100 grams .
However , there are other factors that will also affect the cost of operating the reactor , such as maintenance cost .
With the economic production of hydrogen ( H2 ) by thermochemical cycles , it can reduce the maintenance cost for operating the VHTR .
The final argument advanced by the supporters of LFR is LFR perform much better than VHTR .
However , recycling of nuclear waste will result in the production of plutonium , which can be used as nuclear weapon ( Butler .
Hence , recycling of nuclear waste is not safe in term of security .
It is because the higher the outlet temperature , the greater is the efficiency of electrical generation .
VHTR generates electrical energy in two ways , from nuclear reactant directly and from hydrogen fuel .
In conclusion , VHTR is safe because it is designed to attained thermal stability and it uses inert coolant , which is helium .
Hence , it should be evident that VHTR works better than LFR in term of security , cost and performance .
Since VHTR is one of the better options among the generation IV nuclear reactors and it is feasible , we should invest and support in further research and development on VHTR .
